title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Cook pudding with milk as directed on box.
When pudding comes to boil, stir immediately into dry cake mix.
Pour this into a greased and floured cake pan (9 x 13-inch).
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts on top of cake mix.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable couscous
directions: In a 5-quart Dutch oven, heat 1 tablespoon of the oil over moderate heat.
Add onions.
Saute, stirring occasionally for 5 to 7 minutes, until golden brown.
Add carrots, potatoes and garlic. Cook for 2 minutes.
Stir in stock, tomatoes, thyme, basil, salt, pepper and bay leaf.
Bring liquid to a boil.
Lower heat.
Simmer vegetables, covered, for 5 minutes.
Add parsnips.
Simmer, covered, for 3 minutes.
Add zucchini, yellow squash and chickpeas and simmer, covered, 8 minutes, or until vegetables are just tender.
Remove bay leaf.
Using glass measuring cup, remove 1 1/2 cups liquid from Dutch oven to saucepan.
Stir in raisins and remaining oil, then bring to a boil and stir in couscous.
Remove from heat.
Let stand, covered, 10 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Serve the vegetables over the couscous.
Serves 4 to 6, 570 calories per serving.

title: easy caramel frosting
directions: Melt margarine, stir in brown sugar.
Cook and stir over low heat 2 minutes.
Add milk.
Continue stirring until boiling. Remove from heat, cool to lukewarm.
Add confectioners sugar and vanilla while beating.
Beat until spreading consistency.

title: mozzarella meat loaf
directions: Grease 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine meat, bread crumbs, egg, onion, salt and oregano in a bowl.
Stir in 3/4 of tomato sauce.
Cut a piece of waxed paper 15 inches long.
Form meat into a 13 x 9-inch rectangle on waxed paper.
Sprinkle meat with cheese and mushrooms.
Starting with narrow end of meat, lift waxed paper to roll meat in jelly roll fashion.
Place meat, seam side down, in prepared pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 30 minutes.
Remove drippings from baking pan.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over meat loaf and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: candy
directions: Cook until boils.
Add 1 cup peanut butter until melts.
Pour over 5 cups corn flakes and drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: crunchy cucumber sticks
directions: First day:
Peel 7 lbs. cucumbers.
Take seed out and cut lengthwise.
Soak 24 hours in 2 gals. water and 2 c. lime water.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce, onion juice, salt and pepper to taste.
Chop up as many shrimp as you want.
Cook until all are mixed well.

title: chili dip
directions: Mix chili, cream cheese, olives, salsa and serve.

title: baked flounder
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use a baking dish just large enough to hold fish fillets and spray dish with Pam or other no cholesterol spray.
Rub fillets with lemon juice, salt and pepper; place in dish.
Sprinkle with tarragon.
Cover with sour cream and bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with chives and parsley.
Serve immediately.
This will serve six.
Great for dieters.

title: sunshine cake(diabetic)
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Make a well in dry ingredients.
Add in order the oil, egg yolks, orange juice, liquid sweetener, egg whites and cream of tartar.
Beat until smooth.
Add 1/2 teaspoon cream of tartar to egg whites; beat until stiff.
Add yolk mixture to beaten egg whites; gently fold in until well blended.
Do not overmix.
Pour into a 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve plain or with fresh fruit.

title: fish curry
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender, except fish and onions. Layer fish and onion rings; pour curry mixture over.
Bake at 300° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken in salted water.
Remove from water and cut into bite size pieces.
Boil noodles in chicken stock until tender, approx. 10 minutes.
Cut velveeta into chunks.
Add cheese, chicken, peas, salt and pepper after draining water off noodles. Mix well and serve.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Do not add meat, chips and dressing until ready to serve.
Feeds a lot of people.

title: 48 hour cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage very fine. Place shredded cabbage in a large bowl. Add the chopped onions, green and red peppers and celery. Mix together the sugar, celery seed, mustard seed, salt and vinegar. Pour the mixture over the cabbage mixture and stir well.

title: magic bars
directions: Melt stick of margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat margarine in
1 1/2 cups graham cracker crumbs.
Pour evenly the condensed milk.
Sprinkle chocolate chips; sprinkle chopped nuts.
Top with flaked coconut.
Press down lightly.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
This is delicious and also very easy.

title: low-fat stroganoff
directions: Cook ground turkey and turkey bacon until brown.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Drain off excess fat and liquid.
Blend flour, salt, paprika and pepper with meat-onion mixture.
Stir in undiluted soup.
Cook uncovered over medium-low heat for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring often.
Remove from heat and stir in sour cream, mixing until well blended.
Serve over cooked rice or noodles.

title: cinnamon chip gems
directions: Beat butter and cream cheese in large bowl until well blended; stir in flour, sugar and almonds.
Cover; refrigerate about 1 hour.
Divide dough into 4 equal parts. Shape each part into 12 smooth balls.
Place each ball in small muffin cup (1 3/4 inches in diameter); press evenly on bottom and up side of each cup.
Heat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs in small bowl.
Add Eagle Brand
and vanilla; mix well place 7 Hershey Cinnamon Chips in bottom of each muffin cup; fill a generous 3/4 full with Eagle Brand mixture.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until tops are puffed and just beginning to turn golden brown.
Cool 3 minutes. Sprinkle about 15 chips on top of the filling.
Cool completely in pan on rack.
Remove from pan using small metal spatula or sharp knife. Cool and store at room temperature.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Add 3 cups water, onion, celery, 1 teaspoon of salt and 1/8 teaspoon of pepper.
Bring to boiling point.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 to 25 minutes.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: Put into measuring cup and set aside.
Mix water, eggs and vinegar.
Blend in mixing bowl flour, salt, sugar and shortening. Pour water, egg and vinegar mix over dry ingredients.
Mix into a ball.
Can store in plastic bag in refrigerator or use now.

title: easy barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
For spareribs, brown ribs in oven for 30 minutes to remove some of the fat.
Drain.
Add sauce. Marinate for several hours or overnight.
Sauce is also good over poultry.

title: six layer toffee torte
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients.
Dissolve 2 teaspoons coffee in 1 cup boiling water.
Add to bowl and beat for 2 minutes.
Pour batter into 3 (8-inch) greased and floured round cake pans and bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely.

title: vegetable sandwich spread
directions: Grate vegetables; drain well.
Mix mayonnaise and cream cheese together.
Add well drained vegetables.
Add a dash of salt and red pepper.
Spread on your favorite bread.

title: people puppy chow
directions: Melt together the butter, chocolate chips and peanut butter. Pour over cereal. Stir well. Add powdered sugar and stir until coated.

title: junk salad
directions: Mix well and serve.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: Cook bacon in a large kettle or saucepan until crispy-brown; remove.
Drain on paper toweling; reserve.
Saute onion, carrots and celery in the bacon fat about 5 minutes or until tender. Drain clams; reserve liquid.
Add potatoes.
Cook 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Remove bay leaf.
Add clams and reserved bacon.
Simmer 5 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley, if you wish.
Makes 6 servings.

title: my favorite rolls
directions: Soften the yeast in the warm water. Combine the boiling water, oil, sugar and salt. Cool to lukewarm and add yeast.
Stir in and beat well the flour and milk.
Add flour to make soft dough. Chill, then make out in rolls or store dough in refrigerator for a couple of days, making out as needed.
When rolls are made out, allow to double in bulk in warm place before baking at 400° until golden brown.
Dough may be used for cinnamon rolls or any fancy sweet rolls.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Blend mayonnaise with lemon juice and stir into chicken mixture. Pour into 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese and potato chips.
Bake at 450° until a few bubbles appear on top.

title: marinade meat
directions: Put all ingredients in jar and shake.
Pour over any cut of meat.
Leave overnight.
Grill; slice thin.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill for 2 hours before serving. Serve with fresh fruit as a dip.

title: coconut milk cake
directions: Combine sugar to egg whites and beat until stiff.
Combine all other ingredients and beat with electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Fold in egg white mixture.
Prepare 9 x 13-inch pan with grease and flour.
Pour mixture into pan making sure all bubbles are removed by pounding pan on the table several times.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: taco sauce
directions: Peel and chop tomatoes or puree them to equal one gallon. Seed the peppers if you wish mild sauce.
Run the peppers, onion and garlic through food processor if you wish.
Put all ingredients in a large pan and add salt, chili powder, cumin and vinegar.
Cook down some (the longer cooked the better the sauce and hotter).
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Place softened ice cream in cookie pie crust.
Place in freezer until ready to serve.
Slice into pieces.
Top each slice with chocolate syrup, top that with a spoonful of whipped topping and garnish with pecan.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Mix together first 8 ingredients.
Add salt and pepper.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Melt oleo and mix with Ritz crackers. Spread on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: watermelon rind preserves
directions: Remove outside green peel and inside red ripened part of the melon.
Weigh to be sure there is 1 pound of the light green rind. Cut into 1-inch cubes.
Cover with cold water and let come to a good boil.
Drain off the water; add sugar, lemon, lemon rind and a small amount of water to make a syrup.
Boil until rind is clear and syrup is rather thick.
Pour into hot, sterilized jars and seal at once.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add others.
Line pans with wax paper.
Bake in a 300° oven for 1 1/2 or 2 hours.

title: super dip
directions: Cook spinach in well salted water until tender; drain thoroughly and mash.
Mix with other ingredients and let set 24 hours.
Sprinkle with paprika before serving.
Keeps well in the refrigerator.
Makes 3 cups.

title: caramel oatmeal chewies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine 1 1/2 cups flour, brown sugar, soda and salt.
Stir in margarine, mixing until well blended.
Reserve 1 cup.
Press remaining onto bottom of prepared pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Top with nuts and chocolate pieces.

title: crab and cheese hors d'oeuvres
directions: Place muffin halves on cookie sheet.
Mix together the butter, cheese, mayonnaise, garlic powder and crab meat.
Spread mixture onto English muffins.
Cut each muffin into 4 squares.
Put into freezer until frozen.
Remove and separate as many squares as you want for a serving and put into plastic bag.
Refreeze these and serve when ready to use.
Bake at 425° until browned.

title: salisbury steak with mushroom gravy
directions: Combine meat, pepper and salt.
Shape into 3 or 4 plum oval patties.
Pan-fry in hot fat in a skillet or broil 4 to 6 minutes each side.
Serve with mushroom gravy.
Makes 2 generous servings.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Keep 2 tablespoons crumbs for crumbs on top.
Add remaining ingredients.
Makes 1 cake in glass pan. Oil and flour pan.
Put crumbs on top.
Sprinkle cinnamon.

title: frito salad
directions: Mix in a large bowl and serve.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1 cup pecans.
Mold into 1 large or 2 small balls.
Roll balls in remaining pecans. Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours before serving (can be frozen).

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients in a well-greased casserole.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread in oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch). Heat oven to 350°.
Bake until golden brown about 25 minutes.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixer bowl.
Blend, then beat at medium speed on electric mixer for 4 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch fluted tube or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes, or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean and begins to pull away from sides of pan.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Remove from pan; finish cooling on rack.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: fruit smoothies
directions: In blender, combine milk, yogurt, banana, whole strawberries, pineapple with its juice and lemon juice; cover and blend until smooth. With blender running, gradually add ice cubes; blend until smooth. Garnish with halved strawberries, if desired. Serve immediately.

title: cheese cake cookies
directions: Place paper cups in muffin tins.
Place a wafer round side down in bottom of paper cup.
Cream together cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Pour mixture over wafers almost to the top of the cup.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool and top with pie filling.

title: beat like thunder gingerbread
directions: Put all ingredients in mixing bowl in order given. Beat like thunder. Bake in greased muffin pans, regular size, at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cranberry delight
directions: Put lemon juice and Cointreau in shallow dish. Sprinkle gelatin over it and dissolve.
Into a saucepan large enough to hold all ingredients, drain pineapple chunks.
Save pineapple for later use. Add sugar and powdered ginger.
Cook over medium to medium-low heat.
Wash cranberries and drain well.
Add cranberries to the pineapple juice mixture and cook, stirring constantly, until cranberries start popping.
Take the pan off the heat and add the gelatin mixture which should be a pancake.
Tear into pieces and mix with the cranberries. Add the pineapple chunks and walnuts.
Let mixture come to room temperature.
Place into canning jars and store in refrigerator.
Can be stored up to 6 months.

title: ada brady's chicken with pastry strips
directions: Read directions first.
Cook one cut up chicken (top of stove). Mix flour, margarine and salt.
Sprinkle with cold water and mix until consistency of pie crust dough.
With rolling pin, roll thin and cut in strips 2 1/2 x 1 1/2-inches.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.

In boiling chicken broth (lift chicken out of broth and set aside), drop strips in and (careful not to burn), shake pot often and do not stir much (the stirring breaks up the strips). Careful not to add too many strips to broth.
If so, it will be too thick.
Cut heat real low and cook slow 30 minutes shaking pot often.
Drop chicken back in pot and let stand 20 minutes.
Add a little black pepper.
You may need one or two cups of boiling water added to broth to keep it all thin enough.
While cooking, a few pats of butter adds to flavor.
Eat and enjoy.

title: southern style baked corn
directions: Mix undrained whole kernel corn, cream-style corn, eggs, corn bread mix and sour cream in a bowl.
Stir in butter and add salt and pepper.
Spoon into 10 x 10-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese; bake for 15 minutes longer.

title: chocolate chip pumpkin bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream sugars, butter and eggs.
Add flour, pumpkin, water, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and cloves.
Mix thoroughly.
Fold in chocolate chips.

title: squash pickles
directions: Slice squash 1/2-inch thick, then add onions, peppers and garlic.
Cover with salt and ice; mix and let stand for 3 hours. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over drained squash mixture. Heat just to boiling and put in jar and seal.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Make a roux of butter, flour and milk. Add potatoes and onions. Bring to a boil. Simmer 10 minutes. Add bacon, sour cream, cheese, salt and pepper.

title: grandma's bohemian bread dumplings
directions: Mix together in a large bowl everything except the bread and water for boiling dumplings. Hand beat for 5 minutes. (Yes, you will get tired!)

title: baked squash
directions: Cut up squash and onions.
Cook in salted water until tender; drain.
Mash with potato masher.
Mix chicken soup, sour cream and pimentos.
Melt margarine over stuffing mix.
Line baking dish with 2/3 of stuffing, then pour squash filling on top with rest of stuffing.
Bake at 340° for 35 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until frothy. Beat in sugar.
Add oil and vanilla and beat until thick and lemon colored.
Add loosely packed, grated zucchini.
Sift dry ingredients and add to egg mixture. Fold in pecans.
Pour into 2 (8 x 4-inch) greased and floured loaf pans or 4 small loaf pans.

title: orange jello
directions: Mix Cool Whip, cottage cheese and dry jello well.
Add drained fruit and stir.
Let set about 6 hours.
You can change jello flavors and fruits to your taste.
(Example: strawberry, peach with peaches, etc.)

title: baked chicken breast fillets
directions: Set oven at 400°.
Use a cast-iron skillet or baking sheet. Dip chicken in yogurt.
Mix all ingredients in a bowl and dip chicken in seasoning; coat well.
Bake for 1 hour, turning it every 20 minutes.

title: orange fruit salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and add the other ingredients after cutting the peaches in small pieces.
Congeal.

title: bavarian beef
directions: Tenderize steak or pound until thin.
Cut into 2 x 1-inch strips.
Blend cornstarch, salt, black pepper and garlic powder. Brown meat in oil; add onion.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Stir in beer, broth, pepper sauce and brown sugar.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add carrots and cook 15 minutes longer or until meat is tender.
Spoon over rice. Makes 4 servings.

title: almond tea
directions: Mix together.
Chill and serve over ice.

title: creamy beef and rice
directions: Combine all ingredients, blending until smooth.
Heat until hot.
Serve over fluffy rice.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: french torte
directions: Use 8 x 11 1/2-inch glass pan.
Melt butter.
Add ingredients of crust together.
Press to bottom and side of pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Crumble and let cool.
Press to bottom and sides of pan again and add 2 cans cherry pie filling mixed with 4 tablespoons water.

title: billygoat cookies
directions: Add eggs one at a time, while mixing.
Cream sugar and butter. Add cinnamon and vanilla.
Cut dates fine.
Dredge with flour; add to mixture with nut meats.
Dissolve soda in a little warm water. Add to mixture as you add flour alternately; mix well.
Drop by small spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill overnight.
Put liquid mixture in ice cream freezer.
Line with ice and salt alternating layers.

title: strawberry-banana yogurt smoothie
directions: Place all ingredients in blender container. Cover, blend on high speed for 30 seconds or until blended. Pour evenly into 4 glasses. Serve immediately.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in 10 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with buttered Pepperidge Farm stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
May be stored in fridge overnight if necessary.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and oil well.
Add sugar and beat.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add dry ingredients, milk and vanilla.
Bake in 10-inch tube pan (grease and dust with cocoa) for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.
Wrap in foil when cool.

title: lo mein
directions: In large skillet, cook egg noodles in butter until brown. Add all other ingredients. Cook 10 minutes on stove. Pour into 9 x 13 baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Cream 3 tablespoons sugar and butter.
Add pretzels and spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350° or microwave 2 1/2 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and topping.
Spread over crust and refrigerate 1 hour before next step.

title: tuna or ham casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together with 1/2 bag of chips.
Put in casserole dish and sprinkle remaining chips on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into ice cream bucket.
Finish filling with milk.
Freeze.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix everything together in large bowl.
Grease loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until browned on top.

title: lasagna
directions: Bring water, salt and oil to boil.
Cook noodles until until "al dente" about 15 to 18 minutes.
Drain and dry noodles.

title: german apple cake
directions: Sift sugar, flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Beat in eggs and oil.
Mix in apples, raisins, nuts and dates.
Batter will be stiff. Bake for 50 minutes.

title: liver pate
directions: Have cream cheese and braunschweiger at room temperature.
Mix all the ingredients together.
Serve with crackers.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In a large casserole dish, place rice.
Add chopped broccoli, chopped onion, grated cheese, sliced water chestnuts and mushroom soup.
Mix together gently until combined.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chicken wings deluxe
directions: Wash wings and cut off tips.
Split wings into two legs.
Mix remaining ingredients into a marinade and marinate for 2 hours in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serve warm.

title: chicken italian and rice
directions: In a cake pan, add one small bag of uncooked rice.
Then add the cream of chicken soup, water and Italian dressing.
Mix everything together well.
Then put your chicken on top.
Cover with foil.
Cook at 375° for 1 hour.
Then uncover and stir the rice up.
Re-cover the pan.
Let cook for 1 more hour.
If you like your rice a little dry, uncover pan and then let it cook for another 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes in a loaf pan.

title: super easy pound cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Add and mix in frosting.
Bake in tube or Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.
(Also good, chocolate cake mix and cherry pie filling.)

title: angel biscuits
directions: Stir shortening into flour and sugar.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add buttermilk to this, then add to flour mixture.
Mix well.
Turn out on floured sheet.
Roll to 1/4-inch biscuits. Reserve remainder in refrigerator for next day.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: grandma cannon's fudge
directions: Stir and cook the first 5 ingredients until soft ball stage, then add the salt and vanilla.
Remove from heat.
Let set until warm.
Beat with mixer until fudge loses its shine.
Add the nuts. Pour into buttered pan.
Refrigerate.

title: italian potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Peel and dice potatoes.
In large casserole dish combine all ingredients.
Stir well.
Cover with foil.
Bake and stir occasionally.
Cook until potatoes are soft.

title: potato and beef casserole
directions: Put potatoes in a greased oblong pan, alternately with meat; sprinkle with onion around.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour soup and water mixture over it.
Bake in 350° oven, after sprinkling cracker crumbs over the top, for 45 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and butter well, then add remaining ingredients.
Pour in greased pan.
Bake in an 18 x 12 x 1-inch pan at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cover after 10 minutes of cooling time with waxed paper.
Finish cooling.
Ice as soon as cool. German chocolate cake icing is wonderful on these brownies.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan or dish.
Lay broccoli in bottom of pan; next lay cut up chicken.
Cover completely with milk and soup mixed together.
Cover with Cheddar cheese.
Cover with herb stuffing mix made according to box directions.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan and place in oven to melt.
After removing pan from pan, sprinkle crumbs and press down with fork.
Sprinkle coconut over crumbs; add layer of chocolate chips and then a layer of pecans.
Drizzle with condensed milk.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into 30 bars.

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix ingredients together lightly with a fork.
Place in a lettuce cup and garnish with 1/2 hard-cooked egg.
Chill.
Tuna may be substituted with 2 ounces diced cooked chicken, ham, etc. Yield:
1 serving.
Carbohydrate 21 g, protein 19 g, fat 5 g, calories 205.
One serving = 2 meat low-fat exchange, 1/2 bread starch exchange.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs.
Mix and add salt, bananas, nuts and flour. Mix soda in tepid water and add to flour mixture.
Put in greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake for 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: skillet squash medley
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, melt butter; stir in all remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until crisply tender (8 to 10 minutes).
Yield: 6 servings.

title: green beans with hamburger
directions: Cook and stir ground beef and onion in large skillet until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Stir in garlic, 1 1/2 cups water, the soy sauce and molasses; heat to boiling.
Add green beans and heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Blend cornstarch and 1/4 cup cold water; stir gradually into meat mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Serve over rice; garnish with onion rings.
If desired, pass additional soy sauce. Makes 4 servings.

title: peach pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan and set aside.
Cream together the butter or margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, soda and salt in separate bowl. Mix together sour cream and chopped peaches.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream and peaches, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Beat well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla and almond extract.
Pour batter into prepared pan and bake for 75 to 80 minutes or until cake tests done.
Makes one 10-inch cake.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash and dry tomatoes and cut out the hard stem area. Slice tomatoes about 1/4 inch thick. Combine cornmeal, salt and pepper. Coat bottom of cast iron skillet with bacon grease or oil. Dip each tomato slice in buttermilk, then in cornmeal. Lay each slice in hot skillet and turn down heat to medium. Fry until golden brown on both sides, turning once. Drain on paper towels.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a bowl, melt butter.
Add olive oil, garlic, parsley, onion, lemon juice, basil, oregano and salt. Place shrimp in one layer on large, shallow baking pan.
Pour butter mixture over shrimp.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Bake 5 minutes in oven.
Place pan closely under heated broiler briefly, just until shrimp are flecked with brown.
Serve with noodles or rice.

title: favorite apple pie
directions: Peel apples; slice thin.
Combine sugar, flour, spices and salt.
Mix with apples.
Put into pastry lined pan; dot with butter.
Add top crust.
Brush with milk and sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: pasta casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and pepper in skillet.
Add can of tomatoes.
Cook macaroni until tender.
Place half of macaroni in baking dish.
Pour half of beef mixture on macaroni.
Sprinkle half of cheese.
Top with rest of macaroni.
Pour rest of beef mixture and top with remainder of cheese.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Brown onion and garlic in 1/4 cup of olive oil.
Add canned tomatoes or 1/2 can of water.
Simmer in saucepan for 30 minutes. Wash, dry and slice eggplant crosswise.
Place in a bowl of salted water for 10 minutes.
Dry slices on paper towels.
Fry in hot oil until soft and light brown.
Place one layer of eggplant in baking dish.
Cover with sauce mixture; add cheese, then layer again and repeat until used up.
Bake at 300° until browned, about 30 minutes.

title: layered salad
directions: Place layers into a clear bowl.
Let stand for 24 hours in refrigerator before serving.

title: beef marinade
directions: Mix marinade ingredients together and put into large zipper-type plastic bag with meat.
Refrigerate several hours or more.
Bring meat to room temperature, then broil or grill.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Cream butter and flour; add nuts.
Press into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until light brown.

title: homemade granola
directions: Combine all dry ingredients except dry fruit in a large mixing bowl.
Combine honey and oil in a large measuring cup.
Pour over ingredients, folding in with a large wooden spoon until well coated.
Pour into a
large roasting pan and bake at 250° about 1 hour, or until light brown in color, stirring occasionally.
Cool and store in glass jars with tight lid.

title: chicken tostadas
directions: Spread cream cheese on tostada shells.
Toss chicken with salsa; add on top of cream cheese.
Add lettuce, tomato and cheese.

title: chicken 'n rice salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine rice, chicken, peas, celery and grated onion.
In another bowl, blend together mayo, salt and pepper.
Thoroughly mix into chicken and rice mixture.
Chill 1 hour.
Serve with lettuce.

title: sausage and egg puff
directions: Brown sausage; drain on paper towel.
Grease a 2-quart casserole dish.
Spread bread cubes over bottom.
Sprinkle sausage over bread cubes.
Spread cheese over sausage.
Beat eggs.
Add milk, salt and mustard.
Pour over ingredients in dish.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: koch kase(cooked cheese)
directions: Cut butter into cheese; add other ingredients.
Bring to boil in top of double boiler.
Stir well as it hangs on pot.
Add caraway seed.
Best served warm, but can be refrigerated.

title: apple orchard punch
directions: Combine apple juice, cranberry and orange juice.
Stir.
Add ginger ale; stir.
Slice thin vertical apple slices to float on top of the punch.

title: grandma wells' 1968 chocolate pie
directions: Combine all ingredients (except milk and pie crust); beat good.
Add milk and cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie crust and top with meringue.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown and crumble sausage with onion.
Drain.
Spoon sausage into a large greased casserole dish.
Tear bread in small pieces and place on top of sausage.
Beat eggs and milk in blender and pour over sausage and bread.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper; put grated cheese on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: chocolate mint pie
directions: Mix together cookie crumbs and butter; press into 9-inch pie plate to make crust.
Freeze 1 hour.
Spread ice cream in an even layer.
Freeze 8 hours.
Spoon whipped cream over top.
Garnish with candies.
Serve immediately.
Serves 8.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti in boiling water until just tender (do not overcook).
Melt butter; blend in flour.
Stir broth into flour mixture.
Add cream.
Cook until mixture thickens and bubbles. Add salt and pepper, drained spaghetti, mushrooms, green peppers and cooked turkey and cheeses.
Stir and put into casserole dish. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: jello pie
directions: Let jello cool, then put in graham cracker-lined pie pan.

title: zucchini freezer jam
directions: Cook zucchini in pot on stove for 1 hour.
Add sugar, pineapple and Sure-Jell.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add apricot Jell-O.
Stir well.
Pour into pint jars.
Let stand, uncovered, 24 hours at room temperature.
Put lids on and freeze until ready to use.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Put chicken in 2 quarts boiling water with carrots, onions and 2 teaspoons salt.
Cook slowly until tender and the meat leaves the bones.

title: fruity popsicles
directions: Sprinkle gelatine over water.
Let stand 1 minute.
Add hot juice, stirring until gelatine dissolves.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 6 popsicle molds or paper cups.
Freeze until partially frozen.
Insert ice cream sticks; freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer 5 minutes before serving.
Remove mold. Makes 6 popsicles.

title: sweet potato surprise
directions: Arrange sweet potatoes in buttered baking dish. Combine sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and apricot juice in saucepan.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly. Stir in apricots, butter and pecans. Pour over sweet potatoes. Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut lemon torte
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, combine sweetened condensed milk, egg yolks, ReaLemon brand, rind and food coloring, if desired.
Over medium heat, cook and stir until thickened, about 10 minutes.
Chill. Meanwhile, prepare cake mix as package directs.
Pour batter into two well-greased and floured 8 or 9-inch round layer cake pans.
Bake 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from pans; cool thoroughly.
With sharp knife, remove crust from top of each cake layer.
Split layers.
Spread equal portions of lemon mixture between layers and on top to within 1 inch of edge.
Frost side and 1 inch rim on top of cake with whipped topping.
Coat side of cake with coconut; garnish as desired.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt
the marshmallows, milk and Hershey bars together; cool. Stir
the whipped cream in the cooled mixture, then add the vanilla.
Put
in the pie crust.
Refrigerate for about 2 hours.

title: applesauce loaf
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Mix flour with salt, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg; add to shortening mixture.
Blend in applesauce; fold in nuts.
Pour into a loaf-size baking pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cheesy hash-spinach pie
directions: Prepare plain pastry for a single crust pie.
Prick bottom and sides well with fork.
Bake at 450 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from oven; reduce oven temp. to 350 degrees.

title: pecan clusters
directions: Melt caramels with water in saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Add pecans; mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful on wax paper.
Melt Candiquick in double boiler over hot water.
Dip caramel drops in Candiquick.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: new england beef broil(one serving)
directions: Place corned beef in 6 1/2-quart Dutch oven.
Cover with cold water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until almost tender.
Turn beef once and skin foam, if necessary.
Add onions and turnips; cook for 30 minutes.
Add potatoes, carrots and cabbage; cook for 20 minutes or until meat and vegetables are tender.

title: mashed potato-carrot-parsnip trio
directions: In 4-quart saucepan over high heat, heat potatoes and enough water to cover to boiling. Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 25 to 30 minutes until potatoes are tender. Drain. Cool and peel. Return to saucepan.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Cook pasta until al dente. Cut vegetables into small pieces and break apart broccoli.
Saute carrots, celery, mushrooms, tomato and onion in virgin oil.
Add broccoli, salt and pepper. Add chicken broth. Simmer for 5 more minutes. Combine with pasta and serve with sprinkles of Parmesan cheese and parsley.

title: salami dip
directions: Heat pan.
Add 2 tablespoons juice from olives plus 2 tablespoons juice from peppers.
Cook salami until limp.
Add olives and peppers.
Cook for 1 minute.
Add cream cheese and whisk until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Serve hot or let cook. Good with crackers and chips.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on cookie sheet to make crust.
Bake and cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayo and Ranch dressing together.
Spread on cooled crust.
Chop vegetables (you can use any other vegetable you like).
Spread shredded cheese on cream mixture.
Sprinkle all mixed vegetables on cheese.
Cut into small squares and refrigerate.
Ready to serve.

title: peach trifle
directions: **Jello vanilla flavor, sugar free, reduced calorie pudding and pie filling.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook the beef and onion until light in color. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and bake.

title: dilled oyster crackers
directions: Mix everything, except crackers. Pour over crackers and put into covered container. Let set for 1 hour before serving.

title: old fashioned dried apple stack cake
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Sift	well flour, salt, soda, baking powder,
salt
and
ginger. Cream shortening, then add sugar,
a little
at a time, blending well.
Add sorghum; mix thoroughly. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well until smooth after each. Pour very thin layers (1/3-inch) into 9-inch pans and bake.
This will
make	6 or 7 layers. When you've cooked dried apples	about 3 to 4 cups (sugar and cinnamon to taste) spread between each layer and on top layer.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Place corned beef in a large heavy bottomed boiler with cold water to cover. Add all other ingredients but cabbage. Uncovered, bring to a boil, skimming carefully as much scum as possible is removed.
Cover.
Turn fire to low and simmer for about 3 to 4 hours until tender when pierced with a fork.
Remove beef to carving board and allow to come to room temperature. Strain remaining juices, reserving 2 cups of the stock.
(The stock is too strongly flavored to use undiluted for boiling cabbage.)
Pour the reserved 2 cups of stock back into the kettle. Add 2 cups cold water and bring to a boil.
Add cabbage. Cover, reduce heat to low and simmer for about 15 minutes at which time cabbage should be tender.

title: burger bundles
directions: Flatten beef in 6-inch patties.
Place 1/4 cup stuffing mix in each and roll meat around stuffing.
Place in square casserole pan and cover with can of soup mixed with milk.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: overnight bran muffins
directions: Combine
sugar,
eggs, cooking oil and salt.
Mix well. Add All-Bran,
natural bran, bran flakes, raisins, buttermilk and 4 cups
flour.
Mix
soda with 2 cups boiling water.	Mix all together.
Leave overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: cheese pennies
directions: Combine margarine and grated cheese.
Add flour and soup mix; blend until dough forms.

title: burritos
directions: Cook meat; drain.
Stir in all ingredients.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally until thick.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Drain juice from berries and pineapple to make 1 cup; add to jello.
Stir in berries and pineapple.
Pour into 2-quart dish; cover and refrigerate until firm.
Combine cheese, sugar, sour cream and vanilla.
Spread over salad and sprinkle with nuts.

title: sausage stars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blot sausage dry with paper towels and combine with cheeses, dressing, olives and pepper.
Lightly grease a muffin tin and press 1 wrapper in each cup.
Brush with oil. Bake 5 minutes until golden.
Remove from tins, placing on baking sheet.
Fill with sausage mixture.
Bake 5 minutes until bubbly. Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix and smooth graham crackers and melted butter in bottom of large cake pan.
Beat butter, powdered sugar, vanilla and eggs until smooth and creamy.
Spread on top of crust.
Slice bananas lengthwise and lay on top of cream.
Cover bananas with 1 large can crushed pineapple, well drained.
Cover with whipped topping. Next, spoon on chopped pecans and maraschino cherries. Refrigerate at least 2 or 3 hours before serving.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and salt together in a quart saucepan.
Add milk and mix well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring often until thick enough to form a ball in cool water. Set off heat.
Add butter, vanilla and pecans.
Stir mixture until hard enough to drop on wax paper.

title: german bean soup
directions: Cook bones until meat falls off, for 2 hours, using low heat to simmer.
Add vegetables.
If using canned beans, add near end of cooking stage.
Add pepper to taste (before or after cooking). Serve with cornbread.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: red velvet cake #1(quick and easy)
directions: Use directions on cake mix with 2 exceptions.
When measuring water, pour 1 large bottle of red cake coloring in cup.
Then add water to make amount of water on box.
Add level tablespoon of cocoa to cake mix.

title: christmas cheese tree
directions: Have everything at room temperature.
Mix ingredients together.
Shape a cone from cardboard and lay over sherbet glass. Cover cone with Saran Wrap.
Frost with cheese mixture.
Decorate with stuffed olives, pimiento, ripe olives and gherkins.

title: marinade for grill
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Marinate chicken or steak overnight. Recipe is enough for 6 chicken breasts or 2 large steaks.

title: cauliflower bake
directions: Boil cauliflower for 10 minutes; drain well.
Combine soup, cheese and mayonnaise.
Add cauliflower and mix well.
Pour into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Toss bread crumbs in melted oleo. Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until hot.

title: white fruitcake
directions: Wash raisins; chop.
Combine with 1 cup orange juice; let stand overnight.
Save 1 1/2 cups flour to mix with candied fruit and nuts.
Sift remaining 3 cups flour with baking powder and salt.
Mix candied fruit and nuts with reserved 1 1/2 cups flour. Cream butter.
Add sugar; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Gradually add dry ingredients, beating after each addition.
Add coconut, floured fruit and nuts, raisins and remaining orange juice; beat well.
Divide batter evenly into 2 well-greased 9 or 10-inch tube pans (loaf pans).
Bake in a very slow oven (250°) for about 2 1/2 hours, or until done.

title: creamy cod bake
directions: Heat butter in saucepan.
Add fish and saute for 3 minutes. Remove to baking dish and season with salt, pepper and paprika. Combine soup and milk and pour over fish.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Place in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: icebox pie
directions: Put Jell-O, boiling water and sugar in a bowl.
Mix well until Jell-O and sugar are dissolved.
Cool.
Chill mixing dish, beaters and evaporated milk.
Pour milk into mixing dish and whip until foamy.
Fold in cooled Jell-O mix.
Pour into prepared graham cracker crusts (makes 2 pies).
Chill until firm.

title: cream cheese coffee dessert
directions: Dissolve coffee in water.
Make crust of Oreos, pecans and butter.
Save 1/4 cup for garnish.
Press crust into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, sour cream and sugar.
Add the other ingredients and beat for 4 minutes.
Important:
beat for exactly 4 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Check after 1 hour. Good without frosting!

title: thanksgiving turkey cookies
directions: For each turkey you will need 2 chocolate stars for the feet, 1 chocolate covered cherry or candy of similar size and shape for the body, 2 candy corn for the head and 1 cookie for the tail feathers.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain.
Spread half in bottom of casserole dish.
Melt 1 stick of butter and cheese together. Spread mushrooms and water chestnuts on top of broccoli and top with 1/2 of cheese mixture.
Spread remainder of broccoli in casserole.
Top with rest of cheese mixture.
Melt 1 stick of butter.
Crush Ritz crackers in the butter.
Pour over top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use Cool Whip instead of mayonnaise.
(You can tell when you have enough of the Cool Whip.)

title: mississippi seafood gumbo
directions: Heat Crisco oil in heavy pot; add flour and brown slowly until a very dark roux has been made.
Add onions and garlic and brown, then add ham and brown.
Add okra.
Continue to brown mixture very slowly for about an hour or more.
Bring to a boil in large pot the water, Worcestershire sauce, tomatoes, Tabasco, salt and pepper.
Add browned mixture and cook slowly for 4 hours.
Add shrimp.
Cook slowly for 2 hours.
Add bay leaves 1 hour before serving.
Serve over 2 tablespoons rice in large bowl.
May be prepared several days ahead.
Freezes well.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add 1 egg and 2 cups flour.
Be sure to mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Add the other egg, remaining flour and vanilla.
Mix well.
Dough will be very stiff. Roll into balls (about 1 teaspoon dough each) and place on greased cookie sheet two inches apart.
Bake 10 to 14 minutes in 350° oven.

title: barbecue bean dish
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and celery; drain grease off.
Saute ground beef; drain and set aside.
Mix pork and beans, kidney beans, tomato sauce, ketchup, hickory smoke and steak sauce; stir altogether.
Mix barbecue spice seasoning, parsley flakes and sugar; mix together.
Add celery, onion, green pepper and ground beef; stir together.
Season to your taste.
Bake at 350° until a little thick, 35 to 45 minutes.

title: healthful fudge
directions: In large saucepan, heat honey and peanut butter, stirring constantly, just until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in carob powder; mix well.
Stir in sunflower seed, sesame seed, coconut, walnuts and raisins.
Press into a buttered pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch). Chill, covered, for several hours or overnight.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 2 1/2 pounds fudge.

title: chocolate river bars
directions: Turn oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In a large mixer bowl, beat butter or margarine with electric mixer on medium speed until softened (about 30 seconds).
Add brown sugar and sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg and extract.
Beat well.
In a medium mixing bowl, stir together flour, baking soda and salt.
With mixer on low speed, gradually add flour mixture to butter mixture, beating until well mixed.
Spread batter in the greased baking pan.
Sprinkle chocolate pieces evenly over top of batter.
Place in the 350° oven about 2 minutes or just until chocolate pieces soften.
Remove pan from oven.
With a table knife, swirl the melted chocolate pieces into the batter.
Return the pan to the 350° oven.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes more or until golden.
Cool in pan on cooling rack.
Cut into bars.
Makes 32 bars.

title: pickles
directions: Cover whole cucumbers with boiling water.
Allow to stand until next day.
Drain.
Repeat this procedure on the next 3 mornings.
On the 5th day, drain cucumbers and slice 1/2-inch slices.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all together and pour in greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: fudge brownies
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat sugar and butter.
Add eggs; mix well. Add flour, cocoa, and salt.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes.

title: crock-pot chicken parmesan
directions: Beat egg, salt and pepper together. Dip chicken breast halves into egg and coat with bread crumbs. Saute chicken in butter in skillet until lightly browned. Transfer chicken to crock-pot. Pour spaghetti sauce over chicken. Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours. Sprinkle cooked chicken with Mozzarella cheese and grated Parmesan cheese. Cook an additional 15 minutes to melt cheeses. Serve over pasta, if desired.

title: christmas morning souffle
directions: Remove crusts from bread and cut in one-inch squares.
Grate cheese into three piles.
Fill casserole with alternate bread and cheese layers, beginning and ending with bread.
Beat eggs.
Add milk and salt.
Pour over layers
in casserole.
Pour melted butter over all.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour.

title: pancho's cheese dip
directions: Blend cans of tomatoes (juice too).
Put in Dutch oven.
Add garlic powder, cumin and pepper.
Dice the jalapeno finely.
Add to mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Add the cheese (grated) until melted.
Remove from heat and cool.
Mixture will be thick and lumpy.
Add 1 cup of water and blend.
May freeze.
Makes a lot!

title: broccoli pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Lightly grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate. Steam broccoli 5 minutes; drain well. Mix broccoli, onion, pepper and cheese in pie plate. Blend remaining ingredients until smooth. Pour into pie plate and bake until golden brown and knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean (35 to 40 minutes). Let stand 5 minutes before cutting. Refrigerate leftovers. Serves 6.

title: easy bake swiss steak
directions: Butter or grease
a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Cut up meat in serving size preferred. Lay meat in buttered dish. Cover with aluminum foil. Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken and cool. Cut chicken up and debone. Combine chicken, chicken soup, chicken broth and vegetables in a cooking dish.
In separate bowl, mix flour, butter and milk. Pour over the top of chicken and bake at 350° for about 1 hour. Let stand for 15 minutes before serving.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain and mash.
Combine all ingredients except a small amount of cheese and crackers.
Pour into casserole.
Sprinkle with crackers and reserved cheese.
Dot with margarine.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until slightly brown on top.

title: swiss steak
directions: Shake meat in paper bag with flour and pepper.
Brown onion and meat on both sides in wine. Drain, if necessary, to remove any excess fat.
Stir in tomatoes. Cover tightly.
Cook slowly 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until tender.

title: peanut butter snacks
directions: Add each ingredient in 1 at a time until mixed up.
Roll into small balls, then roll in cracker crumbs.
These refrigerate well.

title: tomato cheese ring
directions: Dissolve jello in hot V-8 juice.
Let cool.
Mix cheese with mayonnaise.
Add to cooled V-8 mixture (I mix with a hand beater). Place in oiled ring mold and refrigerate.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Add butter, egg yolks and milk; cook until thick.
Add vanilla and cover with beaten egg whites of the 2 eggs.
Brown in oven.

title: swiss chocolate cake
directions: Bake Swiss chocolate cake per directions.
After baked, pour Eagle Brand condensed milk over with inserted holes in cake. Refrigerate 24 hours.
Top with Cool Whip blended with Heath or Skor candy bars.

title: nubian chocolate roll and filling
directions: In a large bowl, let egg whites stand for 1 hour.
Preheat oven at 375°.
Grease a pan; line with wax paper.
At high speed, beat whites to form soft peaks.
Gradually beat in 1/4 cup of sugar, beating until stiff.
Using same beater on high speed, beat yolks with remaining sugar, until thick and lemon color (about 5 minutes).
Low speed beat in cocoa, vanilla and spices.
Fold egg mixture into egg whites; spread evenly in pan.
Bake 12 minutes until surface springs back.

title: garden salad
directions: This salad can be made with green peppers in it or any other vegetable.
Drain all vegetables.
Add dressing.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Top with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pancakes
directions: Sift flour. Combine with eggs and oil. Gradually add milk while stirring. Batter should be a little thick. More milk or flour may be added to reach desired consistency. Pour by 1/4 cup onto hot griddle or nonstick skillet. Flip each cake only once when edges look done. Serve hot with your favorite syrup or fruit.

title: white grape salad
directions: Mix the cream cheese, salad dressing and lemon juice.
Mix in grapes to coat.
Chill.

title: rolled, stuffed flank steak
directions: Wipe steak with damp paper towel. Trim excess fat.
Score surface in diamond pattern on both sides 1/8-inch deep.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in Dutch oven or casserole. Add celery and onion and saute until tender.
Remove from heat. Add bread cubes, parsley, salt, poultry seasoning, marjoram and pepper, tossing lightly until well mixed.
Place stuffing lengthwise down center of steak, starting at narrow end.
Roll up steak.
Secure with skewers.

title: southwestern bean salad
directions: Rinse and pick through beans.
Place them in separate bowls and soak overnight in enough cold water to cover.
Drain beans and place in separate saucepans. Cover with water and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer until tender, about 1 hour. Drain beans and rinse with cold water.
Pat dry.
Place beans in a large bowl. Add the remaining ingredients. Toss gently to mix. Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour before serving. Great with ribs, grilled pork chops or chicken.
Makes 4 servings.

title: oatmeal cookies(80)
directions: Beat egg, water, oleo, shortening, sugar, cinnamon and half of the cake mix (dry) until smooth.
Stir in remaining cake mix, oats, raisins and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Cool slightly before removing from pan.

title: persimmon date nut bread
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Dissolve soda in persimmon pulp.
Mix into creamed ingredients.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Add orange rind, dates and nuts.
Turn into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 350° preheated oven for about 75 minutes or until food pick stuck in center comes out clean.
Turn out on rack to cool.

title: broccoli casserole 1
directions: Mix and pour in a casserole dish.
Top with 3/4 stick of butter and Ritz crackers.
Crackers should cover the entire mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: ham and sausage jambalaya
directions: In heavy 8-quart Dutch oven, melt drippings or lard over medium heat.
Add onions, green pepper, celery and garlic.
Cook until vegetables are wilted and transparent, about 5 minutes.
Add ham and sausage; cook, stirring occasionally, until sausage is lightly browned, about 8 minutes.
Add rice.
Cook, stirring constantly, until rice is light golden brown, about 5 minutes. Add tomatoes; stir until combined.
Cook 2 minutes.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill thoroughly.

title: cheese cake tarts
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Place wafer in foil cups upside down.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Let cool; spoon canned filling on top.
Refrigerate.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine flour, bran, sugar, salt and soda.
Combine and add all other ingredients.
Stir just enough to moisten.
Add raisins. Stir just enough to distribute.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° approximately 20 minutes.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating after each.
Sift flour with baking powder; add to creamed mixture, 1 spoonful at a time, alternately with milk.
Add vanilla; stir in pineapple and juice.
Blend well.
Pour into a well-greased 10-inch tube pan or 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Place in a cold oven at 325° and bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and let set all night. First thing in the morning, add whipped cream and butter mints.
Let set all day.

title: baba ghanouj-i(an arab eggplant dip)
directions: Pierce eggplant in several places, set on a baking sheet, and bake in a 350°F. oven for 1 hour. Let cool.

title: parmesan canapes
directions: Cut each slice of bread into 6 pieces.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Drop 3/4 teaspoon on bread squares.
Place under boiler until lightly browned.
Toaster oven may be used.
Set control on "top brown only." Serve hot.

title: irish stew
directions: Roll meat in flour; brown in hot oil or butter.
Place meat in stewpot; add liquid, onions, celery, thyme, parsley, salt and pepper to taste.
Slowly bring to a boil, then let simmer (covered) until meat is just about tender, approximately an hour for lamb, 1 1/2 to 2 hours for beef.
Skim fat from top.
Add carrots, potatoes, parsnips and turnips.
Simmer for additional 45 minutes to 1 hour (covered).
Remove lid occasionally to see if more liquid is needed.
Vegetables and meat should then be quite tender. Thicken liquid with extra flour if desired.
(If you can't find turnips, I substitute rutabaga).
This is a really great recipe.

title: bob andy pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Set aside.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add yolks; beat until smooth.
Add flour and spices.
Mix, then add milk.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° until set, about 35 minutes.
Makes a 9-inch pie.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour in 8 x 10-inch dish and congeal.

title: easy kids brownies
directions: Cream eggs, sugar and butter well.
Add rest of ingredients and beat well.
Spread in greased 7 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: white peppernuts
directions: No directions were given, but you mix the ingredients and roll into thin ropes.
Cut into 1/2-inch pieces and bake 7 minutes in 400° oven.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: In
Dutch oven brown bacon until crisp.
Drain off fat. In same
pan cook and stir ground beef and onion until meat is brown and
onion
is tender.
May want to drain fat.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water.
Stir bouillon and remaining ingredients into
meat
mixture.
Cover and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut squash and onion into desired size pieces, then cook together until tender.
Place half of stuffing mix in bottom of casserole dish, greased with butter.
Add soup to mixture and pour in mixture and remaining stuffing mix on top.
Dot with butter. Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: quaker fruit and oat bars
directions: Combine all ingredients except 2/3 cup oats. Press in 7 x 11-inch dish. Bake for 10 minutes. Remove from oven; spread preserves over top and sprinkle remaining oats on top. Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: jewell's potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until fork inserts smoothly.
Skin and dice potatoes.
Peel and dice eggs.
Put in large bowls.
Stir in all other ingredients.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: quick supper
directions: Slice meat into thin one inch pieces and brown.
Cook Rice-A-Roni according to package directions with meat added.
Just before time is up, add mushrooms and green peppers and cover for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: indian bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix sugar and oil.
Add eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Blend in pumpkin.
Combine dry ingredients and blend into pumpkin mix.
Stir in nuts and raisins.

title: veggie bake
directions: Cook and drain first 2 ingredients.
Grease pan.
Arrange broccoli as desired, in rows or mix.
Cube cheese.
Cube 1/2 stick oleo or butter.
Put on cauliflower and broccoli.
Crumb crackers; mix with 1/2 stick melted butter.
Sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° until bubbly, 20 to 30 minutes.

title: grilled blue fish(can use any fish you like)
directions: Note:
Ingredients may vary as to how many fish fillets you have.

title: chocolate chip pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly in a small mixing bowl.
Gradually add sugar; beat well.
Add margarine and vanilla; mix well.
Blend in cornstarch.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve warm, topped with whipped cream or topping.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sprinkle with sugar. Place on greased sheet.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Crunch cookies.
Stir into softened ice cream and Cool Whip. Pour mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan and cover with foil.
Freeze and eat!

title: apple pie filling
directions: Mix together and cook until thick.
Pack quart jars with sliced apples and pour over liquid.
Cold pack for 20 minutes. Makes 7 quarts.

title: 2 plus 2 cake
directions: Mix and bake.
A good, easy, quick cake.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Place cucumbers and onions in a gallon jar.
Mix all other ingredients cold.
Pour over cucumbers.
Fill to 1 inch of top. Put lid on tight.
Let stand for 5 days before eating.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
You may use a mixer.
Put in a 2-quart casserole dish or 2 (1-quart) casserole dishes.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, uncovered.

title: pennsylvania red cabbage
directions: Heat drippings in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients and dash of pepper.
Cover tightly and cook over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Cook between 15 to 25 minutes for desired degree of doneness.

title: vodka cream sauce
directions: In 1-quart pot, bring water to boil.
Plunge in fresh tomatoes and leave for 30 seconds to 1 minute to loosen skin.
Remove from water, core end and peel.
Slice tomatoes in half horizontally and squeeze out seeds. Chop into small cubes.
Heat olive oil and butter in skillet.

Add onions and soften without browning. Add tomatoes and cook for about 5 minutes. If tomatoes seem very watery, cook a little longer to evaporate excess liquid. Add cream and cook another minute. Add vodka and simmer for an additional 3 minutes. Serve hot over freshly cooked pasta.
Serves 8.

title: ranch cookies
directions: Mix together the first 8 ingredients; beat together.
Add remaining ingredients one at a time.
Drop by spoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes lots of cookies.

title: magic fruit cake
directions: Break mincemeat into chunks in a medium size saucepan; add water.
Stir over medium heat until lumps are broken up.
Boil 1 minute; stir occasionally.
Cool.
Butter a 9-inch tube pan or spring pan.
Line with wax paper and butter again.
Sift flour and baking soda.
Combine eggs, mincemeat, condensed milk, fruit and nuts.
Fold in dry ingredients.
Pour in pan; bake slow at 300° for 2 hours plus, until center springs back when lightly touched with finger and top is golden brown.
Turn out of pan.
Remove paper. For a richer cake, use two packages of mincemeat quantities of water and other ingredients stay the same.
It makes a big cake and so-so-so good.
Serves 12.

title: mallow fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: clarence's peach pie
directions: Melt the oleo in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix the sugar, flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add the milk to this mixture and stir as a cake batter.
Bring the water to a boil with the peaches.
Add the batter by spoonfuls to the melted (hot) oleo. Add the hot peaches on top of the batter.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until crust is brown.
Crust rises to the top.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Chop beef in blender.
Save out 1/4 cup to roll ball in.
Chop onions and mix with beef, cheese and salt.
Form ball and roll in beef.
Store in refrigerator.
Better the longer you store it. Serve on Ritz crackers.

title: roast burrito
directions: Cook a roast in skillet on top of stove until very tender. When done, sprinkle flour over meat to make a paste.
Add stewed tomatoes, green chiles and onion.
Stir all together good.
Roll mixture in flour tortilla.
Put grated cheese on top and what else you may like.

title: grape-nuts custard
directions: Scald milk.
Combine eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla in large mixing bowl.
Add scalding milk slowly, while mixing thoroughly. Add Grape-Nuts and pour into baking dish.
Set in pan with hot water and bake 1 hour at 350° in a preheated oven.

title: spiced peaches
directions: Drain peaches.
Bring to a boil peach juice, sugar, vinegar and spices.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Pour hot syrup over peaches.
Let cool.
Chill thoroughly.
Remove spices after 24 hours.

title: corris' orange eggnog
directions: Beat eggs until lemon colored.
Stir in sugar, cinnamon, ginger, cloves, orange and lemon juices.
Cut ice cream in small cubes and put into punch bowl.
Pour juice mixture and ginger ale. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Makes 15 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add mashed bananas and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour batter into 2 greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour. Cool on wire rack for 15 minutes before removing from pans.

title: baked apples and stuffed pork chops
directions: Mix stuffing as directed on bag or make your own as usual. Using a large electric skillet or roasting pan for oven, slice pocket in pork chop clear to the bone as if cutting half as thin, or place 2 thin ones on top of each other.
Fill with stuffing. Arrange in pan so there is room for apples to bake at the same time.
Core apples.
Do not peel.
Fill core hole with one or two marshmallows and 2 tablespoons of brown sugar.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Just mix together and pour into shells.
Refrigerate.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. During the last 5 minutes, shake nutmeg on top.

title: corn beef and tomatoes
directions: Open can of beef; break apart.
Place in 2-quart saucepan with onion and enough water just to cover, cook until onions are tender then add salt and pepper and tomatoes.
Let simmer for 25 minutes. Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: no-knead refrigerator rolls
directions: Soften yeast in water and set aside.
Beat well the Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Add yeast and blend well.
Add 4 cups of flour and the salt; beat on medium speed until smooth.
Stir in 4 to 4 1/2 cups more flour.
Store in refrigerator, tightly closed, overnight or until needed.
Will keep for 4 to 5 days.

title: applesauce chocolate cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together; beat with mixer while you measure the dry ingredients.
Add the next 4 dry ingredients to the wet mixture; beat until smooth.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 3 tablespoons of sugar on top of batter. Sprinkle with a small amount of chocolate chips (about 2/3 of a 12-ounce package).
Bake at 350° for approximately 35 to 45 minutes, or until done.
Serve warm or cold.

title: miniature cheesecakes
directions: Combine first five ingredients and beat at high speed for 5 minutes.
Put one vanilla wafer on the bottom of each "midget" foiled cupcake cup.
Pour 1 tablespoon of cheesecake mixture in each cup.)
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until thin cracks appear on top of each cake.
Remove from oven and let cool.
They will seem to fall, but this is normal.
Drop 1 cherry on top and refrigerate.
Makes approximately 28 to 30 cheesecakes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Place sugar, peanut butter and salt in a bowl; blend with a fork until evenly mixed and like coarse meal.
Add nuts, then vanilla and water, a small amount at a time.
Knead until consistency of fudge, adding more water if necessary.
Shape into small balls or 1-inch rolls.
Roll in crushed peanuts or confectioners sugar.
May be coated in chocolate melted with paraffin if desired.

title: fancy strawberries
directions: Mix coconut with strawberry jello and enough Eagle Brand milk to work good.
Make into strawberries, then roll in strawberry jello.
Decorate top with powdered sugar icing tinted green to look like stems and leaves, pretty to decorate with cookies and tasty. (Icing made with a little powdered sugar, butter and milk.)

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all
together,
pour into casserole dish.
Dot with butter.
Cook at 350° until brown and firm.

title: french apple pie
directions: Slice apples and put into deep baking dish.
Add water and sugar over them.
Place in oven at 375° and let them stew for 15 minutes while preparing remaining ingredients.

title: microwave apple crisp
directions: Microwave margarine in medium size bowl or 4-cup measure until melted.
Stir in oats, brown sugar, flour and nuts.
Microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes, stirring frequently during the last 2 minutes, until crisp and toasted.
Pour filling into a 9-inch microwave-safe pie pan.
Microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes until hot.
Sprinkle oat mixture over filling.
Serve immediately.
Top with ice cream.

title: tuna stuffed shells
directions: Boil water.
Drop pasta shells in with pinch of salt.
Mix 1/2 can cream of mushroom soup, tuna and peas in bowl.
When pasta shells are finished, cool them in cold water.
Stuff with tuna mixture.
Place shells in shallow baking pan and spoon or pour remaining soup on top.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: farrell's salad
directions: Combine lettuce, radishes, onions and mushrooms in a large bowl.
Cover and refrigerate thoroughly.
Pour low calorie dressing over lettuce mixture.
Toss to coat.
Top with ham, turkey, cheeses and tomatoes.
Serve.
You may add more dressing if desired (1/4 cup).
Serves 8.

title: "jiffy" hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 15 to 18 minutes at 350°. Cool cake.
Cake will be very thin!
Soften cream cheese and mix with 1/2 cup milk.
When creamy, add puddings and remaining milk; drain pineapple and mix and spread over cake.
Then spread Cool Whip and sprinkle pecans over Cool Whip.

title: bubble bread
directions: Combine sugar, cinnamon and margarine.
Pull bread apart into small balls.
Dip each ball in sugar mixture.
Place into well-greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm and just pull apart with fingers.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix spinach, potato soup, Parmesan cheese, sour cream and pepper together well.
Top with grated Monterey Jack cheese and paprika.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes in casserole dish at 350°.

title: split pea and veggie soup(not gassy)
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and cook at least 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients and cook another 1/2 to 1 hour.
Discard allspice.
Freezes well.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Grease pan.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve the yeast in 2 cups warm water.
Add the shortening to mixture.
Add the flour.
Mix well. Cover with wax paper and let rise to double. Roll out on floured surface and cut.
Place on cookie sheet and let rise about 30 minutes. Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: baked fish
directions: Wash fish thoroughly.
Rub inside and out with salt and pepper.
Prepare highly seasoned bread or mushroom force meat. Stuff.
Lay the fish straight in the cheesecloth with the back up, to resemble a live fish.
Cover tail with strip of brown paper to prevent burning.
Lay strips of bacon about 2-inches apart across fish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Baste every 10 minutes with 1/2 cup hot water and 2 tablespoons butter or a Spanish sauce.
When ready to serve, remove paper from tail. Garnish with parsley, tomato slices, lemon and pickles.
Make eyes of small stuffed olives.
Serve with tartar or Spanish sauce.

title: orange dream salad
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Boil until glossy, about 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour into a large bowl and refrigerate overnight.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve orange jello in the boiling water; cool slightly. Add the 7-Up, then the crushed pineapple, bananas and the marshmallows.
Let cool.
Bring to a boil the pineapple juice, flour, sugar, egg and the butter.
Cool and fold in 1 package Dream Whip or whipped cream and spoon onto first layer.
Spread Cheddar cheese over the salad.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: no-knead refrigerator rolls
directions: In mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar, salt and about half the flour.
Add egg and shortening.
Gradually beat in remaining flour until smooth.
(Best to use kneading hooks with electric mixer, but small mixer can be used at beginning.)
Cover bowl with damp cloth and place in refrigerator.
About 2 hours before baking, cut off amount needed and return remaining dough to refrigerator.
Shape into rolls and place on greased baking sheet. Cover; let rise about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.
Makes about 4 dozen medium rolls.

title: raspberry vinegar
directions: Combine ingredients. Cover and let stand for 5 days or more at room temperature.
Strain vinegar and pour into a sterilized bottle. Discard raspberries. Store vinegar at room temperature.

title: hamburger chop suey
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet.
Add broth, soy sauce and sugar.
Add vegetables.
Bring to a full boil, separating vegetables with a fork and stirring frequently, until sauce cubes are blended.
Cover and simmer 2 minutes.
Bring again to a boil. Stir in rice.
Cover, remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift all dry ingredients together in large bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Mix buttermilk and dissolved yeast.
Add buttermilk and yeast to flour mixture.
Stir until flour is damp.
Knead on floured board 2 to 3 minutes.
Store in refrigerator in covered bowl.
Roll out like biscuits.
Bake at 400°; do not let rise.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: applebrosia
directions: Mix orange juice and water.
Add pineapple and coconut and mix well. Add apples and desired sweetener. Store refrigerated in glass container several days (stirring occasionally) prior to serving.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook beef and garlic in a skillet until brown; drain.
Stir in paste and next 7 ingredients.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Remove bay leaves.
Cook noodles according to directions and omit salt.
Drain.
Combine cottage cheese and sour cream; stir well.

title: chicken with pepper and cheese sauce
directions: Combine 2 tablespoons flour, salt and pepper; toss to coat chicken.
In a skillet cook chicken in oil until tender.
Remove chicken, add onion, peppers, jalapeno, garlic, flour and chicken broth to make a thick paste.
Stir well.
Add milk, sour cream and Worcestershire sauce.
Add chicken and cook until well blended. Stir in cheese and cook until melted.
Serve over hot pasta.

title: spinach-artichoke au gratin
directions: Melt margarine; add onions and saute.
Add flour and stir until blended.
Add milk and bring to a slow boil.
Add spinach and artichokes.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Add cheeses and cook 10 minutes more.
Season to taste.

title: mother's chocolate pie(delicious warm or cold)
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients.
Add 1 cup milk.
Stir until well mixed.
Bring to a boil in heavy saucepan.
Boil, stirring all the time for 1 minute.
Cool while you combine eggs with 1 cup milk and add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour cooked mixture in.
Stir and pour in partially baked pie shell (homemade best).
Bake in preheated 350° oven until set.
Add meringue made with last 3 ingredients.
Bake until brown.

title: family pie(cobbler)
directions: Cook apples almost to sauce.
Add sugar to taste.
Pour into a large cake pan.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: cranberry slush
directions: Dissolve the cherry jello in the boiling water.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Put in an ice cream pail and freeze.
When served, put a large scoop of slush in a glass and fill with 7-Up.
If you want it stronger, add more vodka. Delicious as nonalcoholic drink also.

title: punch
directions: Follow package directions and prepare the first 4 ingredients. Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.
Double recipe makes 3 gallons.

title: six-layer dinner
directions: In a large rectangular buttered baking dish, layer all the ingredients in the order listed.
Cover and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chili
directions: If too thick, add tomato juice.
Cook hamburger and sausage. Drain off grease.
Add remaining ingredients.
The longer it cooks, the better it tastes.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat and onion in oil.
Stir to break meat in bite size pieces.
Drain excess fat.
Cover and cook 1 to 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add water, if needed.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Stir first 5 ingredients well to a creamy paste.
Add flour and cocoa.
Put soda into boiling water and stir in the last thing.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: corn oysters
directions: Heat fat and oil in deep fryer or Dutch oven to 375°.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt, eggs and corn liquid.
Stir in corn. Drop by rounded tablespoons into hot fat until brown approximately 4 to 5 minutes.

title: pineapple and cherry salad(good and simple)
directions: Mix pineapple and sugar.
Let come to a rolling boil.
Add pie filling (ready mix) to this, then add the Jell-O mixture.
Mix well and pour into a crystal or white bowl.

title: butter finger bars
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil. Stir in peanut butter and cereal. Press into an 8-inch square cake pan.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger; drain grease.	Add remaining ingredients to hamburger. Let simmer a few minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients except the bacon.
Place in Pyrex dish. Place strips of bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: seafood cocktail sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with shrimp or raw oysters.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly all ingredients, except bacon and tomato sauce. Put into loaf pan.
Cover with strips of bacon if you like that flavor.
Pour over all tomato sauce.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs.
Mix soda with applesauce, add to first mixture.
Sift spices with flour.
Add to other mixture.
When mixed well add nuts and raisins (makes a stiff batter).
Pour in 2 tube pans.
Put in oven about 200° for 1 hour.
Increase to 300°.
Cook around 2 1/2 hours more.
Makes 2 cakes, about 4 pounds each.

title: fruit filled cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Slice dough into 24 slices.
Refrigerate remaining dough.
Place slices 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Spread each slice with 1/2 teaspoon of jam.
Set aside. Slice remaining dough into 24 slices.
Cut 1-inch star shape out of center of each cookie slice.
Place cookie slices on jam topped cookie slices.
Press edges slightly.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 14 minutes or until edges are light golden brown.
Cool 1 minute. Remove from cookie sheet.

title: yummy lemon fruit dip
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender.
Blend until smooth.
Serve as a dip with cut up fruit (apples, bananas, pears, etc.).
This dip is delicious.
People will think it's made with whipped cream and other fattening things.

title: angel food cake with strawberries
directions: Cut cake to make 2 layers.
Dissolve jello in 1/2 cup hot water.
Add partly thawed strawberries, partly drained, and let jell for 5 to 10 minutes.
Whip the cream and add jello mixture. Ice between layers and outside.

title: dinner rolls
directions: In large bowl combine 1 1/3 cups flour and yeast.
