Heat milk, sugar,
Crisco
and
salt,
just
until	warm;
stir occasionally to melt Crisco.
Add
to dry ingredients in bowl; add egg.
Beat with
electric
mixer
for
1/2 minute;	scrape sides of bowl constantly.
Beat
minutes
at high speed. By hand stir in enough remaining flour to make soft dough.
Place in greased bowl;
turn once to grease surface. Cover; let rise 1 to 1 1/2 hours,
until
double.
Punch
down;
turn	out
on lightly floured surface.
Cover; let rest 10 minutes. Shape as desired. Cover;
let rolls rise 30 to 45 minutes until double on greased baking sheet. Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: frozen salad
directions: In first bowl, mix sugar, bananas and cream cheese.
Cream together and set aside.
In second bowl, combine strawberries, pineapple, chopped nuts and Cool Whip.
Add ingredients from first bowl; mix well.
Freeze until solid.
Set out 1/2 hour before serving.

title: cream cheese corn casserole
directions: Saute bell pepper and onion.
Blend flour and margarine.
Add sour cream and cream cheese and blend well.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake about 30 minutes at 375 degrees.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream the sugar and margarine. Add flour and eggs alternately.
Add vanilla and buttermilk.
Put in pie shell. Set oven to 350°.
Cook about 1 hour or until pie doesn't shake.

title: ground beef and tomato sauce
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in skillet in margarine until soft.
Remove onion and green pepper.
Brown ground beef and pour off fat.
Add onion, green pepper, salt, pepper, tomato soup and water.
Bring to a boil, then cover and simmer for 30 minutes. Can add catsup to give a sweeter taste.
Serve on mashed potatoes or noodles.

title: onion rings
directions: Peel onions and slice 1/4 inch thick.
Cover with ice cubes and let stand 30 minutes.
Wipe dry.
Separate into rings.
Sift flour, sugar and salt together.
Combine egg and milk, then add shortening and mix well.
Dip onion rings in batter and fry.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Melt the butter in a saucepan and add leeks, onion, celery and broccoli.
Saute about 5 minutes over low heat, so that the butter won't brown.

title: hot taco dip
directions: Cut cheese into small pieces and melt with soup; add broccoli. Serve hot with taco chips or veggies.

title: mom's famous lasagna
directions: Brown meat.
Add salt, sugar, oregano, garlic salt, pepper and tomato sauce.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Cook and drain wide egg noodles.
Combine cooked noodles, cream cheese, sour cream and green onions.
In a 3-quart casserole, alternate layers of noodle mixture, meat mixture and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
This can be made ahead and frozen, then cooked the day you want to serve it.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: tomato puree deluxe
directions: Place all ingredients in a large kettle.
Cook over medium heat until tomatoes are tender.
Remove bay leaf.
Force through strainer or process in blender.
Return tomato mixture to heat and cook until reduced to half the original volume.
Pour into hot sterilized jars and seal.
Yields 3 pints.

title: marinated rump roast
directions: Combine wine and remaining ingredients.
Place roast into a heavy-duty Ziploc bag and pour combined ingredients into the same bag.
Seal and refrigerate overnight.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Beat eggs and add sugar and flour mixture.
Add syrup, vanilla and pecans.
Dot with butter and bake in uncooked pie shell in moderate oven about 1 hour or until done.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup, water and wax in a saucepan until it spins a thread. Add peanuts; stir. Cook until syrup is amber color, stirring constantly. When peanuts smell parched and temperature reaches 300°, remove from heat. Add vanilla and butter. Rapidly stir in soda and salt. Pour on greased cookie sheet. Spread with spoon. Cool and break into pieces.

title: sweet potato bake
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water until tender, but not mushy; peel while hot, then cool.
Combine brown sugar, cornstarch, salt and cinnamon in heavy saucepan.
Stir in apricot nectar, water and orange peel.
Bring to full boil and stir constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in butter.
Cool slightly.
Stir in pecans.
Cut potatoes in half and put in loaf pan.
Pour sauce over potatoes so all are glazed.
Add marshmallows, if desired.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 25 minutes or until sauce is bubbling.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: holiday dessert
directions: Fold whipped topping into egg nog.
Alternate layers of crumbs and egg nog in
parfait
glasses.
Let stand 10 minutes in refrigerator.
Garnish
with whipped topping and maraschino cherries and cookie fans.
Serves 6.

title: peachy jello mold
directions: Add Jell-O to water and mix to dissolve.
Add peach pie filling.
Place in the refrigerator until it jells.
Add Cool Whip and place in Jell-O mold.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: red apples
directions: Bring sugar, water and red hots to a boil; cook until red hots are melted.
Peel apples; cut in large pieces.
Drop into mixture and boil about 5 minutes.
Take off heat and let set until apples soak up color.

title: streusel cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat cake mix with eggs, oil and orange juice with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended. Pour evenly into greased 13 x 9-inch cake pan. Mix brown sugar and cinnamon in a medium bowl. Stir in cereal and dried fruit; sprinkle evenly over batter in pan. Bake 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool completely on wire rack. Makes 16 servings.

title: potato rolls
directions: Combine 2 cups flour, potatoes, sugar, undissolved yeast and salt in large bowl.
Heat water and butter until very warm.
Stir into yeast mixture.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make soft dough.
Knead on lightly floured surface until smooth and elastic, about 6 to 8 minutes.
Cover and let rest 10 minutes.

title: american macaroni and cheese
directions: Fry bacon until lightly browned over medium heat; drain.
In 2 tablespoons of bacon drippings, saute celery about 3 minutes, or until crisp-tender.
Add flour; cook about 1 minute.
Add milk, water, bouillon granules and hot pepper sauce.
Stirring, bring to a boil and boil until thickened.
Add cheese; stir until melts. Remove from heat.
Stir in macaroni, chives, pimento and all but 1/4 cup of crumbled bacon.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with cracker crumbs and reserved 1/4 cup bacon.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven until hot and bubbly.

title: crazy cake
directions: Put all dry ingredients in baking pan and make 2 wells.
In one put vinegar and oil.
In the other put vanilla and cold water. Mix and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: schnitzel beans
directions: Dice bacon and fry crisp.
Slice onions and fry until soft. Cut the beans into small (1-inch) pieces and brown them slightly with the bacon and onions.
Add the tomatoes, seasoning and boiling water.
Cover and cook slowly until beans are tender.
Add water if necessary so there will be a little sauce to serve with beans.

title: chicken renee(carolyn garner)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chicken breasts and Mozzarella. Place chicken breasts on waxed paper and flatten each piece. Spread mixed ingredients on top of chicken breasts.
Roll pieces up jelly roll style and place seam side down in 9 x 13-inch baking dish in which 1/2 stick oleo has been melted.
Cover and bake 1 hour in 375° oven.
During last 10 minutes of baking, sprinkle with the Mozzarella.
Serve with cooked and drained spaghetti noodles.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Mix stuffing and butter.
Combine half with chicken and place in dish.
Mix soups and broth and pour over chicken.
Top with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: green bean corn casserole
directions: Drain beans and corn and mix together in casserole dish.
In a bowl, mix sour cream, soup, onions, cheese and spoon over beans and corn.
Top casserole with crushed Ritz crackers and drizzle with butter.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: santa's whiskers
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.

Blend and add the vanilla and milk. Stir in the remaining ingredients. Form into 2 rolls (2 x 8-inch). Roll in 3/4 cup coconut. Wrap and chill several hours. Preheat oven to 375°. Slice rolls into 1/4-inch rounds. Bake on ungreased cookie sheets 12 minutes or until edges are golden. Yields 4 dozen.

title: burrito casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and onion. Drain. Add taco mix and cook according to package directions. Add refried beans and cheddar cheese soup.

title: rosemary bread
directions: Mix cottage cheese, eggs, sugar, soda, oil, salt, rosemary and hot water.
Add yeast mixture.
Add in flour.
Dough should not be too dry or too sticky.
Place in well-greased bowl and place in warm, draft-free place.
Let rise 40 minutes.
Punch down dough and let rest 15 minutes.
On floured surface, shape into several long loaves or braids or dinner rolls.
Let rise again in warm place for 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes until golden.

title: coffee mix
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Add 2 rounded teaspoonfuls to boiling water.
Stir well.
Store remainder of mix in an airtight container.

title: steamed zucchini
directions: Melt stick of butter or margarine.
Put sliced zucchini in with butter.
Add brown sugar and let simmer kind of slow until zucchini is good and tender.
`Serve as a side dish.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and egg well.
Stir in pineapple.
Blend flour, soda, salt and nutmeg.
Stir in.
Mix in nuts; chill 1 hour.
Heat oven to 400°.
Drop rounded teaspoonful 2 inches apart onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Remove stems and seeds from peppers.
Rinse and drain on towel.
Mix ground beef, bread crumbs, salt, pepper, onion and 1/2 cup tomato juice.
Stuff peppers with beef mix.
Pour remaining tomato juice over stuffed peppers.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover; bake 15 minutes longer.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: mock potato salad
directions: Cook cauliflower until tender; drain.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Cover and store in refrigerator.

title: salsa dip
directions: Brown meat.
Add cubed cheese and tomatoes.
Cook until cheese melts.
Keep on low heat (crock-pot).

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil carrots, onions and squash until tender.
Put in blender or processor.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in casserole dish 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mock beef stroganoff
directions: In frying pan, saute onion in margarine over medium heat. Add meat & brown. Drain off fat. Add flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms (if desired). Cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add soup and simmer for 10 minutes. Stir in sour cream (room temperature). Heat through. Serve over cooked noodles, rice or bread.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Put first three ingredients in food processor and blend. Chill.
Form a ball and roll in chopped nuts.
Serve with Triscuits.

title: artie's blueberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, cream the sugar and oleo. Add egg, salt and vanilla, beating well. Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Last, fold in berries.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake about 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Delicious used warm with milk or ice cream.

title: praline topping
directions: Combine.
Spread carefully over hot cake.
Brown in oven 5 minutes.

title: butterhorns
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in butter as for pie crust.
Add beaten eggs, warm milk and yeast mixture; beat well.
Do not knead.
Put in refrigerator overnight. In the morning, divide into 4 parts.
Roll out.
Spread with melted butter; sprinkle with sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Cut into 12 pie shape pieces.
Begin at wide end and roll up.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, until brown.
Frost; sprinkle with nuts.

title: pear bread
directions: Drain pears and chop fine.
Combine oil, sugar, pears, cinnamon, applesauce and beaten egg whites.

title: gumbo
directions: Saute onions in butter in a saucepan.
Add vegetables, hot water and seasonings.
Cook slowly until mixture is thick.

title: chicken salad in melon halves
directions: Mix all together except cantaloupe.
Spoon salad into cantaloupe halves and top with slivered almonds and frosted grapes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Blend cream cheese and Eagle Brand together well.
Add lemon juice and vanilla, then mix and spoon into crust.
Refrigerate. May be topped with cherry pie filling.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzels, margarine and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Press in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix together cream cheese, 3/4 cup sugar and whipped topping.
Spread over pretzel mixture.
Let stand overnight.

title: mrs. le tourneau's fruit cake or lemon cake
directions: Put all fruit in a bowl.
Mix 1 cup of the flour with the fruit.
If using cherries and pineapple, mix them in the batter first without any flour on them.
Cream the butter and sugar.
Add Karo, lemon extract and alternate flour and whole eggs.
Beat well (5 minutes with electric beater).
Pour mixture over fruit and nuts.
Pour in loaf pans or tube pan.
(Note:
Put brown paper on bottom of pans; grease well.)
Bake slowly at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Test to see if done.

title: peach and pineapple congealed salad
directions: Mix pineapple with jello until thoroughly dissolved.
(Warm crushed pineapple in microwave first, then add the jello.)
Do not add water to jello.
Add Cool Whip.
Blend in buttermilk and nuts. Store in refrigerator overnight before serving.

title: baked shrimp
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine first 9 ingredients in shallow 2-quart baking dish and mix well.
Remove 1/4 cup of this mixture and set aside.
Add shrimp to baking dish and mix thoroughly. Bake for 15 minutes and serve immediately.
Can be frozen, uncooked, to serve at a later date.

title: new peanut butter crispy treats
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In large saucepan over low heat, stir together the corn syrup, sugar and peanut butter. Stirring constantly, bring to boil and boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add cereal and toss to coat well.
Press into pan. Cool.
Cut into 2 x 2-inch squares.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then add turkey broth until it is very moist.
Bake in oven at 350° until inserted knife comes out clean.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Place drained asparagus in an 8 x 8 casserole dish. Spread the cream of mushroom soup over the drained asparagus. Layer the eggs over the soup. Sprinkle crackers over top and drizzle with melted butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Take out and sprinkle cheese on top and put back in oven until cheese is melted.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix sweet potatoes and oleo together; add eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Put in baking dish.
Mix brown sugar, flour, nuts and butter.
Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream pepper, pimentos and 1/2 can of onions.
Pour into 1-quart casserole. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.

title: no bake chocolate pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
Pour into crust.
Mix instant pudding as directed on the box.
Pour pudding mix over cream cheese mix.
Spread Cool Whip on top and then sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: wonderful vegetable bars
directions: Cover bottom of 11 x 17-inch ungreased pan, with rolls. Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Rolls should start to brown, but not quite done.
Cool.	Mix cream cheese, Miracle Whip or mayonnaise and
dressing
mix.
Spread on rolls.
Sprinkle on vegetables. Cover
with
wax
paper
or
Handi-Wrap and press down.
Chill 3 to 4 hours and then cut into bars and serve.

title: honey-paprika sweet onions
directions: Place onions, cut side up, in lightly greased 9 x 13 x 2 inch baking dish.
Combine butter and remaining ingredients; pour over onions.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: okra n rice
directions: Cut okra in rings. Steam in very little water until done. Add to bacon drippings and cook until light brown. Cut onion and pepper medium fine. Add crumbled bacon.
Add the rice and 2 cups water, season with salt and pepper. Cook over medium heat for about 45 minutes or until done.

title: pork chops and dressing
directions: Mix onion soup with water.
Place salt and peppered chops in dish.
Pour soup over.
Place under broiler until brown.
Take chops out of dish; sprinkle dressing over soup and place chops on dressing.
Cover with foil and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cocoa nut balls
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream the butter, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture, blending thoroughly. Add nuts and mix well. Shape into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake approximately 20 minutes. Do not brown.
Cool, then roll in powdered sugar.

title: coca-cola barbecue sauce
directions: Combine the ingredients in a heavy saucepan and gradually bring to a boil over medium heat. Reduce heat and bring to a simmer. Simmer the sauce until reduced by 1/4, 6 to 8 minutes. Transfer the sauce to clean jars and let cool to room temperature, then refrigerate until serving. The sauce will keep for several months, refrigerated.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs and butter until smooth.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then mix 1 egg, cream cheese and powdered sugar; spread on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: crab casserole ii
directions: Dice 4 slices of bread into buttered baking dish.
Mix crab or shrimp, mayonnaise, onion, bell pepper and celery.
Spread on bread.
Trim crusts from last 4 slices of bread and place on top. Next, beat the eggs.
Add milk and pour over the mixture in baking dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Then bake for 15 minutes at 325°. Take out of oven and spread soup on top.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: quick chocolate fudge
directions: Bring all ingredients to a rolling boil.
Cook 2 minutes. Beat and pour in greased plate to harden.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients into large bowl.
Make a hole in the center and add salad oil, pumpkin, eggs, water and nuts.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into 3 well-greased and floured 1 pound coffee cans 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hearts of artichoke salad
directions: Drain artichoke hearts and cut each in half.
Wash and tear up greens.
Toss all with curried dressing.

title: easy pot pie
directions: Pour soup into one deep dish pie shell and top with the other one.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: congo bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the shortening and sugar.
Beat until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add vanilla. On low speed, mix in dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts, chips and dates.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: new jersey doughnuts
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs and lemon peel.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Sift flour with baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Mix well. Roll out on lightly floured board and cut with doughnut cutter. Fry in hot fat (365°) for 3 minutes.
Drain on paper toweling. Makes 2 dozen.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix in bowl and set aside the apples, cinnamon and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Mix flour, 2 1/2 cups sugar, oil, unbeaten eggs, salt, orange juice, vanilla and baking powder in a large bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Grease and flour large tube pan. Alternate batter and apples, beginning with batter and ending with apples.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon.
Crumble crackers.
Add eggs and pepper.
Amount of pepper can be reduced, if desired.
Make into patties.
Fry patties in oil until brown.
Remove from heat; drain on paper towel.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Add chocolate chips and raisins.

title: banana split cake(makes 2 pies)
directions: Beat butter, eggs, vanilla and powdered sugar for 15 minutes with electric mixer.
Cut in 1/2 with butter knife.
If mix stays separated, it is thick enough.
If mix is runny, add more powdered sugar and beat a little more.
Put 1/2 of mix in each graham crust. Spread evenly to cover bottom.
Place a layer of bananas and pineapple in each pie.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for at least 6 hours.
Can be made a day ahead.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Boil pineapple juice.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar and flour.
Pour into hot juice.
Stir constantly, cooking over medium heat until thickened.
When ready to use, add whipped heavy cream to sauce.
Fold in cut-up fruit.

title: broccoli with ziti or rigatoni
directions: In a large pot, brown garlic in the oil until lightly brown (can slice or chop garlic as you prefer).
Add 1 cup of water or chicken broth, the basil, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Let simmer about 10 to 15 minutes.
Add the broccoli and cook until al dente.

title: peach salad
directions: Mix and bring first three ingredients to a boil until thick. Cool thoroughly.
Add chopped peaches and Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add peanut butter, then eggs and beat together.
Add vanilla.
Sift soda and flour.
Mix well.
Roll in balls and place on cookie sheet.
Take a fork, dip in sugar and press dough one way, then another.
Bake at 350° until done.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: off-white icing
directions: Combine ingredients and beat with mixer for 5 to 7 minutes. This makes a wonderfully spreadable and delicious frosting.

title: taffy apple dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, brown sugar and vanilla until smooth. Spread on small serving plate.
Sprinkle with chopped peanuts. Serve with apple wedges.

title: crawfish fettucini
directions: Melt butter in large, heavy saucepan.
Add onions, celery and bell pepper.
Cook 10 minutes, until clear.
Add soup and blend well.
Cover and cook for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add parsley and crawfish tails.
Cover and cook for 20 minutes, stirring often.
Add cheese, jalapeno peppers and garlic, then mix well.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook, covered, on low heat for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain and add sauce.
Mix thoroughly and pour into a 3-quart buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease bottom only of a 10 x 14 pan, preheat oven to 350 F, mix pecans and coconut and spread in bottom of pan.
Prepare cake mix as directed, pour over coconut and pecans.
Mix together the remaining ingredients and spoon over batter.
Bake 45-50 minutes.

title: viva la chicken
directions: *Save chicken drippings for top.

title: fresh vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls together on baking dish. Bake as directed on package. Cool.

Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing mix. After crust has cooled, spread cream cheese mixture on crust. Mix together vegetables and spread on top of cream cheese mixture. Sprinkle cheese on top and press down. Chill. Cut into bite size pieces.

title: pudding in a cloud
directions: Prepare pudding mix with milk as directed on package for pudding, chill.
Divide whipped topping among 8 dessert glasses, using about 1/3 cup in each.
With the back of a spoon, make a depression in the center and spread topping up the sides of the glasses.
Spoon pudding mixture into glasses.
Chill.
Makes 8 servings.

title: gingerbread(triple batch)
directions: Combine ingredients and bake until done at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: orange-glazed pork chops
directions: Brown chops on both sides; season with salt and pepper. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chops.
Cover; simmer for 1 hour.

title: three-bean baked beans
directions: In a large skillet or saucepan over medium heat, brown beef, bacon and onion; drain.
Add beans.
Combine remaining ingredients; stir into bean mixture.
Pour into a greased 2 1/2 qt. baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350 degrees for 1 hour or until beans reach desired thickness.

title: mushroom scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine soup, 1/2 cup cheese, pimento and salt in bowl.
Stir in milk and potatoes gradually.
Place in greased baking dish. Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 6 servings.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Grate German chocolate and mix with all other ingredients into batter.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° about 55 minutes.

title: skillet ball cookies
directions: Cook first 8 ingredients over medium heat for 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add remaining ingredients and roll in balls. Roll in coconut.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine raisins and nuts.
Blend all ingredients together. Mixture tends to be thick.
Grease 2 loaf pans.
Divide evenly into pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, depending on individual oven.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix eggs and oil in large mixing bowl; add salt and pepper. Add zucchini and onion; mix.
Make sure vegetables are covered well, then add cheese.
Gently toss again.
Pour into 2 1/2-quart casserole, well buttered.
Pat top with butter.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° for 20 minutes.

title: lane cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add other ingredients.
Put in cake pans and bake at 375° until done.

title: bean dip
directions: Place kidney beans in a skillet. Cook until kidney beans are soft.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Brown ground beef, pepper and onion. Add tomato sauce, chili powder and remaining seasonings, stirring well.
Simmer until desired thickness.
May be used for basic recipe for chili beans by adding 2 large cans kidney beans and hot sauce, if desired.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Prepare the rhubarb.
Sprinkle over it the 1/2 cup sugar, the nutmeg and the water.
Cut the margarine into the first 4 ingredients.
This should be crumbly.
Put 1/2 of this mixture into a greased 8-inch baking pan.
Add the rhubarb mixture, then the rest of the crumbles.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: beans 'n wieners
directions: In slow cooker, combine all ingredients.
Cover.
Cook on low setting for 3 to 4 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: strawberry delight salad
directions: Sprinkle sugar over berries.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Drain berries, reserving juices.
Add enough water to make 1 cup.
Add to gelatin and chill until partially set.
Combine marshmallows and milk.
Heat in top of double boiler and stir until marshmallows melt.
Cool thoroughly and fold in whipping cream.
Add berries to gelatin and fold in marshmallow mixture.
Pour into a 1 qt. mold and chill until set.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sprinkle chicken with poultry seasoning. Bake for 45 minutes to one hour or bake in microwave until cooked through.
Put in freezer for about 15 minutes or until cool enough to handle.
While chicken is cooking, chop celery and onion.
Cube carrots and crush garlic.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream butter with sugar until well blended.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture alternately with sour cream; blend well.
Drop on greased cookie sheets. Spread into 2-inch rounds and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake in 400° oven until golden brown, about 12 minutes.

title: pecan coffee cake
directions: Stack in
Bundt
or angel food pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes; turn out immediately.

title: fast food biscuits
directions: Mix yeast and 1/4 cup warm water.
Add this to your buttermilk mixture and then add all to the flour.
Mix well.
Place in a large covered container and refrigerate overnight.
Roll out on floured surface and cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on baking pan in 400° oven and cook for 15 minutes or until browned.
Makes 2 dozen biscuits.

title: jello salad
directions: Bring jello and pineapple to boiling point.
Let cool. Add buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Mix and let set in refrigerator.

title: easy chocolate icing
directions: Melt chocolate chips; allow to cool slightly.
Stir in sour cream and vanilla until smooth.
Vary amounts according to amount needed.
This is very ample for a 9-inch two layer cake.

title: fresh raspberry pie
directions: Combine the berries with the lemon juice.
In separate bowl, combine the sugar, flour, cloves and 1 to 2 tablespoons water if it looks dry.
Add this mixture to the berries and mix lightly. Put in a pie crust and dot with butter.
Cover with a top crust and cut slits.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: children's party punch
directions: Combine lemonade and 1 pint ice cream; beat until smooth.
Add milk; color to tint desired.
Chill; put in bowl.
Top with scoops of additional pint of ice cream.
Serves 14.

title: pumpkin pound cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Make a well.
Add oil, eggs, water and pumpkin.
Mix well.
Bake in a greased tube pan at 300° for 1 hour.

title: texas casserole
directions: Cook hamburger and garlic in butter until done.
Add tomato sauce.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add salt, pepper and sugar.
In separate bowl, combine cream cheese, sour cream and onions. Alternate layers of noodles, hamburger and cream cheese mixture in large casserole dish.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Add mushrooms.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: parmesan salad
directions: In a salad bowl, mash together the garlic, salt, mustard and pepper.
Then add the cheese, lime juice and olive oil.
Mix well and let sit until ready to serve.
Just before serving, heap the lettuce on top and toss well.

title: honey-mustard chicken drumettes with sesame seed
directions: If using chicken wings, separate them at the joints into 3 sections.
Discard the tips or save for stock.
Place chicken in shallow dish.

title: rum pound cake
directions: Boil for 5 minutes.
Add 1/4 cup rum; bring to boil again. Drizzle over cake.

title: columbian beef stew
directions: Cook meat and seasoning until meat is tender.
Add potatoes, carrots, celery and tomato paste.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Add peas, corn on cob and oregano.
Cook for additional 5 minutes.

title: super sunday casserole
directions: Place chopped cabbage in the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Place the carrot slices evenly over the top.
Place the sliced potatoes evenly over the top.
Salt and pepper between layers.
Mix the soup with the milk and poultry seasoning and pour over the top.
Arrange the browned pork chops over the top.
Top with sliced onions.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: diet pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Spray Pam in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Place 4 rings of pineapple on bottom.
Blend rest of ingredients in blender.
Pour over pineapple rings.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in water until tender, drain and set aside.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° until brown.
Add 1 cup chopped pecans to dough if you like nuts.

title: rindsragout
directions: Brown steak with onion.
Heat broth to boiling.
Mix sour cream with flour; stir into broth and add mushrooms.
Season to taste.
Mix all of the ingredients together and place in a slow oven for about an hour or so.
Serve over hot noodles or rice.

title: gourmet goulash
directions: Place beef, onion, garlic and 1 teaspoon salt in an electric skillet.
Heat at about 350°; cook and stir until beef is browned. Add noodles.

title: easy easy tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients and spoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cheesy broccoli bake
directions: In a bowl, combine the broccoli, soup, cheese spread and rice. Transfer to a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Toss bread crumbs and butter; sprinkle over top. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes; uncover and bake 15 minutes longer. Yield: 4 servings.

title: chicken scampi
directions: Heat butter in skillet. Add chicken and cook until browned. Add soup, water, lemon juice and garlic. Heat to a boil. Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes or until done. Serve with pasta.

title: fresh mushroom salad
directions: Slice mushrooms into salad bowl.
Grate Mozzarella cheese and add to mushrooms.
Chop green onions and parsley; add to mushrooms.
Mix oil, vinegar and Cavender's seasoning separately. Do not pour dressing over mushroom salad until ready to serve. Parsley must be fresh.

title: green beans a la provencale(a true french dish from the provence region of southern france.)
directions: Clean and cut green beans in half.
Steam or boil beans until cooked but still a little crunchy.
In separate pan, put olive oil, parsley, salt, large onion (cut in quarter size pieces), garlic and tomatoes (cut in quarters).
Cook over slow heat with a lid and let simmer until onion is cooked, stirring regularly. Tomatoes will produce a lot of liquid.
Add green beans (drained) to the tomatoes and other ingredients and let simmer another 15 minutes or until green beans are fully cooked.
Leftovers are great warmed up but do not use canned beans for this recipe. Serve hot after draining most of the liquid.
The leftover liquid is often used by the French as additional sauce added to a meat stew.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except oleo, in a casserole dish. Pour melted oleo over top.
Bake at 400° for approximately 25 minutes or until lightly browned on top.

title: homesteader's casserole
directions: Layer in casserole dish, 1/2 potatoes, 1/2 sausage and 1/2 Velveeta cheese in chunks.
Layer remaining potatoes, remaining sausage and package of vegetable.
Cover and cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and cook until melted.

title: dumplings
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together into mixing bowl. Combine milk and salad oil.
Add all at once to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Drop from tablespoon atop bubbling stew.
Cover tightly.
Let mixture return to boiling.
Reduce heat (don't lift cover).
Simmer 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes approximately 10.

title: denver chocolate pudding
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Melt chocolate and butter and add milk and vanilla.
Combine all together and pour into a buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle the following (in order listed) over mixture:
1/2 cup brown sugar, 1/2 cup white sugar and 4 tablespoons cocoa; 1 cup cold water poured over all.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: apples and kraut pork chops
directions: Peel and cut apples into 1/2-inch cubes.
Remove outer leaves of cabbage; cook and shred.
Peel and dice onion.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease large roasting pan.
In large bowl, toss together the apples, cabbage, onion, salt, pepper, vinegar and broth.
Pour into roasting pan.
Place pork chops on top.
Cover and roast two hours.
Chops should be nearly falling off the bone.
May be served with boiled potatoes.

title: wine cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well with electric mixer. Beat for 5 minutes.
Bake in a 9-inch tube pan for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle top with confectioners sugar.

title: fruited pistachio pudding
directions: In large bowl, combine pudding mix, whipped topping and salad dressing; mix well.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Leave in bowl or spoon into individual serving
dishes.
Serve immediately or chill.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add strawberries, pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Pour half of mixture into a 13 x 9-inch dish; let congeal.
Spread sour cream on top of congealed layer, then add remaining mixutre on top; let all congeal.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring to a boil the first 4 ingredients and boil 1 minute. Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients, stirring well after each. Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Bake frozen pie shell.
In medium saucepan over high heat steam broccoli.
In another pan over medium heat melt butter.
Stir in flour and salt until smooth.
Add onion and cook 1 minute.
Slowly stir in milk, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and begins to boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in broccoli and cheese.
When cheese has slightly melted, stir in eggs.
Add cooked meat.
Bake 30 minutes or center is firm to touch.

title: mama's waffles
directions: Blend baking soda, buttermilk, egg and butter, then, 1 tablespoon at a time, blend in self-rising flour.
Makes 12 waffles.

title: chicken potato soup
directions: In a large pot, put the water.
Add all vegetables and bouillon.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 3 minutes.
Add hash brown potatoes; simmer for 3 minutes.
Add soup, milk and water, chicken and cheese; simmer again until cheese is melted and chicken is heated well.

title: strawberry-jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in one cup boiling water.
Add strawberries while hot.
Let cool.
Add pineapple (drained) and nuts.
Let partially jell.
Whip Cool Whip and cream cheese together and add to partially jelled ingredients.
Pour into mold or container and let jell.
Serves approximately 12.

title: dressing for banana croquets
directions: Stir all ingredients together. Bring to a slight boil until thickens. Be sure to continue stirring. Allow dressing to cool.

title: squash casserole
directions: May mix squash with zucchini squash if desired for color. Personally I prefer a little more minced onion.
I also add about 1 tablespoon of cut pimento for color.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Put onion, margarine, Cheez Whiz and soup in a pan.
Melt and pour into casserole dish.
Top with chips.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add dry ingredients and milk. Mix well.
Fold in cranberries, washed and drained.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: candy bar cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Pour into sheet cake pan and bake.
While cake is still hot, poke holes with wooden spoon handle in cake.
Pour sweetened condensed milk and ice cream topping in cake holes.
After cooling, frost with Cool Whip and sprinkle brickle chips on top.
Refrigerate leftovers. This cake is best when served cold.

title: tortellini soup
directions: Mix broth and spinach.
Crush with hand the tomatoes over stockpot.
Italian sausage should be baked at 400° for 45 minutes. Cool overnight and slice.
Add to soup.
Slice up 1 large onion. Brown onion and mushrooms in frying pan.
Add to soup.
Add Italian seasoning and salt and pepper to taste.
Add 1 pound of cheese tortellini.

title: home-style chicken seasoning
directions: Mix together and store in plastic or glass container with tight lid.
One teaspoon of this seasoning may be substituted for 1 packet of G. Washington's seasoning (golden) or for 1 teaspoon of McKay's seasoning.
When substituting for McKay's, use less salt in recipe.

title: tarzan bars
directions: Grease
x 13-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine brown sugar, preserves, butter, vanilla and eggs.
Blend well.
Stir in remaining ingredients (except powdered sugar) by hand just until moistened.
Pour
into
prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for about
35 minutes or until done.
Cool.
Spread with powdered sugar.
Cut into bars.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat corn and milk.
Add egg.
Stir in crackers.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: fresh tomato vegetable soup
directions: In large saucepan or kettle, cook bacon until lightly browned. Remove and drain; crumble and reserve.
Pour off all but two tablespoons fat.
Add onion, chopped celery and quartered tomatoes; cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are tender.
Simmer, uncovered, over low heat for 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and bacon; simmer 30 minutes longer, until vegetables are tender.
Makes about 1 1/2 quarts and serves 6.

title: lisa's rainbow cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs, flour, sugar, almond extract and butter with electric mixer. Divide into 3 bowls. Add 8 drops of food coloring to each bowl (more, if desired).
Spray three 11 x 7 x 3/4-inch aluminum pans with Pam.
Place mixture evenly into pans and bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until you can pull a toothpick out clean.
Let cool about 30 minutes.
Melt the chocolate.
Place one layer on waxed paper and spread chocolate on one side.
Let chocolate harden.
Flip over on waxed paper. Repeat for second layer.
When chocolate is hardened, thinly spread the preserves on the other side.
Make a sandwich, making sure to keep the chocolate on top and bottom.
Cut into bite size pieces.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Sprinkle sliced tomatoes with 3 tablespoons salt and let stand 3 hours.
Rinse, drain well and then grind enough tomatoes to make 2 quarts.
Mix vinegar and sugar and pour over ground mixture. Boil 15 minutes and serve.

title: sesame chicken(from israel)
directions: Blend together in a large bowl with flour and sesame seed, along with the paprika and a little salt.
Coat the chicken thighs in the mixture.
Dip them first in a mixture of the eggs and chicken broth, then back into the flour again.
You may brown these lightly in a frying pan and finish in the oven or you may simply bake them at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a greased pan.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: love bites
directions: In a large bowl, mix vanilla wafer crumbs, powdered sugar, walnuts and cocoa powder.
Stir in cherries and corn syrup until well mixed.
Sprinkle with water and mix until throughly blended, using hands if necessary.
Shape mixture into 3/4-inch balls. Roll in colored sugar.
Store in an airtight container overnight before serving.

title: easy hot appetizers
directions: At least 4 hours before serving, chop green onions and tops very fine.
Combine mayonnaise, cheese and onion very well.
Store in a tightly covered container in the refrigerator until ready to serve.
Split biscuits and spread mix on top of each half.
Broil with or without paprika sprinkled on top until bubbly.
Keep a close eye, as these burn very quickly.
Serve at once warning guests that they are very hot.

title: adelle payne's pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Check to see if done by gently shaking.
Serves 8.

title: blackberry lemonade
directions: Puree berries in processor.
Strain through sieve, pressing on solids with back of spoon.
Transfer to large pitcher.
Add 12 cups water, lemonade concentrate and 3 tablespoons sugar, taste, and more sugar if desired.

title: date nut bread
directions: Cut dates into small pieces and let stand in boiling water with baking soda while mixing dry ingredients.
Add melted butter and well beaten egg.
Last add the water with dates, nuts and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly until well blended.
Bake in well-greased 9 x 5 x 2-inch bread pan for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Grease mold with mayonnaise.
Heat soup in double boiler. Soften cream cheese and add to soup gradually.
Mix Knox gelatine with 1/4 cup shrimp water.
Add to soup and cream cheese mixture. Let cool 15 minutes.
Add mayonnaise, shrimp, celery and onion. When mixture begins to thicken, pour into mold and refrigerate.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature. Chop onions and cut up dried beef into small pieces. Combine all ingredients using about 3/4 of the beef. Roll ball in remaining beef for outside coating. Refrigerate. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: sloppy joes
directions: In a large skillet, fry onion and hamburger till well done. Add seasonings, tomato soup and water. Cook over medium heat 20 to 30 minutes. Remove from heat, add vanilla and worcestershire sauce. Serve on buns.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix mayo, sour cream and taco season mix together well and set aside.
Spread refried beans layer thin on tray.
(I use pizza pan.)
Then spread seasoned sour cream/mayo mixture on top of beans.

title: banana boat pudding
directions: Prepare pudding mix as directed on box.
Cover and chill. When chilled, fold in marshmallows and whipped cream.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter over medium heat.
Add meat and brown.
Add flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add soup.
Simmer uncovered for 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream. Heat through.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Cook noodles as directed on package.
Serve Hamburger Stroganoff over cooked noodles.

title: vegetable cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into balls or logs.
Makes 1 large or 2 medium.

title: curry potatoes and tuna
directions: Cut the potatoes into 1/4-inch slices.
Mix the tuna and the grated garlic.
Mix the chicken bouillon soup, curry powder, sugar, soy sauce and salt together.
Put the potatoes, tuna and the bouillon soup mixture in the pot; cook them on low heat.
Put them on the dish; sprinkle with the chopped parsley and raisins.

title: candy bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add oatmeal, Karo and vanilla.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 15 minutes at 350°. Do not overbake.
After completely cooled, spread with chocolate mix.
To make chocolate mix, melt in heavy saucepan chocolate chips and peanut butter.
After icing, place in refrigerator to cool.
Cut into bars.

title: applesauce cupcakes
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and spices together.
Mix sugar, shortening and egg.
Add applesauce, nuts and raisins (add carrots, banana and coconut now, if desired).
Bake in greased and floured muffin tins or paper cupcake holders at 300° to 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Beat cake mix, eggs, pudding and oil.
Add the 7-Up.
Bake mixture at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: apricot cookies
directions: Mix flour, butter and cream cheese.
Form into about 5 balls and refrigerate until chilled.
Take 1 ball out and roll out in powdered sugar; cut into about 12 squares.
Put about 1 teaspoon filling on each square and spread evenly over it.
Roll tightly and bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter together. Pour melted chocolate in paper cupcake liners. Layer peanut butter mixture and top with layer of melted chocolate. Refrigerate until set.

title: apple bundles
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare apples with coring, peeling and slicing thinly.
Cut in half.
Unroll dough; separate into 8 triangles.
Cut each in half to make 16 triangles.
Place 3 to 4 apple slices at the wide end of each strip and roll up.
Arrange bundles in a deep dish baker.

title: spinach and strawberry salad
directions: Wash spinach thoroughly.
Drain and pat dry with paper towels. Remove and discard any tough stems.
Break into bite size pieces. Place in a large salad bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and toss with Sweet and Sour Salad Dressing.
Serve immediately.

title: zucchini pita
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased 9-inch pie pan. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour, until brown and crusty.

title: ground meat roll-ups
directions: Saute onion in oil in skillet.
Add ground meat; cook until brown and crumbly, stirring frequently.
Drain.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add 1/2 cup milk gradually, stirring constantly. Cool.
Roll biscuit dough into 1/4-inch thick 18-inch square on floured surface.
Spread with ground meat mixture.
Roll as for jelly roll; seal ends.
Slice into 1 1/2-inch slices.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Combine remaining 1/2 cup milk, soup, chili powder and catsup in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Serve over roll-ups.
Yields 18 servings.

title: chocolate covered pretzels
directions: Combine chocolate chips and shortening in a microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave on High for 1 minute; stir.
Microwave again for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes until melted.
Dip pretzels in chocolate and put on wax paper to dry.
Put in refrigerator or let dry in room. Enjoy.

title: easy peas
directions: Heat soup and cheese until cheese melts.
Add peas and pepper. Heat.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pink stuff
directions: Place contents of the Eagle Brand milk in a large bowl followed by carton of Cool Whip, cherry pie filling and crushed pineapple (well drained).

title: cherry pecan bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs until light and fluffy.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture with buttermilk.
Beat until blended.
Stir in nuts and cherries.
Add vanilla.

title: fudge in the micro
directions: Butter a 9-inch square baking dish; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, combine chocolate chips, sweet chocolate, nuts and Marshmallow Creme; set aside.
In 2-quart measure, combine sugar, evaporated milk, butter and salt; mix well.
Microwave at High for 2 minutes, stirring after each minute.
Microwave at High for 1 1/2 to 4 minutes, or until mixture comes to a full rolling boil. Pour hot milk mixture over chocolate mixture.
Mix until chocolate melts and Marshmallow Creme is blended.
Spread mixture evenly into prepared dish.
Chill until cool and set, about 3 hours.
Cut into small squares.

title: mexican dip
directions: Simmer until cheese is melted.
Serve warm with chips.

title: california toffee butter crunch
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan. Coarsely chop half the nuts and set aside. Finely chop the remaining nuts and sprinkle buttered pan with half of finely chopped nuts.
Cover with 6 chocolate bars.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Cream 2 tablespoons sugar and margarine.
Add pretzels. Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool. Mix next 3 ingredients together and spread on pretzel base.
Mix jello and water together.
Add 10 ounce package frozen strawberries.
Mix well.
Pour on top of cream cheese mixture. Refrigerate.

title: "almost" yummy sugar-free punch
directions: Place frozen concentrate (lemonade and orange juice) in blender with 1/2 cup water.
Whirl until blended.
Add frozen strawberries.
Again whirl until blended.
Pour this mixture into punch bowl.
Add 2 liter bottles of Sprite.
Taste.
If mixture is too strong add ice cubes.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix beer with flour.
Put in greased loaf pan.
Bake 40 minutes, maybe less, depending on oven temperature.
Bake at 375°.

title: fudge custard pie
directions: Place flour, brown sugar and salt in an unbaked pie crust. Take fingers and combine or mix together over bottom of crust. Combine other ingredients and pour over the flour and sugar mix. Scatter a few shakes of ground cinnamon or nutmeg over the pie ingredients and place in oven at 400° for 10 minutes.
Then reduce heat to 350° until the custard is set, perhaps 30 minutes.
A delicious pie!

title: nacho dip
directions: In glass or microwavable container with lid (approximately 8 x 8-inch) press cream cheese across bottom of dish for first layer. For second layer, spread chili across cream cheese.
Spread salsa for third layer.
Add layer of sliced jalapenos (optional). Sprinkle cheese across top.
Place lid on and microwave approximately 5 minutes or until Cheddar cheese is melted.

title: apple squash casserole
directions: Peel vegetable and cut into small slices or chunks.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter.
Mix with sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, nuts and salt. Place a layer of squash in a 2-quart casserole dish. Drizzle with sugar-butter mixture. Top with a layer of apples, then butter-sugar.
Repeat until all ingredients are used. Dot with remaining butter. Cover and bake 45 to 60 minutes (may be a little less) at 350° until tender. Serves 4.

title: fluffy yogurt fruit pie
directions: In larger mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in yogurt, lemon juice and food coloring.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into prepared crust.
Chill 4 hours or until set.
Garnish with strawberries.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 5 x 9-inch loaf pan. Bake at 325° for about 1 1/4 hours or until top is brown.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: sunny orange french toast
directions: Place Cream of Wheat cereal on wax paper; set aside.
In a medium bowl, beat together the sugar, orange rind, orange juice, eggs
and vanilla extract.
Dip each bread slice into orange juice mixture just to soak.
Coat with Cream of Wheat cereal.
Dip again in orange juice mixture.
Arrange all slices in single layer on large cookie sheet.
In large skillet or griddle, melt margarine over medium-low heat; fry 2 or 3 bread slices at a time to brown both sides.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peach cobbler
directions: First melt butter.
Pour into baking dish; set aside.
Mix sugar, flour and milk into pan the butter was in.
Pour the peaches over the mixture, then if desired sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Put into oven.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions. Mix in mushroom soup and sour cream.
Chop chicken and mix all together.
Add 1 cup chicken broth.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour in preheated oven.
Great for leftover turkey.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in a casserole dish.
Add other ingredients to butter, except chicken.
Mix well.
"Dip" top of chicken in mixture, then turn over and put on top of rice.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: irish soda bread
directions: In a mixing bowl combine flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse meal. Stir in caraway seed and raisins.
Combine buttermilk and egg. Stir into dry ingredients just until moistened.
Turn out onto a floured surface and knead lightly until smooth.
Shape dough into a ball and place on a greased baking pan.
Pat into a 7-inch round loaf.
Cut a 4-inch cross about 1/4-inch deep on top to allow for expansion.
Brush top with milk.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until golden brown.
Yield:
1 loaf.

title: raisin cookies that stay soft
directions: Boil raisins and water for about 5 minutes.
There should be 1/2 cup juice left after cooking.
Cool.
Cream sugar and Crisco. Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift flour, salt, nutmeg, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add to egg and sugar mixture.
Combine soda to raisins and add to the dough.
Drop walnut size dough on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: drop noodles
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients, adding the water to the flour and egg. The dough will be sticky. Add salt if needed. Drop dough by rounded spoonful into boiling broth. Noodles are done when they float to the top. Put finished noodles into bouillon. You can also put noodles into soup or add chicken for chicken and noodles. Also great in fried cabbage and potatoes.

title: rum slush
directions: Combine boiling water and sugar in a large plastic container and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Cover and freeze.
Serve plain or with white soda or 50/50.

title: turtle cake
directions: Follow directions on box for mixing cake mix.
Put half the batter in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt and stir in double boiler the caramels, milk and margarine.
Spread that mixture over the cake and then add remainder of batter.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients together quickly, divide in half and roll out between wax paper.
Comes out the same everytime.
Can freeze. Makes 2 crust pie.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Crumble all toast, bread and corn bread into a 9 x 13 pan. Debone chicken and add to the bread. Saut onions and celery until soft and clear. Add to the bread and chicken. Add remaining ingredients. Moisten well with chicken broth and mix it up. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until lightly brown. Cool and serve.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Cream oil, sugar and eggs together.
Add buttermilk and dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: no bake squares
directions: In saucepan, melt chocolate in the milk over low heat, stirring until thick and smooth. Remove from heat; add peppermint. Reserve 1/2 cup of mixture for frosting. Add remainder to crumb mixture. Stir until all crumbs are moistened. Turn into pan. Press down. Spread reserved chocolate mixture on top; chill.

title: chinese scotchies
directions: Melt butterscotch chips in a double boiler. Add the rest of the ingredients. Drop by teaspoonful onto wax paper; refrigerator about 30 minutes. Store in airtight container.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Cream lard and sugar.
Mix all dry ingredients except soda and add to creamed mixture.
Add soda to soup and mix well.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add the water and mix.
Add dates and nuts. Bake at 350° about 40 minutes or until a toothpick comes up dry from the center of the cake.

title: stuffed steak(rouladen)
directions: You will also need white thread to tie up steak.

title: chicken quesadillas
directions: In small bowl, combine soup, chicken, 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese and chopped pepper.
Top 1/2 of each tortilla with 1/4 cup soup mixture, spreading evenly to within 1/2-inch of edge.
Moisten edges of tortillas with water; fold over, pressing edges to seal. On 2 large baking sheets, arrange tortillas.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes, or until hot.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese.
Serve with salsa and sour cream.
Garnish with green onions and cilantro, if desired.

title: edith harris' spoon bread
directions: In saucepan, add boiling water to cornmeal.
Cook, stirring until mushy consistency.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar, baking powder, salt and oleo.
Stir in milk and well beaten egg yolks. Fold in egg whites.
Bake in greased 2-quart casserole at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Note:
Amounts of ingredients depend on size salad you want.

title: puff donuts
directions: Blend together the sugar, butter (or margarine), eggs and milk.
Mix flour and baking powder together well, then add to first mixture.
Drop dough by teaspoons into hot shortening.
Fry until golden, turning once.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add remaining ingredients and mix just to moisten.
Pour into round 8 or 9-inch cake pan or quiche pan. Bake at 375° (350° for glass pans) for 35 minutes or until brown and set in the middle.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix together the ham, pork, beef, milk, bread crumbs and eggs. Sprinkle brown sugar on corn flakes and put on top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 300°.

title: broccoli cauliflower casserole
directions: Thaw veggies and combine in 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Combine cheeses into microwave-safe bowl and cook 5 to 8 minutes or until smooth. Pour cheese over veggies and crumble crackers over the top. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients. Place in loaf pan (microwave). Pour catsup on top. Microwave on High for 15 minutes. Check for doneness.

title: lazy day lasagna
directions: Cook noodles as directed and drain.
Add browned meat and oregano to spaghetti sauce.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: (You may substitute peanut butter for chocolate chips.)

title: cole slaw
directions: In salad bowl, combine cabbage, carrots, green pepper, salt and pepper; toss slightly to blend.
Add vinegar to mayonnaise, a teaspoonful at a time, stirring well after each addition.
Pour over cole slaw; toss until well mixed.
Makes 2 servings.

title: saurbraten
directions: Cover the rump roast with the vinegar and let stand overnight. In the morning, take half the vinegar and as much water.
Add a few peppercorns, cloves, bay leaf, onion, a little allspice, raisins and almonds.
Let beef stew in this liquid until tender.
Take out beef and slice.
Brown the flour in a piece of butter.
Add to liquid and stir until smooth.
Thicken with 2 to 3 gingersnaps stirring to a smooth paste.
Add hot water, if necessary.
Put the sliced meat in with the liquid and simmer slowly until ready to serve.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix and cook over medium heat until thick.
Stir constantly and add coconut.
Put in cooked pie crust.

title: barbecue hot dogs
directions: Leave on high to melt jelly; then leave on high to brown hot dogs, about 3 hours.

title: old-fashioned vegetable soup
directions: Place meat and water in a large soup kettle.
Bring to a boil. Skim surface occasionally.
When broth is clear, add tomatoes or juice, celery, onion and parsley.
Cover and simmer gently for 2 1/2 hours.
Add carrots, rutabaga and potatoes.
Simmer 1/2 hour.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Mix cornmeal, eggs, oil and corn. Fold in sour cream last and mix well. Pour into pan that has been sprayed with cooking spray. Bake 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: communion loaf
directions: Mix all together into a bread pan, 4 or 5 inches in diameter. After baked, brush on butter and brown.
Wrap in foil or Saran Wrap.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: squash supreme
directions: Mash cooked squash, add onion, soup, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Butter casserole dish and sprinkle with 1/2 of crumbs. Add squash mixture.
Cover with remaining crumbs and generous dots of butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: squash supreme
directions: Mash squash.
Add sour cream, soup and other ingredients except crumbs.
Sprinkle a layer of crumbs in the casserole dish. Spoon in squash mixture.
Cover with crumbs and dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: layered bean dip
directions: Layer ingredients in this order:
refried beans, picante sauce, tomato, green onions, cheddar cheese, and olives in a 10 x 10 inch serving dish.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: zucchini stuffing
directions: Saute zucchini and onion until tender.
Combine with all ingredients in large bowl except margarine and 1/2 cup stuffing. Mix thoroughly.
Spray 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with Pam.
Pour mixture into pan.
Combine margarine and 1/2 cup stuffing mix and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: squash patties
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, beating until smooth.
Stir in squash and onion; add pepper if desired.
Drop mixture by tablespoonfuls into hot greased frying pan.
Cook until golden, turning once.
Drain on paper towel and serve.

title: hootenanny frapp
directions: Combine sugar and water in a large saucepan; cook over medium heat until sugar dissolves, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; stir in orange juice concentrate, strawberries and pineapple. Pour mixture into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Freeze until firm.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick, cheese and milk until blended.
Spoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 20 minutes or until brown.
Melt butter; add garlic powder.
Brush on biscuits.

title: sugared peanuts
directions: Mix
sugar
and
water in an iron skillet.
Add peanuts and bring
to
a
boil
for about 20 minutes over medium heat. Stir constantly the last few minutes, until liquid crystallizes on peanuts.
Spread
evenly on large cookie sheet and bake in a 325° oven for 15 minutes.

title: creamed peas and mushrooms
directions: Cook peas and keep warm.
Cook onion in butter for about 5 minutes.
Add peas and mushrooms and cook for 5 minutes.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and cook slowly for 10 minutes.

title: lemon rice pilaf
directions: In a medium saucepan, melt butter over medium heat.

Add onion and saute stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes or until softened. Add rice and cook, stirring for one minute, or until well coated. Add broth, lemon juice, lemon rind, bay leaf, salt and pepper; bring to a boil.
Lower heat, cover and simmer until rice is tender and all liquid is absorbed (15 to 20 minutes for white; 35 to 40 for brown rice).
Remove bay leaf.
Top each serving with slivers of lemon zest or sprinkle with parsley, if desired.

title: watergate salad
directions: Drain fruit; mix Cool Whip and pudding thoroughly.
Fold in other ingredients.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: millionaire candy
directions: Melt in double boiler the package of caramels with the water. When melted, stir in the pecans.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Chill in refrigerator for 2 to 4 hours.
In double boiler, melt the Hershey bars and wax.
Dip the candy in the chocolate and put on wax paper.
Keep chocolate hot to make smooth candy and less will be used.

title: oven-fried onion rings
directions: Spray large baking sheet.
In small bowl, stir together crumbs, margarine, salt and red pepper.
Spread crumbs on a sheet of wax paper.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add fruit liquid.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in cottage cheese, nuts, cherries, whipped cream and drained fruit.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook ingredients until peanuts start to pop and turn brown. Remove from heat and stir in 2 to 2 1/2 teaspoons of baking soda and pour onto buttered baking sheet.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients; drain and return to pan.
Add next 4 ingredients plus 2 cups of water.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.
Cook shells and add to soup 5 minutes before you are finished cooking.

title: banana split cake
directions: Early in day or day ahead, soften vanilla ice cream in refrigerator, about 40 minutes.
Finely chop 1/2 cup walnuts, reserving remaining 1/4 cup for garnish later.
In 9-inch spring-form pan, combine chopped nuts, graham cracker crumbs, 3 tablespoons butter and 2 tablespoons sugar.
With fingers, press mixture to bottom of pan.
Evenly spread vanilla ice cream on top of crust; freeze until firm, about 45 minutes.

title: mexican corn salad
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Leave the cheddar cheese chunks until just before serving.	Then mix the remaining ingredients and add.
Salad will keep a couple of days if cheese not added.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar until fluffy.
Continue creaming, adding eggs, one at a time.
Mix flour, cocoa and baking powder gradually.
Add to creamed mixture on low speed in 4 equal parts with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake in prepared pan at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal refrigerator crisps
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in all remaining ingredients.
Divide dough in half.
Roll into 2 rolls in waxed paper.
Rolls should be about 2 inches in diameter. Chill and slice 1/4 inch thick.
Bake at 350° until golden brown. These rolls may be frozen.

title: orange sliced candy cake
directions: Use 1 cup flour over dates and candy.
Cream margarine and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add buttermilk and mix well.
Add flour, candy, nuts, dates and coconut.
Cook in a tube pan at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: time to spare ribs
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Shake flour in oven cooking bag (large, 14 x 20-inch).
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Add barbecue sauce, onion and green peppers.
Squeeze bag to blend all ingredients.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Mix all together and put in casserole dish.
Mix 1 cup cornflake crumbs and 1/4 cup melted butter until crumbly.
Put on top of potato mixture.
Bake for 1 hour, uncovered, in 350° oven.

title: peanut butter kiss cookies
directions: Beat margarine, peanut butter, 1/2 cup granulated sugar and brown sugar until creamy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
In another bowl, stir together flour, baking soda and salt.
Gradually add and blend into creamed mixture.
Place the 1/4 cup granulated sugar in a small bowl.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar to coat.
Place balls 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove cookies from oven.
Quickly top each with kiss.
Press down firmly.
Let cool completely.
Store airtight.

title: rich chocolate frosting
directions: Beat sugar, milk, butter, choco bake, vanilla and salt in small mixer bowl until smooth and creamy.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: microwave fudge
directions: In a bowl, mix powdered sugar and unsweetened cocoa, add milk and margarine and microwave on High for 4 1/2 to 6 minutes.
Add nuts and vanilla; stir until smooth.
Spread in a greased square dish and chill.

title: pepperoni pizza spread
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 9 ingredients.
Spread into a 13 x 9 baking dish, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly and lightly browned.
Makes about 6 cups.
DO NOT USE reduced fat mayonnaise.
Can be spread on breads or use crackers for dipping.

title: aunt letha's harvest bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Beat in eggs 1 at a time.
Add pumpkin and orange juice.
Add sifted dry ingredients; mix well. Add nuts.
Pour in 4 one-pound coffee cans, greased and floured. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cans can be sealed and frozen. Serve plain or spread with cream cheese softened with pineapple juice.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: In large bowl, stir together flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.
In small bowl beat together water, vinegar and egg.
Add to flour mixture and stir until all ingredients are moistened.
Divide dough into 5 portions.
With hands, shape into flat round patty.
Chill 1/2 hour.
Roll out and bake at 450° on center rack of oven.
Dough may be kept in the freezer until ready to use.

title: chinese chews from alaska(by jimmie mae king)
directions: Mix
all together and spread in greased pan.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Cut while warm and roll in powdered sugar.

title: baked chicken
directions: Arrange beef on bottom of baking dish.
Cook chicken halfway and then put chicken on top of beef.
Mix cream of chicken soup and sour cream and pour on top.
Bake at 200° until done.

title: texas stew
directions: Brown meat. Drain.
Add Ro-Tel, soup, onion, garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Let simmer until onions are tender.
Cut up cheese, let melt in meat mixture and spices.
When melted, add rice. Serve hot over Fritos in a bowl, or can be used as a dip.
Serves 12.

title: sausage bread
directions: Add pepper and onion to sausage as it finishes browning. Cook until vegetables are limp and onion is clear.
Grease a bundt pan.
Cut one can of biscuits into quarters and line the bottom of the pan.
Spread 1/2 of the cheese and 1/2 of the sausage mixture over the biscuits.
Cut the second can of biscuits into quarters and repeat the layers using the remaining sausage mixture and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30-35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: green chili pinwheels(appetizer)
directions: Mix ingredients together and spread equally on 3 flour tortillas.
Roll up tortillas individually.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate for 3 hours or more.
Cut into pinwheels shortly before serving.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: gazpacho
directions: Plunge tomatoes in boiling water for 30 seconds to loosen skins, then immerse in cold water.
Slip skins off; core and coarsely chop tomatoes.

title: harvey house cole slaw
directions: Cook and pour over layers while boiling.
Place in refrigerator for 4 hours.
Mix and serve.

title: roast beef
directions: Combine soup, water and soup mix together.
Place in crock-pot.
Add roast and cook overnight on low heat.

title: pancakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add milk and eggs.
Mix. Place 2 tablespoons oil in frypan. When hot, add batter by spoonfuls. Turn when batter has bubbles on top and is dry around edges.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Boil sugar and corn syrup together for one minute.
Stir in peanut butter, margarine and vanilla.
Pour over cornflakes and mix well.
Drop on wax paper-covered cookie sheets.
Let sit until firm.

title: "heart smart" spinach stuffed shells
directions: Mix spinach, Ricotta, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses, egg, nutmeg and pepper; set aside.
Cook shells as directed, omitting salt.
Drain.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Fill each shell with about 1 tablespoon of spinach mixture.
In bottom of 9-inch square baking dish, spoon 1/2 cup of sauce.
Place shells in single layer over sauce.
Pour remaining sauce over shells.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes until heated through and bubbly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Put into greased pan and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add melted butter, Coke and cocoa; stir well.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Fold in marshmallows.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes. Remove from oven and ice cake while still hot.

title: parmesan potatoes(4 servings)
directions: Position rack in lowest third of oven and preheat to 375°. Place potatoes in roasting pan.
Add oil and red pepper and toss to coat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bake until tender on inside and crusty on outside, turning once, about 1 hour. Sprinkle with Parmesan and basil.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg, milk and bananas.
Set aside. Combine flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Add flour mixture to banana mixture.
Add pecans.
Pour mixture into greased bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: nine day slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, celery, onions, carrot and green pepper.
Add 2 cups sugar and blend well.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil and pour over cabbage mixture immediately and allow to cool. Cover and store in refrigerator.
Slaw will stay fresh and crisp for 9 days.

title: coney island hot dogs
directions: Saute meat until brown.
Drain fat off.
Add onions and cook until transparent.
Add garlic, chili powder, dry mustard, brown sugar, lemon juice and tomato sauce.
Cook and stir until well blended.

title: polish kielbasa at christmas time
directions: Mix well and stuff in casings.
Makes 4 small rings.
Cook in large pot, covered with water, for 45 minutes.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Lay aluminum foil on pan.
Place beef, sliced potato, onion, bell pepper, salt and pepper.
Bake in oven for 1 hour at 375°. Serve with rice.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Blend all ingredients, stirring well. Pour into pie shell.
Bake in center of oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown ground beef and mix with taco seasoning.
Set aside to cool.
Mix together mayonnaise and whipped cream cheese.
Spread on bottom of glass pie dish.
Layer salsa, then ground beef and package of sharp cheese.
Top with onion, tomato and green pepper. Sprinkle on top.

title: apple dip
directions: Put this in a microwavable dish.
Nuke for 30 seconds.
Stir until bits are melted.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Cook a pan of cornbread your normal way.
Crumble up and add these ingredients.
Mix all together and pour into greased pan. Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat; add beans and simmer 15 minutes.
Drain.
Cool. Add cheese, meat, beans and onion to lettuce.
Toss.
Before serving, add chips and tomatoes.
Toss.
Add dressing.
Toss.

title: almond squares
directions: Combine cake mix, 1 egg and margarine; mix well.
Press into 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
With mixer, mix remaining eggs, cream cheese, vanilla and almond extract with powdered sugar until smooth and creamy.
Spread on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: breakfast donuts
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups flour and yeast.
Heat milk, margarine, sugar and salt until warm.
Add flour mixture and potatoes.
Beat with mixer 30 seconds on low, then 3 minutes on high.
Stir in remaining flour with spoon.
Cover and chill 2 hours or overnight. Stir down; roll to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with doughnut cutter. Fry in hot oil until brown.
Dip in Donut Glaze.

title: one dish fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven
In 3 quart casserole dish, melt margarine
in
oven.
Combine other ingredients (except fruit) in mixing bowl and pour over margarine. Do not stir!
Pour hot fruit over mixture.
Do not stir!
Cook 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hawaiian pudding
directions: Melt butter; mix with crushed wafers and pat evenly in 10-inch pan.
Mix lemon juice and milk, stirring until thickened.
Cut bananas over wafers; spread sauce over bananas.
Add drained pineapple over bananas.
Add can of coconut on top of pineapple; cover with Cool Whip.
Add cherries for garnish; sprinkle with nuts.

title: toni's secret sloppy joe sauce
directions: Mix the above ingredients together and then add to the cooked ground beef.
Heat through and Enjoy!

title: too easy peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place fruit in buttered 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Cut crust from bread slices and cut each slice into five fingers.
Place bread fingers over the fruit.

title: sweet cucumber pickle
directions: Slice cucumbers.
Soak 12 hours in lime water; rinse.
Soak 4 hours in salt water; rinse.
Soak 2 hours in clear water; drain. Bring to a boil in alum water.
Rinse in hot water.
Make syrup using sugar, vinegar, turmeric and pickling spices the size of an egg in cheesecloth.
Boil cucumber in syrup for 1/2 hour.
Cool and pack in sterilized jars.

title: layered banana pineapple dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar and margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press evenly onto bottom of pan.
Arrange banana slices on crust.

title: dip for raw vegetables
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate for at least two hours.

title: cherry pie cake
directions: Mix cake with margarine to look like crumbled pie crust.
Save 1 cup for topping.
Spread rest in bottom of 9 x 12-inch greased pan.
Pour pie filling on top.
Put remaining "pie crust" and pecans on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: poor man's dinner
directions: Brown beef and drain fat.
Slice potatoes in thin circles and onion.
Layer the beef, then potatoes and then onion.
Pour the soup over layers and bake until potatoes and onions are done. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift the flour, sugar, cocoa, salt and the baking soda into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add into the pan the vanilla, oil, vinegar and cold water.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken n rice
directions: Mix all ingredients except onion soup mix and chicken.
Place in a greased 8 x 13 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 package onion soup mix over rice mixture.
Place chicken on top and cover with remaining onion soup mix.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not add salt or other liquid. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: french chocolate cake(just this side of fudge)
directions: Grease a 9 or 10-inch spring-form pan.
Preheat oven to 425°.

title: miniature cheesecakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream until fluffy all ingredients. Pour into paper lined cupcake pans.
Fill 2/3 full of batter. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Put pie filling or preserves on top.
Chill.
Makes about 22.

title: reunion casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: sugar-free sweet pickles
directions: Open pickles and drain.
