Empty the sweetener on top of the pickle slices and pour the tarragon over the sweetener.
Do not heat anything.
Shake jar several times after you have tightened the lid firmly.
Then turn the bottle upside down to help the sweetener through the pickles.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook noodles according to package.
While noodles are cooking, beat yolks lightly with a fork and add to cream.
Melt butter.

title: smoked sausage patio packets
directions: You will also need heavy-duty foil, cut into 4 large pieces.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli in small amount of boiling water and drain off excess when done.
Pour milk into small saucepan; bring to boil.
Cook until lukewarm.
Mix eggs with salt and nutmeg.
Add milk and cheese, beating constantly. Pour into grated baking dish; add broccoli.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Must be served hot.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix the ingredients well.
Pour into dish and chill.

title: scones
directions: Mix
flour,
baking
powder,
salt
and
sugar.
Cut in butter.
Add raisins and milk.
Fold in one stiffly beaten egg white.
Turn onto floured board and roll about 1/2-inch thick. Beat egg yolk and add 1 teaspoon water.
Brush over top.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes until golden brown.

title: ham and spinach pie
directions: Cook and drain spinach according to package directions. Combine with next 8 ingredients.
Pour mixture into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Pie is done when tester inserted in center comes out clean.

title: buttermilk dressing
directions: Beat buttermilk and mayonnaise until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
This keeps well in the refrigerator for several weeks.

title: old-fashion pinto beans
directions: Sort and wash beans; soak overnight in large pot.
Rinse and refill covering beans.
Add ham bones and salt.
Let beans come to a boil.
Turn to medium heat and simmer for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add hot water if needed and water boils down. Beans will make own thickness.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat with bacon, onions, cheese, pepper, spaghetti seasoning and garlic salt.
Drain fat from meat and add 1 package spaghetti sauce mix and 1 can tomato paste.
Add water to desired thickness.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease bottom only of loaf pans.
Mix shortening and sugar in a large bowl.
Add eggs, pumpkin and water.
Blend in flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon and cloves.
Stir in nuts and raisins.

title: mexican salad
directions: Use deep casserole dish.
Shred lettuce.
Grate the cheese and have the beans chilled and drained.
Dice tomatoes.
Layer these ingredients.
Pour Catalina dressing over these ingredients.
Add the chilled beans over the ingredients.
Chill 30 minutes.
Add crushed Fritos before serving.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: mulled apple cider
directions: Boil all ingredients together for 5 minutes.
Add 4 quarts orange juice and butter.
Enjoy.

title: fanny farmer fudge
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients for 5 minutes in rolling boil. Remove from heat.
Then add Hershey candy bar, chocolate chips and Marshmallow Creme.
Mix all together until smooth.
Put in large 10 x 15-inch pan, that has been buttered.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine nuts, sugar, salt and syrup in a 4-cup glass measuring cup.
Stir well.
Cook on Full power for 3 minutes and 30 seconds. Stir; cook another 3 minutes and 30 seconds on Full power.
Stir. Add butter and vanilla and cook another 30 seconds to 1 minute on Full power.
Remove and add soda; stir.
Immediately pour into greased cookie sheet, allow to cool and break into pieces for serving.

title: great grandma's sugar cookies
directions: In large bowl, mix margarine or butter, sugar, eggs and almond extract.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix in flour mixture until smooth.
Chill 1 hour. Roll on floured board to 1/8-inch thick.
Cut with floured cutters. Bake on greased sheet in preheated 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes, or until pale brown.
Remove to wire racks to cool and ice.

title: hot rolls
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Heat milk to lukewarm, combine with sugar, oil, egg, salt and yeast mixture. Stir in flour gradually.
Knead by stirring smooth.
Let rise in bowl until double in bulk, punch down, roll out and shape in desired size, let rise and bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding as directed; set aside. In a 12 x 6-inch glass dish, put vanilla wafers in bottom and add pudding. Cut and slice bananas and place them all over pudding. Put Cool Whip on top. Crush about 6 vanilla wafers and sprinkle them on top.

title: dill-glazed whitefish
directions: Fry fillets in oil until tender and flaky.
Remove to serving platter and keep hot.

title: fig cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into lightly greased loaf pan. Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: coconut caramel pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in top of double boiler. Add milk and egg yolks, mixing well.
Place over rapidly boiling water and cook 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from fire, but allow to remain over hot water.
Caramelize sugar by placing 1/3 cup sugar in iron skillet over medium flame and stirring constantly until melted and straw colored. Add at once to thickened mixture. Add butter and vanilla.
Garnish pie with a ring of whipped cream and sprinkle cream with coconut.

title: christmas butter cookies
directions: Rub shortening in flour; add sugar and egg yolks.
Mix until a smooth dough. Roll out thick.
Cut and bake in a hot oven until brown at 425° for 15 minutes.
In some ovens bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes to prevent burning.

title: clam chowder
directions: Dissolve bouillon in hot water.
Fry bacon.
Use bacon grease and add onion, butter and flour.
Stir milk into bouillon mix, then slowly add bacon, onion, butter and flour mixture.
Add chopped up bacon, clams and broccoli and cauliflower mixture. Simmer and cook for 1/2 hour.

title: steak with onions and mushrooms
directions: Use skillet. Turn heat on high.
Season steaks with garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Brown on each side.
Cook to desired type (rare, medium, well done, etc.).
Chop onion and put it in skillet with mushrooms.
Simmer for about 30 minutes (15 minutes on each side).

title: lemon and mint chicken breasts(a fast, delicious and nutritional main dish.)
directions: Marinate chicken for 1 hour in refrigerator with 1 cup of lemon juice.
Drain and pat dry.
In large skillet, heat butter or vegetable oil over medium heat.
Add chicken breasts and cook 6 to 8 minutes on each side or until done.
Remove breasts; keep warm. In skillet, add 1/4 cup of lemon juice, 1 drop of lemon oil (or 2 to taste) and mint leaves.
Warm juices slowly.
Serve chicken breasts with lemon juice dressing and grated lemon peel to garnish. Serves six.

title: light christmas cake
directions: Prepare 2 loaf pans by lining with foil.
Cream the butter. Add sugar gradually; beat until creamy.
Add almond flavor.
Sift dry ingredients.
Prepare fruit and nuts by cutting in small pieces and coating with flour.
Now, beat eggs; add to first part. Add dry ingredients.
Alternate with fruit and nuts and juices, beating after each addition.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake for 2 1/2 to 3 hours in a 275° oven.

title: zucchini yeast bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. In colander, alternate layers of grated zucchini and salt. Leave for 30 minutes, then squeeze out moisture with hands. Combine the yeast with 1/4 cup of lukewarm water. Stir and leave for 15 minutes to dissolve the yeast. Place zucchini, yeast and flour in a bowl. Stir together and add just enough of the remaining water to obtain a rough dough. Transfer to a floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic. Return the dough to the bowl; cover with a plastic bag. Leave to rise in a warm place until doubled in volume, about 1 1/2 hours. Grease a baking sheet. Punch down the risen dough with your fist and knead into a tapered cylinder. Place on the baking sheet. Cover and leave to rise in a warm place and let double in volume, about 45 minutes. Brush with oil and bake until golden, 45 minutes. Cool on rack.

title: ham rolls
directions: Do not separate rolls.
Slice top from rolls in one piece. Place bottoms in baking pan.
Layer ham and cheese on rolls. Replace tops.
Combine margarine, poppy seed, mustard, Worcestershire and onion flakes in measuring cup.
Mix well. Drizzle over rolls.
Refrigerate until margarine is firm or overnight.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake, covered with foil, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cut into desired-size pieces.
Serve hot or cold.

title: strawberry jam(tomato)
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients 20 minutes, then stir in Jell-O.
Put in jars and let set 2 to 3 days in refrigerator.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix bread mixes together and cook as directed.
Let cool. Crumble.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Add salt and pepper, if desired.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes.
Add other ingredients.
Stir well.
Cook by spoonful in heavy frying pan in hot cooking oil.
Serves 6.

title: onion burgers
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet.
Drain.
Add flour.
Stir well. Add the soup and simmer about 10 minutes.
Serve over buns.
This is similar to Sloppy Joes, it is all my children's favorite.

title: vanilla ice cream(freezer)
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar gradually, beating until mixture thickens.
Add remaining ingredients; mix thoroughly. Freeze in ice cream freezer.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: pan coating
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Mixture will be stiff.
Store in a lidded jar in the refrigerator. Coat pans with this mixture. Do not use flour after coating.
This is used instead of greasing and flouring pans.
Mixture will keep quite sometime.

title: meat loaf
directions: Spray a 1 qt. cassorole dish, mix above ingredients together, and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: taco salad
directions: In a large serving bowl, combine lettuce, tomato, pepper and olives.
Mix taco sauce with hamburg.
Just before serving, mix hamburg mixture, chips and cheese with lettuce mixture.
Toss with French Catalina dressing.

title: baked lima beans(from 1975 edition)
directions: Cover beans with cold water; bring to a boil and cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain.
In large roasting pan, place layers of beans and bacon-sugar-onion mixture.
Add catsup and cold water almost to cover.
Bake for 4 hours at 325°.
Stir after 1 hour and add salt to taste.
Do not stir again.
Serves 25.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Bring to a boil and add cucumbers, pepper and onions.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Pour in jars and seal.

title: mrs. rhode's refrigerator rolls
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients. Cool.
Combine the yeast and lukewarm water and dissolve.
Add flour until dough can be handled.
Put in refrigerator.
In the morning work into muffin pans (3 walnut shaped balls in each cup).
Let rise until double. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: too easy punch
directions: Chill both ingredients.
Pour in punch bowl together.
Makes one punch bowl of punch.

title: corn relish
directions: Mix and cook 50 minutes.
Pack and seal hot.
Process in boiling water bath 10 minutes.

title: corn bread casserole
directions: Melt margarine in long baking dish.
Pour half into bowl with mixture of other ingredients.
Stir and pour into baking dish. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown and solid.

title: chicken cacciatore(alex's favorite)
directions: Coat chicken pieces with seasoned flour.
In a 12-inch skillet, brown chicken in oil.
Remove; drain on paper towels. Add onion and green and red pepper to skillet; cook until soft. Drain excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Return chicken to skillet.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spice chiffon cake
directions: In a large bowl, sift flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and spices.
Make well in center of mix. Put oil, egg yolks and water in well and beat with a spoon until smooth.

title: herb baked fish and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In 8 x 12-inch baking dish, combine hot bouillon, uncooked rice and seasonings.
Bake, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Top with broccoli, 1/2 can onions and Parmesan cheese. Place fillets diagonally down center of dish; sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Bake uncovered for 20 to 25 minutes (until fish flakes) and rice is done.
Top with Cheddar cheese and remaining onions.
Cook additional 3 to 5 minutes.

title: trail bologna
directions: Mix all ingredients together with your hands.
Divide into four rolls.
Put on wax paper, then wrap round rolls, shaping as you roll them up.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Take out of refrigerator; take off wax paper.
Bake in broiler pan for one hour at 350°.

title: jade green broccoli chinese-style
directions: Wash broccoli; cut off florets.
Peel stems and slice on a slant into 1/4 or 1/2-inch slices.
Mix cornstarch, 1/2 cup of water or chicken broth and soy sauce in small bowl.
Heat wok or frying pan on high.
Add 3 tablespoons of oil, 1/4 teaspoon of salt, garlic, sugar, broccoli and mushrooms.
Stir quickly 2 to 3 minutes.
Add water mixture; lower heat and cook, covered, for 5 to 6 minutes.
Uncover and add oyster sauce.
Stir and serve.

title: ham and black-eyed pea soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, bring 4 cups water and black-eyed peas or navy beans to boiling.
Boil, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Drain and rinse.
In a 4-quart slow cooker, combine broth, the water, ham, carrots, celery, onion, sage, thyme and red pepper.
Stir in drained peas or beans.
Cover; cook on low heat setting for 11 to 12 hours or on high heat setting for 4 1/2 to 5 1/2 hours.

title: mexican layered dip
directions: Spread refried beans into bottom of large plate.
Slice avocado and remove pit.
Scoop out avocado, add mayonnaise and lemon juice to avocado.
This will make guacamole.
Spread sour cream over guacamole.
Spread cheese over sour cream.
Garnish with tomatoes and onions.
Eat with nacho chips.

title: lime pie supreme
directions: Separate the eggs and beat the egg whites until stiff.
Mix egg yolks, milk, lime juice and food coloring.
Fold in beaten egg whites and pour into crust.
Bake for 10 minutes in 250° oven. Cool and top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mexican corn dish
directions: Melt butter in a large baking pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour into baking dish.
Bake at 375° until golden brown (45 minutes).

title: chocolate chip cheese cake brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut frozen dough into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan with 1/2 of the dough to form crust.
Bake 10 minutes.
Beat cream cheese, egg, sugar and vanilla with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Spread over crust.
Top with remaining dough.
Bake 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Refrigerate.
Makes 18.

title: see sure shrimp
directions: Bring 6 quarts of water to a boil.
Add all ingredients except shrimp.
Bring back to a boil.
Add shrimp.
Boil 10 minutes or until shrimp turn pink.
Remove shrimp from pot and put in container.
Pour juice from pot over shrimp to cover.
Refrigerate in juice until cold.
Before serving, remove shrimp from juice and place on serving platter.
Serve with cocktail sauce.

title: howard's no-fat new york cheesecake
directions: Place rack in middle of oven and preheat to 300°.
Spray 9-inch spring-form pan with cooking spray.
Line bottom with parchment or waxed paper ring and place in pan.
Spray bottom of pan.
Process graham crackers and sprinkle in bottom of pan.
Place cottage cheese in strainer and gently push water out.
Put cottage cheese into processor for 2 minutes until real creamy.
Add cream cheese, sugar, flour, sour cream and egg whites to processor for 30 seconds.
Add vanilla and lemon zest.
Pour into spring-form pan; bake for 70 to 80 minutes or until top is set but center is a tiny bit wobbly when side of pan is tapped.
Turn off oven but leave cake in for 30 more minutes.
Put cake on cooling rack and run a knife around the edge.
Cool for 3 hours.
Refrigerate 3 hours covered.
Cover top with cherry pie filling.

title: patio salad
directions: Add frozen peas and salt to boiling water; boil 2 minutes. Add rice; cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in mayonnaise, pickles, onions and pepper.
Mix lightly with fork and chill.
Before serving, add ham and cheese.
Mix lightly. Serve on crisp greens; garnish with tomatoes, olives and carrot strips.

title: garlic potatoes
directions: Cover potatoes with water in a pan and bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat. Simmer about 20 minutes until tender. Cool.

title: potato fluff
directions: Combine potatoes, milk, salt, pepper and butter.
Beat until fluffy.
Stir in cheese and egg yolks.
Fold in egg whites.

title: peanut butter cookies(quick and oh-so easy)
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Roll into balls.

title: fire station casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions, stirring until meat crumbles. In a saucepan, stir and heat soup, milk and chiles. Cut tortillas into 1 inch squares. In a baking dish, layer tortillas, cooked meat, soup mixture and grated cheese; repeat layers, topping with grated cheese. Bake at 325° for 20-30 minutes.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions, omitting salt; drain thoroughly.
Place broccoli cuts in 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Stir together soup and grated cheese.
Add milk, mayonnaise and beaten egg to soup mix.
Pour over broccoli in baking dish.
Combine bread crumbs and melted butter.
Sprinkle over soup mixture.
Bake in moderate (350°) oven for 45 minutes, until crumbs are lightly brown.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Mix until well blended.
Spoon in diced strawberries.
Pour mixture into the 2 graham cracker pie crusts.

title: elegant stuffed chicken
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before serving, prepare stuffing.
Melt butter over medium heat, add zucchini and cook until tender, about 2 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat.

title: monkey bread
directions: Coat tube pan with Pam.
About 8 hours before serving (night before), put frozen rolls in tube pan.
Melt butter and pour over rolls.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over rolls.
Spread pecans and then pudding over rolls.
Spray Pam on waxed paper or Saran Wrap and place loosely over tube pan.
Leave at room temperature.

title: drizzlin, droolin, hot fudge sauce for ice cream
directions: Put all in a heavy saucepan (except the pecans and vanilla). Stir over low heat until chocolate melts.
Boil 7 to 10 minutes. Add pecans and vanilla.
Pour while warm over dishes of vanilla ice cream.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and gradually add sugar until light and fluffy. Add well beaten eggs.
Sift flour before measuring.
Add to it the spices and salt.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add it and the flour mixture alternately to the sugar, butter and egg mixture. Beat after each addition.
Lightly dredge the fruit and nuts with extra flour.
Stir into mixture.
Add jam and pour into 2 (9-inch) greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: sugarplums
directions: Chop all fruit and nuts in food grinder, using coarse blade. Shape mixture in 1 inch balls and roll in sugar.
Let dry on waxed paper overnight.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes 72 balls; 50 calories each.

title: brunswick stew(50 gallons)
directions: Have beef, chicken and pork precooked, deboned and pulled apart.
Save all water.
Put potatoes, onions and meat water in large black pot.
Cook until done.
Add corn and lima beans; continue to cook.
Add all meats.
Cook some more.
Add tomatoes last and continue to cook until very thick.
You must stir constantly or it will burn.
Add salt, pepper and paprika to taste.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk, vanilla, vinegar, sugar and butter; beat.
Add dry ingredients.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: anise cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add 1 beaten egg and the cream. Mix in the remaining dry ingredients and add enough flour to be able to roll. Cut out the cookies and bake at 350°.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: zucchini pizza
directions: Cook zucchini and onion in margarine until tender.
Add seasonings; cook about 5 minutes.
Cool.

title: vegetable quiche
directions: Pour the creamed mixture into a large bowl and add the drained vegetables.
Mix lightly and add 3/4 teaspoon Italian seasoning or other if preferred.
Gently toss in 1 cup grated Cheddar cheese. Batter should be consistency of a cake batter.
If too thin, add more Bisquick before folding in the grated cheese.
Other cheeses may be used if desired.
Pour batter into a large well-greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika and parsley flakes.
Bake at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes.
This freezes very good.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Remove spices. Serve warm or hot.
Leftovers may be stored in refrigerator and reheated.

title: festive fruit trifle
directions: Thaw frozen strawberries as label directs.
Drain peaches. Cut pound cake lengthwise in half.
Cut each half crosswise into 1/2-inch thick slices.

title: microwave s'mores
directions: Top 4 graham crackers with 1/2 candy bar and 1 marshmallow. Cover with remaining graham crackers.
Wrap individually in a paper towel.
Arrange cookies on glass try of microwave with the seam side of paper towel down.
Time cook on Full power or High (power level 10) for 2 minutes.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Unwrap. Serve.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Mix together oil and sugar.
Add half of dry ingredients.
Mix well and beat in carrots, pineapple and nuts.
Add vanilla and rest of dry ingredients.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat until well blended after each addition.

title: coconut sour cream cake
directions: Prepare yellow cake mix as directed.
Bake and cool.
Split layers into four pieces.
Mix sugar, sour cream and coconut; chill.
Put 1/2 of mixture between layers.
To the other 1/2 of mixture, add whipped topping and ice sides and top of cake.
Put in a tight container and refrigerate for 3 days before cutting.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Grease baking sheet and cover with parchment paper.
Set oven to 325°.
Whisk egg whites until very stiff.
Fold in sugar and coconut.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on parchment covered baking sheets. Bake 15 minutes at 325°.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Add oil, celery seed, onion and celery.
Bring vinegar and sugar to boil; pour over mixture and stir.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in 3 layers for about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot soup
directions: Melt butter in large pan over low heat.
Stir in onion, carrot, thyme, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook 10 minutes.
Add broth and rice.
Simmer until rice is tender 40 to 50 minutes. Put mixture in blender a little at a time.
Blend until smooth. Serves 8.

title: old world manicotti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray 13 x 9 pan with cooking spray. Cook pasta; drain and rinse. In medium bowl, mix 3 cups Mozzarella with Ricotta and fresh basil. With a teaspoon, stuff pasta shells with the cheese mixture. Spoon 2 cups spaghetti sauce into prepared baking pan. Arrange stuffed pasta over sauce. Pour remaining spaghetti sauce over the top of the shells. Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella. Bake for 15 minutes, then remove from oven and sprinkle with Parmesan. Bake for 10 minutes longer.

title: scrumptious sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream the margarine. Add sugar, one cup at a time, mixing after each. Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each.
Add flavorings.
Sift flour, salt and soda. Add to mixture alternately with sour cream.
Pour into greased and floured pan. Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: cornbread sticks
directions: Heat 2 cornbread stick pans which have been greased generously.
Mix batter and pour into very hot pans.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Do not stir rice while cooking.
Drain.
Do not rinse rice.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Serve on a bed of lettuce. Can also be used as a dip, sandwich spread or on crackers.

title: hot ham and cheese sandwiches
directions: Mix last 5 ingredients together.
Spread this mixture on both sides of buns.
Layer ham and cheese on buns.
Wrap individually in foil.
Store in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: john's black-eyed peas
directions: Cook bacon in water for 30 minutes, then add peas and rice. Simmer until peas are soft.
Then add coconut and simmer on lowest heat for 15 minutes.
Lift out bacon and slice.
Drain peas and rice and pop into the oven for a few minutes to dry until rice is fluffy.
Serve with bacon sliced on top.
(You can fry the bacon until crispy and cut into 1-inch lengths.)

title: praline carrots
directions: Cook and drain carrots.
Mix butter sprinkles according to directions on package.
Add other ingredients and pour over carrots.
Bring to a slow boil.
Simmer 5 minutes and serve.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Brown sausage, stirring as needed.
Line a 13 x 9-inch buttered dish with rolls (mash down).
Sprinkle sausage and cheese.
Combine other ingredients and pour over top.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: zucchini puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Heat Fry Daddy or another type of deep fryer.
Drop by teaspoonful into hot grease.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain excess grease on paper towels.
Serve plain or dip in tomato sauce topped with Parmesan cheese.

title: rich fruit cake
directions: Soak fruit in grape juice overnight.
Cream butter; add sugar, egg yolks, flour, spices, jelly, chocolate, fruit and nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into tube pans that have been greased and lined with brown paper.
Bake in a slow 225° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Makes approximately 14 pounds.

title: chicken breast imperial
directions: Wrap each chicken breast half in chipped beef, then secure each with a bacon strip.
Arrange in baking dish and cover with the soup and sour cream mixture.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook noodles according to package instructions.
Mix the seasonings with the melted butter.
Toss with the warm noodles. Mix in cream and cheeses; stir gently until Swiss cheese is melted and noodles are coated.
Saute mushrooms with 2 tablespoons of butter and garlic salt to taste.
Garnish fettuccine with mushrooms and serve immediately.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions and carrots.
Mix sour cream and soup.
Add onion, carrots and chicken.
Place broccoli in pan with croutons. Pour mix over broccoli and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is good and melted.

title: stir-fried chicken and broccoli with sun-dried tomatoes
directions: In wok, heat 1 1/2 tablespoons olive oil over high
heat until hot, swirling to coat sides of pan.
Add chicken and stir-fry meat throughout but juicy, about 3 minutes.
Remove to plate.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Pour boiling mixture over okra and cover with clean new lids and screw on rings.
Jars should seal on their own within 12 hours.
Should any jars fail to seal, they should be stored in the refrigerator.

title: fiesta dip
directions: Using a casserole dish, spread the can of refried beans in bottom of the dish.
Next, mash together the next 5 ingredients in a small bowl.
Pour over beans.
Spread sour cream evenly over avocado sauce, then sprinkle with cheese, then olives.
Top with tomatoes.

title: carrot cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream margarine and sugar.
Beat in egg whites.
Stir in pineapple and vanilla.
Stir together flours, cinnamon and soda.
Stir into liquid ingredients and beat well. Fold in carrots and nuts.
Pour into a nonstick sprayed 9 x 13-inch baking pan or Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.

title: banana bread(from the family of randi saunders)
directions: Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: rhubarb jelly
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Let boil for 10 minutes.
Remove from fire and add strawberry Jell-O.
Seal immediately in hot pint jars.

title: shannon's pot roast
directions: In 8-quart Dutch oven, over medium-high heat, in hot oil, cook roast until well browned on all sides.
Stir in salt, pepper and 3 cups water over high heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to medium-low, cover and simmer 2 1/4 hours.
Add potatoes, carrots and onions; over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce to medium-low heat. Cook, covered, 45 minutes or until meat and vegetables are tender. Arrange meat and potatoes on a platter.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Bring beans to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat.
Cook at least 1 hour until tender.
Saute onions and peppers until tender.
Add spices.
Mix well.
Transfer to beans.
Add tomato paste and tomatoes and simmer another one-half hour.
Season to taste. Serve.
Yields about 2 quarts.

title: hearty beef stew
directions: Heat oil in heavy saucepan.
Add stewing beef and brown on all sides.
Add water and dash of salt.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer about 1 hour.
Cool and skim off hardened fat.
Return to heat and add onion, carrot and potato.
Cook 30 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Mix flour and 1/2 cup cold water by shaking in a small jar.
Add to stew.
Stir until it has boiled for 1 minute and is thickened.
Let simmer until ready to eat. Serves 1.

title: granny's hamburger pie
directions: Prepare cornbread as directed; set aside.
Into iron skillet, cook hamburger and diced onion; drain, add mixed vegetables and corn.
Mix in ketchup; spread thin layer of cornbread on top of mixture.
Bake at 325° until golden brown.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix beaten eggs, pumpkin, sugar, milk and spices until smooth. Pour in a 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle yellow cake mix over top. Sprinkle chopped nuts over cake mix. Drizzle melted butter on top. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. If using a metal pan, bake 10 minutes longer. Bake until tests done. Let cool and store in refrigerator until serving time. Serve with whipped topping.

title: homemade grilled cheese
directions: Put all the cheeses and ham on the bread.
Put butter in the frying pan.
Place the grilled cheese in the frying pan.
Fry until golden brown and until the cheese has melted.

title: tuna ball
directions: Drain tuna.
Flake with fork.
Soften cream cheese. Form ball. Refrigerate as long as possible.
Cover with parsley flakes. Serve with favorite crackers.

title: shrimp and crab casserole
directions: Saute vegetables in butter and add remaining ingredients.
Set oven to 325° and cook, covered, for 1 hour.
Remove cover and cover with mild grated cheese and return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: golden champagne punch
directions: Mix all fruit juices and sugar.
Stir to dissolve sugar. Cover and chill in refrigerator for several hours.

title: fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in a heavy 2 1/2-quart saucepan; bring to a full, rolling boil, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat; stir in chocolate pieces until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme and vanilla; beat until well blended.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: chicken and dried beef
directions: Place dried beef on the bottom of shallow baking pan.
Cut breast in half and wrap each piece in bacon.
Place wrapped chicken pieces in pan on top of dried beef.
Mix sour cream and soup.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 300°
for 2 1/2 hours.
Uncover and bake 1/2 hour longer.
Serves 8.

title: busy day meatballs
directions: Combine and form into balls.
Place in a baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 1/2 hour. Make sauce below.

title: hearty italian soup
directions: Brown turkey, peppers and onion; drain fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients except macaroni and cheese.
Cover and cook 25 minutes.
Add macaroni and cook 15 minutes more.
If desired, top with cheese.

title: easiest ever pot roast
directions: Place beef in a Dutch oven.
Sprinkle soup mix, soup and water over beef.
Cover tightly.
Bake 3 hours at 325°.
Let sit for 15 minutes before serving.

title: spam luncheon loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 375°.

title: easy chicken and rice
directions: Butter a 15 x 10-inch roasting pan.
Mix together all 3 soups and water in a large bowl.
Add the oil, salt and pepper; mix well.
Pour in the pan.
Add uncooked rice; mix in.
Put chicken on top of the soup and rice mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 375° or until chicken is fully cooked.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut up a bowl of broccoli using tender stems.

title: oatmeal cookies(healthy style)
directions: Drain raisins. Blend dry ingredients. Stir in remaining ingredients. Drop on oiled cookie sheet and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 325°. Yields 24 small cookies.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: In saucepan, melt butter.
Add to cracker crumbs and sugar. Mix thoroughly and press into pie pan.

title: crispie speckled candy eggs
directions: Combine Marshmallow Creme, peanut butter and butter.
Mix well until well blended.
Add cereal and candies; mix well.
With greased fingers, shape to form 1 1/4-inch balls, then form into egg shapes.
Place in small baking muffin cups.
Chill for 30 minutes to set.
Store tightly covered in refrigerator or cool, dry place.
Makes 1 1/2 to 2 dozen eggs.
Be sure to chop M&M's, as they mix better.

title: great squash relish
directions: Mix onions and squash.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup salt; set aside for 1 hour.
Drain off liquid.
Mix vinegar, sugar, celery seed, mustard seed and pepper in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Add squash and onion; bring back to boil.
Put in clean jars and seal with hot lid.

title: corn relish
directions: Combine all ingredients except corn in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 12 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add corn and bring again to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 5 minutes, or until corn is just tender.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes 2 cups.

title: all-day-long crockpot beef
directions: Cut beef roast into serving sized portions.
Use more beef if you need more that 6 servings.
Brown beef in a bit of vegetable oil, although you can skip this step if you're rushed for time. Slice onion and separate into rings.
Dice the peeled carrots, dice the celery and slice the peppers into thin strips or circles. Place these into bottom of the Crockpot.
Sprinkle the beef pieces with fresh ground black pepper, minced garlic and the onion soup mix.
Place on top of the vegetables.
Mix the steak sauce and worcestershire sauce in a small bowl with about 1/2 cup water and 1/2 cup tomato juice.
Pour this over the meat.
Turn the crockpot to high for 30 minutes, or if you're in a hurry, skip this step. Turn to low cover and let cook for 7 - 9 hours.
Keep the crockpot covered as much as possible through out cooking time.
When ready to serve, dip meat and vegetables out with a slotted spoon, use the liquid in the crockpot as is or turn the crockpot to high and thicken liquid with a little flour or cornstarch.

title: vegetable-cheese casserole
directions: Cook all vegetables half the time stated on package; drain. Place in casserole dish.
Heat and blend soup and cheese.
Pour over veggies and mix.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Top with onion rings during the last 5 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: chocolate poundcake
directions: Start heating oven to 350°.
Line with wax paper bottom of a 3 1/2-inch deep 9-inch tube pan.
Into large bowl sift flour, cream of tartar, soda, salt and sugar.
Drop in shortening; pour in milk and vanilla.
With electric mixer at low speed to medium speed, beat 2 minutes, scraping bowl and beaters as needed.
Add eggs, egg yolk and chocolate; beat 1 minute.
Turn into pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: easy corn chowder
directions: Combine all together and simmer 20 minutes.

title: chocolate pudding brownies
directions: Cook pudding to directions on box.
Mix dry cake mix into this and beat 2 minutes.
Pour into a greased pan.
Top with nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Good.
Good. Good.

title: lite chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Spray pie pan with nonfat nonstick cooking spray and set aside.
Mix the first three ingredients well and press into the bottom and up the sides of the pie pan.
Set aside. Mix the pudding mixes and milk until thick.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill and top with cool whip.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Combine ingredients, adding flour and milk.
Fold berries and 1/4 cup flour.
Add to mixture.
Spread in a greased pan.

title: wedding soup
directions: Cook escarole or endive slightly.
Heat chicken broth or stock.
Add greens.
Add celery, carrots and meatballs.
Add cooked chicken.
Spread beaten egg over top.
Add acini de pepe macaroni.
Simmer 3 to 4 hours.
Serves 12.

title: oven stew
directions: Have stew meat cut in small pieces.
Take sausage out of skins and put little pieces over top of meat which you have put in roasting pan.
Put vegetables over that.
Add vegetable juice, onion soup mix and tapioca.
Put lid on; stir once.
If too thick more juice may be added.
Oven Temperature:
Cooking Time: 3 hours.

title: foolproof divinity
directions: Place marshmallow cream in large glass bowl; set aside.
Put sugar and water in medium saucepan over high heat; bring to a boil for 3 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Pour over marshmallow cream and mix well.
Stir in nuts and vanilla; mix well. Pour into 9-inch square pan.
Let set until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: butterscotch squares
directions: Cook oleo and sugar together until smooth and well blended. Cool to lukewarm. Add unbeaten egg and beat well.
Add flour, baking powder, then vanilla and nuts.
Spread in 9 x 9-inch pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: cherry bar
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Then add all remaining ingredients except cherry pie filling.
Mix well. Put half of the batter in a large greased and floured cookie sheet with edges. Add cherry pie filling.
Top with the rest of the batter.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Top with a glaze while hot.

title: seafood divan
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: skillet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Bake at 350° in an iron skillet lightly sprayed with Pam.
Bake until done.

title: crunchy beef bake casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Cook ground meat and drain.
Combine all ingredients, except French fried onions.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover and top with onions; bake 5 minutes more.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Roll sugar cookie dough in pizza pan.
Bake top.
When cool, spread with softened cream cheese.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Top with assorted fruits.
Add Cool Whip and pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix together the brown sugar, margarine, syrup and salt and bring to a boil over low heat. Boil 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add the vanilla and soda (will cause mixture to foam). Stir quickly and well.
Pour over popped corn and stir. Bake in a 225° oven for 1 hour or microwave for 9 minutes, stirring every 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir it.

title: children's messy hands fudge
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients with hands.
Add the nuts after other ingredients are mixed.

title: elegant beef tenderloin
directions: Place tenderloin in a lightly greased shallow roasting pan; sprinkle with garlic salt.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Combine wine, soy sauce, butter and lemon pepper seasoning in a small; saucepan.
Cook until mixture is thoroughly heated.
Pour over tenderloin.
Bake an additional 30 to 40 minutes, or until tenderloin registers 140° (rare) or 150° (medium rare).
Baste with pan drippings.

title: oreo creme delight
directions: Put milk into a medium-size bowl. Dip several Oreos at a time into the bowl of milk for at least 5 seconds. Alternately layer Oreos and Cool Whip in a 13 x 9 glass dish. Cover and place in freezer until frozen. Makes a great Sunday afternoon dessert!

title: carrot salad
directions: Peel.
Slice carrots and boil in salted water until tender. Slice onions and peppers.
Place in casserole dish; add carrots. Boil soup, oil, vinegar and sugar for 5 minutes.
Pour over other ingredients.
Store in refrigerator.

title: christmas cake
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, flour, baking powder and lemon extract.
Mix dates, cherries and pecans with 1 cup sifted flour and add.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Makes a large cake.

title: bok choy
directions: Chop cabbage and onion.
Mix together. Cover and set aside. Break noodles in package. Saute noodles, sesame seed and almonds in butter or margarine until light brown.
Cool on absorbent paper. Bring last 4 ingredients to a boil and cool. Store 3 mixtures separately in refrigerator.
Combine them immediately before serving.

title: cranberry meringue pie
directions: In medium saucepan, cook cranberries in water, stirring until cranberries pop.
Add raisins.
Combine 1 3/4 cups sugar and cornstarch; add to cranberry mixture.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Stir in nuts and margarine until margarine melts; cool.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Gradually add 6 tablespoons sugar and continue beating until stiff peaks form.
Turn cooled filling into baked pie shell.
Spread meringue over filling, sealing to edge.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: edith's pound cake
directions: Blend Crisco, margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder together; add alternately with milk.
Add flavorings and food coloring last; blend well.
Pour into a well-greased and floured tube pan; bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: turtles cookies
directions: Sift flour with soda and salt; cream butter.
Add brown sugar. Cream well in egg and egg yolk, vanilla and maple extract.
Add dry ingredients gradually; mix well and chill.
Arrange pecan halves in groups of 5 on greased cookie sheet to resemble head and legs of a turtle.
Shape dough by teaspoon into ball.
Dip bottom into egg white; press lightly onto nuts so tips will show when baked.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 13 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: canadian cheese soup
directions: Cook onions in butter until tender but not brown.
Blend in flour; slowly add hot broth, stirring constantly.
Add milk, carrots, celery, salt and pepper.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture thickens and is bubbly.
Reduce heat; add cheese. Stir to melt cheese.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Yields 8 one-cup servings.

title: dill dip
directions: Chill and serve with chips or Doritos.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in loaf pan.
Cover with 2 strips bacon.
Pour over all one 8 ounce can tomato sauce.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix pineapple and pie filling.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread dry cake mix on top.
Slice margarine in pats; dot the top of dry mix.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: mints
directions: Mix sugar and butter; blend well. Add oil and mix well. Add color to water, then add to mixture (should be like pie crust dough; if not, add more sugar). Can be rolled and cut or used in cookie molds.

title: shellroni and tuna fish salad
directions: Cook shellroni until tender, then chill by running cold water over it. Flake tuna. Blend all ingredients with mayonnaise.

title: peach pound cake
directions: cream butter and sugar until fluffy, Add eggs beaten well, Beat in extracts. Add flour, soda, and salt. Then the sour cream. Mix good. Add the peaches. Pour into a sprayed pan and floured, a bundt pan Bake at 350 degrees for 60-65 minutes. Cool good, then remove from pan and dust with powdered sugar.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar in mixing bowl.
Combine Coke, butter and cocoa in saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Add to flour.
Stir in eggs, buttermilk, soda, vanilla and marshmallows.
Bake in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Boil first four ingredients 6 minutes stirring constantly.
Put chocolate bits and Marshmallow Creme in large bowl.
Pour boiling syrup over stuff in bowl.
Beat until chocolate bits are melted. Pour in pan.
Let stand for a few hours.

title: potato candy
directions: Put potatoes in a bowl. Add sugar.
Mix until thick.
Roll out with a rolling pin. Spread some peanut butter over this and roll up like a log. Refrigerate overnight or until it is chilled completely. Slice into 1-inch pieces.

title: green pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate before serving.

title: cherry dream squares
directions: Combine cake mix plus 6 tablespoons butter and 1 cup oats. Mix.
Reserve 1 cup for topping.
Mix remaining crumbs plus egg and press in pan.
Pour filling over crust.
Add to remaining crumbs 1/4 cup oats, 2 tablespoons butter, nuts and brown sugar. Sprinkle on top and bake 30 to 40 minutes in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown together first 4 ingredients.
Drain grease.
Add onion and bell pepper.
Line baking dish with the corn tortillas.
Add meat mixture.
Over this pour remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, until bubbly on top.

title: apple bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add milk, egg, melted shortening and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add nuts and chopped apples. Stir together.
Bake in a well-greased bread pan at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes one loaf.

title: make ahead chicken casserole
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together in a large bowl.
Cover and place in refrigerator.
Remove 1 hour before baking.
Stir well and
spoon into casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Can be made one day ahead.

title: oreo ice cream cake
directions: Spread crushed Oreo cookies in the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch Tupperware pan. In a saucepan, melt butter and cocoa on medium heat. Add eggs; stir until eggs are cooked. (It will look stiff and lumpy.) Add powdered sugar into cocoa mixture and heat until it becomes soft. (It will look fudge like.) Pour over crushed Oreos, then chill until cooled. Slice ice cream in about 1-inch thick slices. Lay ice cream slices on top of cooled Oreos. Spread top with Cool Whip. Put in freezer.

title: chicken paprika
directions: Heat about half the butter and salad oil in Dutch oven.
Brown chicken, a few pieces at a time until golden on all sides.
Add more butter and oil as needed.
Remove chicken as it browns.
In Dutch oven, saute onion, carrots and celery for 5 minutes.
Add paprika; cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat, stir in flour, catsup, salt and pepper.
Gradually add chicken broth and bring to boiling.
Reduce heat, simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Add browned chicken, simmer covered 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove chicken and vegetables.
Stir in sour cream and heat gently.
Do not boil. Serve over noodles or rice.

title: artichoke squares
directions: Saute onion and garlic in bacon drippings.
Add to the rest of the ingredients which have been combined together.
Put into a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until set.
Cut into squares.
Serve hot or cold.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Scrape carrots and cut into strips 1/4-inch thick and about 1 1/2-inches long.
Place strips in a buttered casserole dish and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Dot with brown sugar and butter. Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 1 1/2 hours.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and cook sweet potatoes until tender; drain.
Melt butter and add brown sugar.
Blend together.

title: egg beater omelet
directions: Spray Pam in nonstick skillet.
Pour out Egg Beaters; let brown a little bit.
Put tomato, green pepper and grated cheese on top.
When brown, fold omelet over halfway and finish browning. Remove from pan and put a tablespoon of salsa over omelet; add a dollop of sour cream and a dash of hot sauce.
Serves one.

title: chinese almond rice
directions: Brown sausage and remove from skillet.
Drain fat.
Chop all of the vegetables and cook until limp.
Prepare noodle soup with hot water.

title: raspberry twists
directions: Mix egg, milk, butter and sugar.
Add biscuit mix.
Stir to blend.
Knead 15 times on surface dusted with more biscuit mix. Roll dough out to 15 x 9-inch and spread with jam.
Fold in thirds and cut into 15 pieces.
Twist and press down on cookie sheet. Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
While warm, spread mixture of remaining ingredients on twists.

title: oatmeal raisin biscuits
directions: Preheat oven at 425°.
Combine flour, oats, sugar, baking powder, salt and soda in large bowl.
Stir in raisins.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in buttermilk just until dough holds together.
Knead dough on lightly floured surface about 10 times.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with 2-inch diameter round cutter.
Place biscuits 1-inch apart on buttered cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool slightly.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Serve with butter.

title: pumpernickel dip
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Make a "bowl" out of one loaf and one broken up to dip.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Mix salt, dry mustard, pepper, chili powder, paprika and sugar.
Sprinkle mixture on both sides of meat.
Combine tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce and water.
Pour over meat.
Cut onion on top of meat.
Bake at 350° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Cover pan with foil.

title: snowball salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip, sour cream, sugar and lemon juice together. Beat well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Chill overnight.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine fruit (cut in bite-size pieces) with drained pineapple.

title: choc-oat-chip cookies
directions: Beat margarine and sugars until creamy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt; mix well. Stir in oats, chocolate chips and nuts; mix well.
Drop by rounded measuring tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 10 minutes for a chewy cookie or 12 to 13 minutes for a crisp cookie.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet; remove to wire rack. Cool completely.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie tin with pastry.
Put in rhubarb.
Mix other ingredients and pour over.
Bake about 15 minutes at 400°, then reduce heat to 325° and bake about 40 minutes longer.

title: "after thanksgiving" turkey corn soup
directions: In 4-quart saucepan over medium heat, heat the corn, broth, turkey, potatoes and thyme to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in green vegetable, milk and pepper.
Heat through.
Yields approximately 8 cups.

title: plain cake
directions: Beat flour, sugar, Crisco, baking powder, salt and milk together for 2 minutes.
Add eggs, egg yolk and vanilla.
Bake about 1 hour at 350° in tube pan.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and beat until it loses its gloss.
Nuts are optional.

title: pumpkin waffles and cinnamon syrup
directions: Heat waffle iron.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In large bowl combine dry ingredients for waffles; blend well.
Add milk, pumpkin, oil and eggs; beat 1 minute at medium speed.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in hot waffle iron until golden brown and steaming stops.
Makes 12 waffles.
Freeze any leftovers and warm up in toaster.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips and margarine with peanut butter in a double boiler or microwave.
Pour mixture over cereal and stir gently until all cereal is covered.
Put powdered sugar in a clean brown paper bag (approximately 3 cups), then add cereal mixture and shake to coat cereal.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well, then fold in crabmeat, sprinkle more Cheddar cheese on mixture and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot or warm with crackers.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 7 x 11 x 2-inch oblong pan.
Combine with sugar, flour, baking powder and salt with milk to make batter.
If too stiff, add a little more milk.
Pour batter over butter.
Mix apples and raisins, then smooth over batter gently.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook until mixture forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat and add 2 tablespoons butter and 3 tablespoons peanut butter.
Beat on medium speed until it begins to set.
Pour into a buttered pan.
Cut when cooled.

title: day ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Beat all ingredients well; spoon into lightly greased casserole.
Refrigerate overnight and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Yields 6 servings.

title: cheese delights
directions: Mix well and make into a roll.
Place in fridge until firm and easier to handle.
Slice into thin biscuits.
Bake at 350° on greased pan 10 minutes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: In a large mixing bowl, dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water and add sugar and vinegar.
Cool to room temperature and add remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold, stirring occasionally to prevent vegetables coming to top.
(I have substituted evaporated skim milk for the cream to lower the fat content.)

title: mexican fudge
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Place cheese in pan and top with diced chilies.
In separate bowl, combine eggs, milk and flour.
Pour over top of chilies.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour.
Cut into squares and serve hot.

title: grandma mary's gravy
directions: Melt grease and add flour; brown.
Pour in milk; stir and add water to desired thickness.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix together well. Grease and flour a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: creamy creole pralines
directions: Put all the ingredients, except pecans, in 3-quart saucepan and cook for 20 minutes. After it has come to a boil, stir occasionally. Add the pecans and cook mixture until the liquid forms a soft ball when dropped into cold water. Stir well. Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper. Place a few sheets of newspaper underneath the wax paper.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar and Karo; microwave 4 minutes on Full power.
Add peanuts; stir.
Microwave 4 more minutes on Full power.
Add butter and vanilla.
Microwave an additional 1 minute.
Add soda and spread quickly on a buttered cookie sheet.
When edges begin to set, stretch peanut brittle.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix ingredients until well blended.

title: green beans in sour cream
directions: Wash beans and remove strings.
Cut green beans into 1-inch pieces.
Cook in a small amount of boiling water for 6 minutes or until tender.
Drain; transfer beans to a 2-quart casserole.
Set aside.
Saute onion and parsley in butter 2 minutes or until onion is tender.
Stir in sour cream, lemon rind, salt and pepper. Spoon sour cream mixture over beans.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over sour cream mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: arroz con picadillo(rice and puerto rican style ground beef)
directions: Chop the 1/2 green pepper, onion and garlic as fine as possible.
Place in skillet with 1 teaspoon vegetable oil at medium flame.
Stir-fry for 1 minute and add ground beef.
Add Adobo, olives and Sazon.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes at medium low flame. Add 1 small can of tomato sauce and cook for 10 minutes (same temperature).
Drain any excess fat and serve over white rice. "Buen Aprovecho!"

title: good morning company
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish with a layer of bacon and a thin layer of Swiss cheese. Break eggs over all. Drizzle cream over whites so yolks peek out.
Bake in a 450° oven for 10 minutes. Take out. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Return to oven for 10 minutes or until eggs are set. Cut in squares to serve.

title: broccoli with water chestnuts
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Mix with other ingredients and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° about 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: aunt millie's sour cream pound cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt together. Cream butter; add sugar.
When mixed, add 1 egg at a time; mix well between each.
Add flour, a little at a time, alternating with sour cream.
Add vanilla and almond.
Bake in buttered tube pan at 350° for 30 minutes, then at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: moussaka(greek dish)
directions: Make alternate layers of vegetables and meat.
Cover with the tomato paste mixed with a bit of water in a large baking pan. Cover with cream sauce made of margarine, flour and milk.
Add egg to cream sauce after sauce is thick.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: angel hash salad
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients together until thick, stirring constantly; cool.
Add fruit and nuts.
Add 1 cup of whipped cream. Serve.

title: easy seafood chowder
directions: Cook potato in small amount of water and add remaining ingredients.
Add 14 ounces of milk.
Heat until hot.
Serve.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt with a pastry blender. Combine egg, water and vinegar in small bowl.
Pour into flour mixture all at once.
Blend with a fork and forms a ball. Roll out with rolling pin.
Makes 2 (10-inch or 9-inch) pie crusts.

title: dixie pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in hot grease; sprinkle with salt and sage. Place in baking dish; top with apples.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Add flour to grease in skillet; blend.
Add water and vinegar; cook until thick.
Add raisins; pour over chops.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings.

title: bugs on a log
directions: Wash celery.
Cut into 3 sections.
Wash carrot, then grate. Mix peanut butter, dry milk and carrot in bowl.
Use knife to stuff celery with mixture.
Place raisins on top.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Wash and drain blueberries.
Put in the water in a saucepan. Cook easily until boiling.
Stir occasionally.
Add butter.
Mix dry ingredients; add to boiling mixture.
Boil gently for 7 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Good on shortcake, pancakes and vanilla ice cream.

title: decadent chocolate cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions, stirring in 1 cup chocolate chips.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until tests done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove and let cool completely.
Brush brandy over layers.
Allow to stand until brandy is absorbed.
Spread preserves in between layers.
Place remaining chips in top of double boiler.
Bring water to boil.
Reduce heat to low; cook until chocolate melts completely.
Remove from heat; stir in sour cream, blending well.
Spread on top layer of cake only.
Garnish top with mandarin orange sections.

title: sweet relish
directions: Chop apples (don't peel), peppers and onions together and pour boiling water over.
Let stand 10 minutes; drain well.
Combine sugar, salt, vinegar and water and cook all ingredients for 10 minutes.
Seal in jars.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Drain shrimp; crumble into bowl.
Add remaining ingredients. Chill.
Serve with chips.

title: pecan pie
directions: Have
a
fresh pastry shell.
Beat eggs; add Karo syrup (put flour
in
sugar),	vanilla, salt and butter.
Pour into shell and
put
pecans
on top.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat
to
and bake until a knife blade comes out clean.

title: nutty apple muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine the flour, baking soda, salt and nutmeg.
In another bowl, beat eggs, sugar and oil.
Stir in apples, nuts and coconut.
Stir into dry ingredients just until moistened.
Fill 18 greased muffin cups three-fourths full.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes before removing to a wire rack.
Yield: 1 1/2 dozen.

title: quick cinnamon crisps dessert
directions: Use raw tortilla dough.
Divide dough into 16 to 18 balls. Roll flat.
Cut into 2-inch wide strips.
Deep fry until brown. Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon mixture over hot strips.
Serve immediately with ice cold milk or hot coffee.

title: chocolate pie(no eggs)
directions: Mix together cocoa, flour and sugar.
Add a dash of salt.
Add milk.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Remove and add vanilla and margarine.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Makes 2 pies.
Cool.
Top with "No Cook Karo Frosting."

title: hot rolls
directions: Combine 2 cups flour, yeast, sugar and salt in large bowl. Stir well to blend.
Add oleo and hot tap water.
Beat with electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Scrape sides of bowl occasionally. Add eggs and 1 cup flour.
Beat with electric mixer for 1 or 2 minutes until thick and elastic.
Gradually stir in just enough remaining flour with wooden spoon to make a soft dough which leaves the side of bowl.
Turn out on a floured board.
Knead for 5 to 10 minutes or until dough is smooth and elastic.

title: strawberry spinach salad
directions: Combine sugar, mustard, salt and vinegar in blender. With machine running, pour in oil slow and steadily. Pulse in onion and poppy seeds. Chill until ready to serve. When ready to serve, toss spinach, berries and pecans with dressing. Serves 6 to 8.

title: pecan pie
directions: Prepare and roll out pastry.
Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry.
Trim pastry to 1/2-inch beyond edge of pie plate.
Flute edge.
Do not prick pastry.

title: plum bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Place batter in 1 large or 2 small greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serve with soft cream cheese.

title: alabama punch bowl cake
directions: Bake and divide cake into 4 parts.

Layer in a punch bowl: crumble cake (1/4), blueberry filling (1/2 can), Cool Whip, crumble cake (1/4), cherry pie filling (1/2 can), Cool Whip, crumble cake (1/4), blueberry filling (1/2 can), Cool Whip, sliced bananas, pineapple and juice, Cool Whip, crumble cake (1/4), cherry filling (1/2 can) and Cool Whip.

title: french onion soup
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, cook onions in margarine on medium-high heat for 10 to 12 minutes until onions are transparent and slightly caramelized.
Stir occasionally while onions cook.
Stir in flour and cook 1 minute; stir constantly.
Add salt and broth. Cover and cook 8 minutes.
Lightly sprinkle garlic powder to taste in soup and remove from heat.
Fill microwavable bowls with soup.
Add slice of bread and top with Swiss cheese.
Microwave on Medium-high until cheese melts.

title: mystery cookies
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into oblong greased pan.
Bake at 300° or 350°
for 45 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: jul-grot or risen-grot(christmas porridge)
directions: Scald rice with boiling water.
Melt butter; add rice and hot water.
Cook carefully until water disappears, about 10 minutes. Add salt, sugar and milk.
Cook in double boiler for at least 1 hour.
Serve with cold milk, sugar and cinnamon.
Also good served plain.

title: oriental shrimp salad
directions: Rinse bean sprouts in cold water and drain.
Combine first 6 ingredients and mix with Soy Mayonnaise.
Serves 8.

title: cranberry pumpkin bread
directions: In a large bowl mix together flour, sugar, baking soda, pumpkin pie spice, salt and baking powder.
In second bowl, stir together remaining ingredients until well mixed.
Add pumpkin mixture to flour mixture.
Stir until all ingredients are well moistened.
Pour batter into two 9 1/4 x 5 1/4 x 2-inch greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 65 minutes or until bread tests done with wooden pick.

title: rumaki
directions: Mix soy sauce, brown sugar, ginger root and garlic in glass or plastic bowl.
Stir in chicken livers and water chestnuts.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours, stirring occasionally; drain.

title: apple cake in bundt pan
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients
in
quart baking dish. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until macaroni is tender.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pineapple-cheese casserole
directions: Pur off liquid and divide in half.
Mix chunks, cheese and half of the liquid in a large casserole.
Add sugar, flour and remaining liquid.
Pour over pineapple. Spread Ritz crumbs on top and spoon melted magarine on crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bacon stuffed potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes and dry.
Rub with oil and bake directly on oven rack at 400° until tender.
Slit and scoop out center. Place in a mixing bowl.
Add butter, sour cream, egg, salt and pepper.
Beat well.
Stir in bacon crumbs.
Pile mixture back into six potato shells, mounding high.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: cinnamon apple salad
directions: Heat candies in boiling water until dissolved.
Pour over jello to dissolve it, then add cold water.
Chill until partially set.
Add diced apples and celery. Put half this mixture in a casserole dish and refrigerate until set.
Cream cheese with milk and spread over the set portion of salad.
Add remaining jello.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Bring the first 5 ingredients to a boil and boil 3 minutes. Add remainder of ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Chill until set.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook your potatoes, onions, carrots, parsley and water for 20 to 30 minutes. Add margarine, evaporated milk, cream of chicken soup, salt and pepper. Cook for a few minutes longer.

title: chocolate peanutty swirls
directions: Place candy coating in a small microwave-safe bowl; microwave at High 1 minute or until coating melts, stirring once.
Set aside.

title: orange jello dessert
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13 pan with slices of pound cake. Whip the cream cheese with the Cool Whip and 1/2 cup sugar until creamy. Spread over pound cake. Drain oranges and crushed pineapple. Spread over creamy mixture. Mix the orange Jell-O as directed on package. Set 1 1/2 hours until it shakes. Spread Jell-O over fruit. Chill and serve.

title: peanut butter pick ups
directions: Microwave on High the corn syrup and sugar together 2 or 3 minutes or until bubbling. Stir in peanut butter. Mix well. Add 2 cups corn flakes. Drop out on wax paper in small clumps. Let cool.

title: lentil soup
directions: In a large stock pot, combine all the ingredients, except tomatoes. Cook for 1 1/2 hours.
Add the tomatoes and simmer for 30 minutes more. Serves 12.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Combine all ingredients together in bowl.
Spread in casserole dish; top with bread stuffing.
Cook for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: maxine wcykoff's peppers in ketchup
directions: Clean peppers; pack in pint jars.
Boil ingredients together for 5 minutes.
Pour over peppers in jars; put knife in jar so solution can go through peppers.
Seal and cold pack for 1 hour.

title: ribbon fantasy fudge
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups sugar, 6 tablespoons margarine and 1/3 cup milk in heavy 1 1/2-quart saucepan; bring to full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling 4 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat; stir in chocolate pieces until melted.
Add 1 cup (1/2 jar) Marshmallow Creme and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Repeat with remaining ingredients, substituting peanut butter for chocolate pieces.
Spread over chocolate layer.
Cool at room temperature. Cut into squares.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order given and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Lower heat to 300° and bake for 45 minutes or until firm.

title: blackened alaskan halibut
directions: Season both sides of the Alaskan halibut with the seafood seasoning. Heat a large skillet on high heat and add the oil. Place the Alaskan halibut fillets in the hot skillet and blacken for 3 minutes per side. Add the Fetzer Sundial Chardonnay and simmer until wine has evaporated. Serve immediately. Serves 2.

title: macaroni shrimp salad
directions: Mix together.
Add salad dressing or mayonnaise and mix well. I add sliced tomatoes and 1 sliced boiled egg and put salad dressing on tomatoes and egg on top.
Sprinkle top with paprika. You can also put a few olives on top if desired.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend milk and egg.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir in corn.
Drop by tablespoon into hot fat.
Deep fry for 2 to 5 minutes or until golden.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar in a bowl.
Heat margarine, cocoa and Coke to boiling.
Pour over flour and sugar mixture.
Put baking soda in buttermilk, then pour over flour mixture.
Add eggs, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Add marshmallows.
Batter will be thin with marshmallows floating on top.
Pour in ungreased cookie sheet or 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: taco pie
directions: Fry onion in oil.
Cook tomatoes, pepperoni, oregano and parsley just a little and drain. Add to onions. Spread cheese in pie crust. Cover with tomato mixture and more cheese.
Beat eggs, milk and basil.
Pour over. Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: cranberry quick cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, combine quick bread mix, oats, coconut, cranberries and orange peel; mix well.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and pour sweet potatoes, sugar, 1 cup sugar, eggs, vanilla and milk into baking dish.
Then combine brown sugar, flour, margarine and nuts, then sprinkle on first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: party mix
directions: Combine Crispix cereal, nuts and pretzels in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Set aside.
Stir together remaining ingredients.
Gently stir spices and margarine into cereal mixture until evenly coated. Bake at 250° for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Spread on paper towel to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: hollandaise dressing
directions: Beat egg yolks; add cream, salt, nutmeg, lemon juice and parsley (if desired).
Cook until thick, stirring constantly. Take off fire and stir in butter.
Serve immediately.
Serves 2.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Beat egg yolks well.
Add eggs, then milk, a little at a time, stirring all the time.
Place in double boiler over hot water and cook until thick.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Stir.
Pour into cooled baked pie shell.
Top with meringue made with the 3 egg whites and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Bake at 350° about 12 minutes, or until meringue is golden brown.

title: bread pudding
directions: Break bread into
bits	in
a mixing bowl and soak with milk, let sit.
In
a
separate
bowl mix margarine, sugar and eggs, beat well with mixer or by hand.
Add bread and continue to mix (this time by hand).
Add cinnamon, nutmeg, raisins and drained fruit cocktail.
Mix
in
well.
Pour
batter
into
a baking pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hershey's light chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray two 8-inch round pans with cooking spray.
In bowl, stir flour, cocoa and baking soda.
In saucepan, melt oil; stir in sugar.
Remove from heat.
Add milk, vinegar and vanilla to mixture in saucepan.
Stir.
Add dry ingredients; pour evenly into pan.
Bake 20 minutes.
Cool and frost.
Low in fat, 3 g without frosting.

title: rutabaga spinach medley
directions: Cook rutabaga 25 minutes or until tender and drain well.
In a large bowl, beat rutabaga on medium speed of electric mixer until smooth.
Beat in margarine, salt, nutmeg and pepper.
Fold in thawed spinach souffle.
Turn mixture into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook and crumble sausage. Layer in order in 13 x 9 glass dish: hash browns with salt added, sausage, cheese, peppers. Beat eggs with milk and pour over the top. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: kirsch fruit dessert
directions: Mix fruit with grenadine syrup and Kirsch in a glass bowl or jar. Cover and refrigerate for 3 hours or more for flavors to blend. When ready to serve, divide the mixture between 4 dessert dishes. Top
each serving with a scoop of raspberry flavored sherbet. If desired, you may garnish the dessert with a mint leaf, however, if a variety of colorful contrasting fruit is available, omit the mint.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apple slices in a 12 x 7 1/2-inch dish.
Combine flour, brown sugar, oats, cinnamon and salt.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle evenly over sliced apples.
Microwave on High, uncovered, for 15 minutes or until apples are tender. Rotate dish halfway through microwave time.
Serve with ice cream (warm).

title: summer squash pie
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Press
bread crumbs into well oiled 9-inch pie pan.
Steam squash until tender;
puree until smooth. (Should have about 3 cups puree.) Saute onion in oil. Puree
the onion;
add
eggs, cottage cheese, cornmeal, salt, Swiss cheese and dill weed.
Add to pureed squash.
Pour into crumb-lined pie plate.
Sprinkle
with
finely
chopped
nuts. Bake 40 minutes or until done.
(Test with knife; done when it comes out clean.) Serves
Can
be
frozen,
then warmed in microwave oven.

title: southwestern rice
directions: Prepare rice according to directions.
In a large skillet, brown ground round and onion; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except rice and cheese.
Remove from heat.
Add cooked rice.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: seasoned collard greens
directions: Check leaves of collards and remove "pulpy" stems and discolored portions of the leaves.
Wash leaves carefully and drain well.
Chop.
Set aside.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Heat tomato soup and pour over jello.
Mix.
Add cold water. Mix, then add cream cheese, shrimp, celery, green pepper, mayonnaise, onion and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Place in refrigerator to set.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Add onion and celery.
Cook over low heat until tender.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Pour mixture into graham cracker pie crust.
Top with cool whip.
Chill for about 2 hours.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix peanuts, sugar, salt and syrup (Yellow Label or Golden Eagle syrup is great) together in a microwave bowl.

Cook on High for 8 minutes in microwave until bubbling and peanuts are browned. Quickly stir in butter and vanilla and cook 3 minutes more. Remove from microwave and add baking soda making sure you stir quickly until mixture is foamy.
Pour immediately onto a greased cookie sheet.
Cool 15 minutes or longer and break apart.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 1 pound.

title: lasagne
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients to form sauce.
Cook sauce until thick.
Mix together next 5 ingredients to form cheese mixture.

title: tuscon casserole
directions: Grease or Pam spray one 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Crush chips to cover bottom of pan.
Sprinkle chicken over chips.
Mix soups, salsa, chiles and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Crush another layer of chips.
Sprinkle cheese over chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Let set 10 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8. Good with salad and rolls or French bread loaf.

title: sugar-free squash pickles
directions: Cover vegetables with crushed ice; let stand for 3 hours.
Mix well and drain.
Bring vinegar and spices to boil.
Add vegetables; bring to boil.
Pack in hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: indian pudding
directions: Scald 3 cups of boiling water in top of double boiler.
Add cornmeal, sugar, spices, salt, molasses and butter.
Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens, approximately 20 minutes.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Add remaining cup of milk, without stirring.
Bake about 2 to 3 hours in 300° oven (slow).
Serve warm with milk, cream or ice cream. Makes 8 servings.

title: wassail
directions: Boil water.
Add tea bags and spices.
Simmer for 5 minutes. Remove tea bags and spices.
Add sugar and juices.
Bring to a boil.
Serve warm.
Store remainder in refrigerator.

title: apple walnut upside-down pie
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Spread on bottom of pie dish.
Add nuts.
Roll out half pie crust and place on top of brown sugar and nuts.
Put apples, cinnamon and sugar on crust.
Roll out top crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown on top.
Remove pie from oven and turn upside-down on plate.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Boil the brown sugar, syrup, oleo and salt for 5 minutes.
Add the soda and vanilla.
Mix with popcorn and bake in oven.
Stir every 15 minutes for 1 hour.
Add peanuts, if desired.

title: melt-away cheese rounds
directions: Cream butter in food processor or mixer until light and fluffy.
Add cheese, flour, salt and paprika or poppy seed.
Form into a dough.
Chill dough for about 2 hours.
Shape dough into small even balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with extra paprika or poppy seed, if desired.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Blend soup, milk and pepper.
In a buttered 1 1/2 quart casserole, arrange alternately layers of potatoes, onions, soup mix and cheese.
Dot top with butter; cover.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour; uncover and bake for 15 minutes until done.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: In a large bowl, blend in good the cake mix, sugar, nectar, oil and eggs.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: elephant stew
directions: 1. Cut elephant into bite sized pieces.
2. Add enough brown gravy to cover.
3. Cook over kerosene fire for 4 weeks.

title: chicken a la king(low in calories and fat)
directions: Cook chicken ahead and cut up.
Cook rice.
Saute chicken, onion, garlic and mushrooms in oil for 2 minutes.
Add to water, cornstarch, chicken base, salt, garlic powder, onion powder and allspice.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Let simmer about 5 minutes, until thickens.
Add blanched carrots and frozen peas.
Heat thoroughly.

title: great strawberry punch
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and mix good. Gently stir in soda before serving.

title: salmon ball(great with crackers)
directions: Mix.
Then roll in parsley and nuts and chill.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and pineapple; heat to boiling.
Stir.
Add jello; stir until dissolved.
Add cherries (with their liquid); stir.
Cool to room temperature.
Add bananas and nuts.
Spoon into pie shells and chill.
Serve with topping; garnish as desired.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: peach pie filling
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook until thick and dark in color.
Mash if desired.
Seal in glass jar.
Great for fried pies.

title: quick diet recipe
directions: In a large saucepan, combine onions, green peppers and 1/4 cup water.
Bring mixture to boiling, then reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 3 to 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: scalloped potatoes supreme
directions: Alternate layers of potatoes, green pepper and onion in baking dish.
Season each layer with salt and pepper.
Mix soup and milk; pour over potatoes.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Makes 8 servings.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Bring brown sugar, oleo and corn syrup to a boil in microwave (about 2 minutes).
Add baking soda and stir well.
Place popcorn in large size grocery bag.
Cover popcorn with caramel mixture and stir well.
Roll up bag and place back in microwave for 2 1/2 minutes on High, stopping once to stir.
