title: baked beans
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Bake 2 hours at 350°, stirring every 30 minutes.
(Freezes great.)

title: olive cheese balls
directions: Mix cheese and flour; mix in margarine.
Form this dough mixture, mold 1 teaspoonful around each olive.
Shape into a ball. Place on ungreased cookie sheet and refrigerate at least 1 hour. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: rosemary potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes well and cut into
bite-sized cubes or smaller as many potatoes as you want to cook.
Place potatoes in a large microwaveable dish or cook on medium heat with small amount of oil in a covered skillet or frying pan.
Chop your favorite onion and add to potatoes.
Scoop 2-3 large tablespoons of margarine into the potatoes and season everything with as much Tone's Rosemary Garlic Seasoning as you like.
Stir it all up in the dish and microwave on high for 5 minutes or stir occasionally if cooked on the stove.

title: spicy shrimp and chicken
directions: Saute bell pepper, onion and broccoli in olive oil.
Remove from pan.
Season shrimp with pepper, Accent and salt and saute in same pan used to saute broccoli, onion and bell pepper.
Add chicken and continue to cook on high heat, adding the remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook for 15 minutes, lowering the heat. Serve over rice.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Cut slice from top of bread loaf; remove center, leaving 1-inch shell.
Cut removed bread into bite size pieces.
Saute celery and onions in margarine until tender.
Add cheese; stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Stir in remaining ingredients;
heat thoroughly, stirring constantly.
Spoon into bread loaf.
Serve with veggie dippers and bread.
Makes 2 cups.

title: english muffin crab triangle
directions: Split English muffins.
Mix all remaining ingredients together and spread on halved English muffins.
Cut each half into quarters.
Heat under broiler until bubbly and brown, about 5 minutes.

title: gumdrop cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add 2 cups flour, spices, eggs and soda.
Sift 2 cups flour over fruit and gumdrops.
Add to creamed mixture.
Bake 2 hours in large angel food pan at 350°.

title: caramel corn
directions: Put air popped corn in brown paper bag that has been sprayed with Pam.
Cook oleo, brown sugar, Karo syrup and soda on High in microwave for 4 minutes.
Stir after 2 minutes.
Works best in Pyrex 4-cup measuring cup.
Pour over popped corn.
Put brown bag in microwave; cook on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove, shake bag and return to microwave.
Cook another 1/2 minute.
Shake; cook another 1/2 minute.
Pour onto cookie sheet; let set up.
Store in covered dish.

title: pineapple chess pie
directions: Beat eggs until broken and smooth.
Mix with sugar and other ingredients.
Cook in unbaked pie shell, first 15 minutes at 450° and then lower to 350°.
Bake about 45 minutes.

title: unstuffed cabbage
directions: Brown meat with onion, remove from heat and drain fat.
Add rice to meat mixture, and mix.
Place cabbage in bottom of 2 quart casserole, buttered.
Spread meat and rice over cabbage.
Blend soup, water, catsup and pour over meat and rice layer.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine, mix well and form into a loaf the first 5 ingredients.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Saute fine chopped onion in margarine until onions are soft and clear.
Fold in cream cheese.
Add crab meat and Tabasco sauce to taste.
Place in fondue type dish.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: apple delight
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan.
Put apples into pan.
Mix the remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together oil and sugar.
Add the beaten eggs and mix well. Add flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Continue mixing.
Fold in diced apples and chopped nuts.
Pour batter in a greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° about 60 minutes or when tested done.
Cool.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: cucumber soup
directions: Peel and remove seeds from cucumbers.
Place in boiling salted water to cover.
Simmer for 5 minutes; drain and chop.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour and stir.
Add stock; bring to a boil.
Add cucumbers, salt and pepper; simmer until cucumbers are tender.
Mix in blender and reheat to serve.

title: pork chops creole
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides.
Slice onion, saving center slices and chop the remaining onion.
Remove chops from pan.
Add water and bouillon cubes and stir until dissolved.
Add rice, onion, salt and spices.
Place chops on top with slice of tomato, bell pepper and onion on top of each chop.
Bake covered at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: boeuf bourguignon
directions: Combine beef cubes and wine and marinate for 2 to 3 hours (if time allows).
Add favorite spice.
Brown onions in bacon grease until clear.
Saute mushrooms in 3 tablespoons of butter; set aside.
Pat beef cubes dry (reserve wine).
Brown in favorite drippings.
Put in 5-quart casserole.
Saute onions and carrots in skillet.
Add flour.
Stir in beef broth, wine and tomato paste. Stir in salt, thyme, garlic, pepper and parsley; pour over beef in casserole.
Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours until tender.
Add mushroom and onion mixture.
Bake an additional 20 minutes. Serve over rice.
Makes approximately 8 to 10 servings.

title: sugar-free tomato soup cookies
directions: In bowl, soak raisins in hot water to cover for 5 minutes; drain.
Combine margarine, egg whites and soup in bowl.
Mix well. Stir in flour, oats, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, raisins and nuts.
Drop onto lightly greased cookie sheet. Flatten with fork, dipped in water.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool on cookie sheet for 2 minutes.
Remove to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: egg biscuits
directions: Beat sugar, oil and eggs together.
Add remaining ingredients. Roll in small balls, brush tops with beaten egg white.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar well.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add food coloring.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Add dry ingredients and buttermilk alternately, starting and ending with flour.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a tube pan.
Cool before frosting.

title: colonial pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, sugar, salt, spices and molasses.
Mix thoroughly. Add eggs and milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 425° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: fast food biscuits
directions: Work butter into flour and add milk.
Roll out on floured board and cut out biscuits. Bake at 450° until brown.

title: buttermilk sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let come to a boil.
Then cook for 5 minutes.
Pour over warm cake or over ice cream.

title: 4 o'clock buns
directions: Soak yeast in 1 cup warm water.
Boil water, salt and sugar 5 minutes.
Add lard and cool.
Add eggs and 4 cups flour, then yeast and remaining flour.
Start at 4 o'clock, knead at 6 o'clock and make buns at 9 o'clock; let rise overnight.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.
These are great for breakfast.

title: tar heel chocolate pie
directions: Pour warm butter over chocolate chips in medium bowl, stirring until chocolate chips are melted.
Add sugar, brown sugar, eggs, flour and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until set.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine peanut butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla; beat until creamy. Beat in milk and egg.
Gradually add flour mix; mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and peanuts; drop onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: hamburger rice chow mein
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in casserole dish and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Remove from oven, add can of chow mein noodles and bake for another 30 minutes at 350°.
(This will seem like a lot of water, but as the rice cooks, it will thicken.)
Makes 8 servings.

title: german caramel cake
directions: Mix the cake according to directions on box of cake mix. Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour half of mixture in pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: banana muffins
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and cream all.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well. Grease your cake cups and pour into the cake cups.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal sandwich cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In mixer bowl, beat 2 1/2 cups margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs and 3 teaspoons vanilla, then combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Stir in oats. Drop by tablespoonfuls on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake 10 minutes or until set.
Cool.
In saucepan, combine chips, sweetened condensed milk, remaining 2 tablespoons margarine and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Over medium heat, cook and stir until chips melt.
Immediately sandwich cookies together with mixture.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: For roux, in a large, heavy saucepan, combine flour and oil until smooth.
Cook over medium-high heat for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat to medium.
Cook and stir about 15 minutes more or until roux is reddish brown.
Stir in onion, celery or green pepper, garlic, black pepper and red pepper.
Cook over medium heat for 3 to 5 minutes or until vegetables are just crisp-tender, stirring often.
Gradually stir in hot chicken broth, okra and bay leaves.
Add shrimp and crab during the last 5 minutes of cooking.

title: oyster and mushroom chowder, 1939
directions: Heat oysters in own liquor below boiling point until edges curl.
Drain, saving liquor.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter, blend in flour.
Add milk gradually, stirring constantly; bring to boil and cook 1 minute.
Add cream, shallots, parsley, salt and pepper. Heat cleaned mushrooms in the remaining butter until hot, but do not brown.
Add mushrooms, oysters and oyster liquor to cream sauce.
Serve hot.

title: tiny grinders
directions: Slightly grease bottom of pan. Layer one roll of crescent rolls. Layer 1/4 pound of salami, ham and Provolone cheese.
Beat eggs and add grated cheese.
Pour over layers.
Layer remaining salami, ham and Provolone cheese.
Spread jar of fried peppers. Layer second package of crescent rolls.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chelle's orange smoothie
directions: Mix well and serve immediately.

title: sausage-zucchini casserole
directions: Cut zucchini lengthwise, remove seeds, cut and dice.
Brown sausage and onion; drain grease.
Add remaining ingredients except Parmesan cheese, mix well and put in a greased casserole. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mother's jam cake
directions: Mix whole eggs, which have been beaten, with the melted butter, buttermilk, brown sugar and blackberry jam. Add flour which has been sifted with the cinnamon, allspice and nutmeg. Add nuts and fold in. Bake in a 9-inch tube pan or two 8-inch or 9-inch layer pans, greased with a mixture of 1 part flour and 2 parts shortening rubbed together. Bake at 325 degrees until done. Let cool slightly, about 5 minutes, and turn it out on a cake rack. While still warm, add bourbon to the bottom of the cake. Pierce the cake & let the bourbon seep into the middle of the cake so it will be a drunken jam cake.

title: creamy peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk to soft ball stage over low heat; remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla and marshmallow cream. Beat until it starts to set.
Pour into buttered dish.
Cool, then cut into squares.

title: cheesy tomato pie
directions: Mix milk and Bisquick together well in Pyrex pie dish and form into a pie crust.
Add remaining ingredients in layers in order listed.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes and allow to cool for 10 to 15 minutes before cutting.
Serves 4.

title: spinach fantastic
directions: Cook rice as per directions.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Thaw and blot dry the spinach.
Combine all ingredients in a bowl and stir well.
Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Put mixture in casserole.
Bake uncovered for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time; beat well. Sift flour; re-measure 2 1/2 cups.
Add salt and baking powder. Save 1/2 cup for flouring blueberries.
Add dry ingredients in 4 parts on low speed of mixer.
Fold in floured blueberries.

title: guacamole
directions: Mash tomato, onion, optional ingredients, and salt to form a coarse paste.
Cut avocados in half, remove pits and scoop into the paste.
Mash a little more just until mixture is blended and avocados are mashed into 1/2 inch chunks.
Serve immediately or cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix ingredients together with mixer (make sure you let cream cheese soften first).
Refrigerate overnight.

title: yankee tea
directions: Steep tea bags about 20 minutes and pour cold water over bags. Put sugar, lemonade and orange juice in gallon jar.
Add tea and fill with water.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding, Crisco oil, water, sour cream and eggs until well blended.
Add chocolate chips and grated chocolate. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler.
Add to sausage and Bisquick. Mix well with hands.
Roll into bite size balls.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.

title: norwegian parsley potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling, salted water for 15 minutes or until tender.
Cool slightly.
With sharp knife, remove one narrow strip of skin around the middle of each potato.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, butter and syrup together. Boil 5 minutes.
Take off heat and add 1/2 teaspoon baking soda. Pour over popcorn and bake for 15 minutes.
Take out of oven and stir really good.
Return to oven for another 15 minutes (peanuts can also be added to this).

title: pineapple and cheese casserole
directions: 1st Layer:
2 (14 ounce) cans pineapple chunks (juice and all).

title: cranberry jewel salad
directions: Mix jello and boiling water. Add cranberry sauce and pineapple; set in refrigerator. When jello starts to congeal, add apple and nuts. No topping on this originally, but it tastes good with the topping from the blueberry salad.

title: luncheon salad
directions: Dissolve gelatine in 3 tablespoons of cold water.
Dissolve cheese in soup over low heat.
Add gelatine mix and cool.
Add other ingredients and pour into an 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Let set until firm.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaf.
Serve with saltine crackers.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, margarine, cream cheese and sugar. Beat with an electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add salt and vanilla.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, and beat well after each addition.
Mix in flour.

title: batter for chicken or vegetable to deep-fry
directions: Beat egg.
Add flour, water, salt and pepper.
Can add 1/2 teaspoon cornstarch for some vegetables.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake on large cookie sheet at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon graham crackers
directions: Sift together first four ingredients.
Cream until light brown sugar and butter.
Beat in honey and vanilla.
Add alternately with flour mixture the milk.
Chill at least one hour.
Divide dough in quarters.
Roll thinly on well floured board.
Cut into 3 x 5-inch rectangles.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Score with fork.
Combine cinnamon and sugar; sprinkle on each rectangle. Bake 13 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage twirls
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in Crisco until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in milk.
Turn dough on floured surface. Knead 1 or 2 times.
Lightly roll dough to 1/8-inch thickness, 17 1/2-inches long and 8 inches wide.
Cook sausage enough to get grease out so that you can spread easily and evenly.
Sprinkle sausage onto dough.
Roll dough jelly roll fashion.
Starting from the long end, cut in 1/2-inch slices.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Beat in eggs.
Add soda, buttermilk, vanilla and lemon.
Add flour; mix well.
Bake in Bundt pan (greased and floured).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until done.

title: cabbage au gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook cabbage in boiling salted water for 10 minutes.
Drain.
Put into baking dish.
Blend soup, milk and cheese.
Pour over cabbage.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Lightly grease oblong pan.
Sprinkle nuts in pan, then coconut.
Mix cake according to directions and spread on coconut. Mix melted margarine, sugar and cream cheese and spread on top of cake.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate carmelita bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine first six ingredients.
Mix well.
Reserve 1 cup; press remaining onto bottom of prepared pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown; cool 10 minutes.
Top with nuts and chocolate.
Mix caramel and 1/4 cup flour until smooth; drizzle over chocolate to within 1/4 inch of pan edges.
Sprinkle with reserved mixture.
Bake an additional 18 to 22 minutes until golden.
Cool completely.
Yields 32 bars.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Boil the chicken breasts until tender.
Chop into bite size pieces. Layer in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish the green beans, chicken soup, cooked chicken pieces and dressing mix. Bake in a 325° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: nanny ruby's chocolate pie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and cook over very low heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove and add 1 tablespoon butter or margarine and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla; mix well.
Pour in baked crust.
Top with meringue and bake until meringue begins to brown.

title: robert redford dessert
directions: Mix ingredients together and put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: quick banana pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix until well blended.
Beat at medium speed 4 minutes.
Turn batter in greased, lightly floured Bundt pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour. If desired, dust with confectioners sugar.

title: meat loaf
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Mix well the meat, beaten eggs, salt, bread crumbs, chopped onion, tomatoes and catsup.
Shape into a loaf. Place in loaf pan and place the bacon strips on the top.
Bake for about 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheeseburger rice
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain fat. Stir in cooked rice, ketchup, mustard, salt and pepper. Add 3/4 cup of shredded cheese. Heat through.

title: sausage strata(for breakfast)
directions: Cook sausage over high heat, stirring frequently, until brown. Drain off grease. Set aside.

title: diabetic fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in a loaf pan at 300° for 45 minutes.
This makes 18 slices of which equals out to 1 fat, 1 bread and 1/2 fruit.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: No water or liquid.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Add sugar, vanilla, salt and cream to eggs.
Beat until well mixed.
Add milk (fill with).
Ready to put into ice cream freezer. Makes 1 gallon.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar and milk together.
Turn oven on to 350°. Take a 9 x 13-inch pan and melt the stick of butter in pan.
When it is all melted, put the mixed batter into the pan.
Layer the peaches in the pan.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: creamy lemon custard ice cream
directions: Bring the cream, half and half, sugar and zest just to a boil over medium heat in a heavy medium saucepan, stirring to dissolve the sugar.
Whisk the egg yolks and salt together in a medium bowl. Add 1/2 cup of the cream mixture to the yolk mixture and whisk until blended.

In a slow, steady stream, add the remaining cream mixture, whisking constantly, and continue whisking until blended. Return the mixture to the saucepan and cook, stirring, over medium-low heat until the custard thickens and leaves a path on the back of a wooden spoon when a finger is drawn across it; do not allow the mixture to boil.
Immediately pour the custard through a strainer into a bowl and stir in the vanilla.
Let cool to room temperature, whisking occasionally.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel potatoes and onions and thinly slice.
Layer potatoes, onion and soup in baking dish.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 250° until potatoes and onions are tender.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake until cheese is melted.

title: happy family casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well except noodles and bread crumbs. Once mixed well, fold in noodles gently and pour into well-buttered casserole.
Place bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: party potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes and cream.
Add all the ingredients and blend well.
Put in a 2 to 2 1/2-quart dish.
Sprinkle 1 cup of shredded cheese on top.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: Combine ingredients and marinate in refrigerator for 24 hours. Serve chilled with cocktail picks.

title: chicken, broccoli and vegetable saute
directions: Brown chicken in melted butter.
Take chicken out of butter. Cook broccoli, carrots and onions in same pan with butter.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Put chicken back in pan with the broccoli and carrots.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Simmer cream of broccoli soup with the milk for 10 minutes; add salt and pepper.
Pour broccoli mixture over chicken and simmer until done.

title: m&m candies super cookies
directions: Coarsely chop 1 1/2 cups M&M's candies.
Reserve remaining candies for decorations.

title: "auntie's" french toast
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in blender.
Place bread, edges touching, single layer in 9 x 13 baking dish.
Pour liquid mixture.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
When ready to cook, pour melted butter evenly over slices.
Sprinkle evenly with orange peel and pecans.
Bake in 400° oven until golden, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mexican wedding cookies(makes 2 dozen)
directions: Mix butter in mixer until fluffy. Slowly add flour. Add pecans, 1/4 cup 10x confectioners sugar and orange extract. Mix well. Use one level tablespoon for each cookie; shape into balls and place 2-inches apart on a greased baking sheet. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes. Transfer to a wire rack with wax paper under. Dust cookies with remaining 10x sugar. These cookies freeze well.

title: elegant chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken with salt, pepper and vermouth; allow to cool in that liquid.
Remove chicken from bone; skin and cut into 3/4-inch cubes.
Thoroughly combine chicken with the remaining ingredients except corn flakes.
Allow to stand at least 1 hour; add additional seasoning, if desired.
Spoon into a greased baking dish, about 8 x 12-inch.
(It can be refrigerated at this point.) Top with crushed corn flakes and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated and very lightly browned.
Makes approximately 12 to 15 servings.

title: egg rolls
directions: Mix sherry, cornstarch
and soy sauce.
Pour over meat. Marinate 30 to 45 minutes.
Shred cabbage, carrots, celery and onion.
Salt and pepper.
Set aside.

title: millionaires
directions: Melt caramels in milk over low heat; add pecans.
Drop by teaspoons onto buttered wax paper.
Chill.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips in heavy saucepan over low heat.
Dip candy into chocolate and return to waxed paper.
Chill.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: pan broiled steak
directions: Brown steaks on both sides in margarine on high heat.
Reduce heat to medium.
Add lemon and salt.
Cook for 10 to 15 minutes or until done.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Line bottom of baking dish with dried beef. Wrap each breast with bacon.
Mix sour cream and soup together with a dash of Kitchen Bouquet.
Pour over chicken and bake at 300° for 3 hours.

title: combination fruit salad
directions: Press the juice out of the crushed pineapple.
To the juice, add orange sections.
Cover and soak overnight in refrigerator. Add carrots, pineapple and apples.
Mix well.

title: mock fruit ice cream
directions: Mash berries with a fork.
Blend into sour cream.
Mix in pineapple and sugar and blend thoroughly.
Spoon into a mold. Freeze 3 to 4 hours.
Delicious!
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: crock-pot stew
directions: Layer in crock-pot as listed.
Cook all day on low or on high for 4 hours.

title: winter salad bowl
directions: Tear endive and head lettuce into bite-sized pieces in large bowl.
Arrange orange slices and onion rings on top of greens. Saute 1/2 cup walnuts in 2 tablespoons butter or margarine; add with dressing and toss.

title: icebox fruitcake
directions: Work all of this together.
Line a container with wax paper. Press ingredients in well.
Keep in refrigerator and slice as desired.

title: crab dip
directions: Heat soup (no water).
Dissolve gelatine in 3 tablespoons cold water.
Remove soup from stove.
Add gelatine.
Blend cheese and mayonnaise into soup mixture.
Add rest of ingredients.
Put in mold that is sprayed with nonstick spray.
Good, especially with small crackers.

title: 7-layer taco dip
directions: Mix refried beans and seasoning mix in an 8 x 11-inch casserole.
Spread out evenly in dish.
Spread 1 carton of sour cream over the beans.
Spread guacamole over the sour cream.
Add a layer of chopped tomatoes (as much as you like).
Add a layer of chopped green chilies.
Add a layer of chopped green onions.
Top it all off with shredded Monterey Jack cheese.
Serve with Doritos or Fritos.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy and 1 stick margarine in double boiler.
Set aside, but keep warm.
Cream 1 stick margarine with sugar.
Add eggs. Add flour, buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Fold in candy, pecans and butter mixture.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: swedish pineapple cake
directions: Mix in order by hand.
Pour into ungreased, unfloured 13x9x2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef and vegetable loaves(club member: laine)
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients with 1 can tomato sauce.
Form into 6 loaves.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove excess fat.
Combine gravy mix with remaining can tomato sauce and water.
Pour over loaves.
Bake 15 minutes longer. Serves 6.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Put in buttered baking dish. Crumble buttered corn flake crumbs on top.
Bake in a 350° oven until well heated and bubbly.

title: pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour tube pan.
In a large bowl, beat sugar and butter with electric beater at medium speed. Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each egg.
Add dry ingredients, milk and vanilla.
Beat 3 minutes.
Pour into tube pan and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
When done, cake should pull away from side of pan.
Cool 15 minutes on rack before removing from pan.

title: yummies
directions: Heat sugar and corn syrup in a saucepan until mixture bubbles. Stir in 6 cups Rice Krispies.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with melted chocolate and butterscotch mixed.

title: golden potato casserole
directions: Peel and grate potatoes into a large bowl with onions and grated cheese.
Heat can of Cheddar cheese soup with 1/4 cup butter until melted.
Remove and blend in sour cream.
Add to potatoes and stir lightly.
Cook in a buttered casserole dish. Dot with butter.
Sprinkle corn flakes over top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: barb's potato salad
directions: Refrigerate potatoes and eggs for several hours.
Mix first 6 ingredients and chill for several hours.
Combine all ingredients. Garnish with sliced egg, radishes and parsley and serve.

title: pumpkin pudding
directions: Mix ingredients in a blender until smooth.
Pour the blended ingredients into a 9-inch square baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean. Chill thoroughly.

title: old fashioned rice pudding
directions: In 4-quart pot, put rice, water and salt.
Bring to boil. Turn down.
Stir until most of water is absorbed.
Add 2 quarts milk.
Bring to a boil.
Turn down to medium heat, stirring constantly, for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: grandma betty's raspberry cookies
directions: Beat cheese, butter, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Blend in flour.
Press dough and roll out.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool; fill in jam.
Dough can be refrigerated to make rolling out easier.

title: sesame rainbow trout
directions: Clean, wash and dry fish.
Place in well-greased, hinged wire grills.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Baste fish with sauce. Cook about 4 inches from hot coals for 8 minutes.
Baste with sauce.
Turn and cook 7 to 10 minutes longer or until fish easily flakes when tested with a fork.
Serves 6.

title: cheese fruit cup
directions: Combine melon cubes and peach slices.
Chill.
With a teaspoon, shape cream cheese into 12 balls.
Roll in chopped nuts. Arrange fruit mixture in individual dishes.
Garnish with cream cheese balls.
Serves 6.

title: scallop noodle casserole
directions: Roll scallops in flour and brown in oil; add remaining ingredients.
Pour into baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rocky road
directions: In medium saucepan, slowly melt chocolate over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; beat smooth.
Stir in marshmallows and nuts.
Spread in buttered 8 x 8x 2-inch pan. Chill, then cut into squares.
Makes about 2 to 2 1/2 pounds. (Can be rolled and cut in slices.)

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix white sugar, flour and soda. Add juice from fruit cocktail and eggs. Beat until fluffy. Fold in fruit cocktail, and pour into a greased 9X13 pan. Sprinkle brown sugar over top of batter.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix together ground beef, rice, onion, salt and pepper.
Form into 8 balls and place in greased baking dish having a tight-fitting cover.
In a saucepan, combine the tomato sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Heat to boiling and pour over meatballs. Cover and bake at 350° about 1 1/4 hours or until visible rice is tender when pressed lightly between fingers.
Serve with tomato sauce.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pumpkin cream cheese bread
directions: Combine sugar, cream cheese and margarine, mixing at medium speed on electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Blend in pumpkin.
Add combined dry ingredients, mixing just until moistened.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 5 minutes; remove from pans.

title: corn fritters
directions: Add all measured, sifted and mixed dry ingredients to corn in a bowl.
Add egg, then melted butter.
Pour about an inch of oil into skillet and heat to frying temperature.
Drop batter by teaspoonfuls into oil.
Turn to brown.
Drain on paper towels and serve hot.	Yields 10 to 15 fritters.

title: oven chicken
directions: Boil chicken and take off of bone.
Reserve broth for later use.
Put chicken on bottom of baking dish.
Add 2 1/2 cups to 3 cups of chicken broth to 1 can of soup.
Pour over chicken. Combine flour, baking powder, milk and melted butter together. Pour over chicken and soup.
Bake in 425° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Crust will rise to top.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Simmer chicken in enough water to cover; add salt and pepper to taste.
Add 1 whole onion and 2 ribs celery; cook until tender. Remove onion, celery, bones and skin of chicken; set aside and reserve the stock for next step.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine
first	7 ingredients, stirring until moist but still lumpy.
Fold
in blueberries.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full. Sprinkle
with sugar.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes. Makes 12 muffins.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Make white sauce of all ingredients, except asparagus and eggs.
Alternate in casserole layers of asparagus, sliced eggs and white sauce.
Top with sauce.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and bake in a 400° oven until brown.

title: 7-up red satin punch
directions: Chill fruit juices and 7-Up.
At serving time, combine fruit juices and pineapple juice concentrate in a punch bowl.
Slowly pour in chilled 7-Up.
Add ice.
Makes about 3 3/4 quarts or 30 (4 ounce) servings.

title: beverly's sugar cookies
directions: Combine sugars, margarine and oil.
Add eggs.
Sift flour and dry ingredients.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.
Add to sugar mixture. Roll into balls the size of a walnut.
Roll in granulated sugar. Place on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with glass dipped in sugar. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes without paring them.
When tender, drain and remove the skins.
Cut in half lengthwise and arrange in a buttered baking dish.
Heat remaining ingredients.
Add to potatoes.
Bake in heated oven at 375° until potatoes are brown.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix mashed bananas, egg and sugar in a medium to large size bowl.
Add butter and mix until blended.
Sift together
flour, soda and salt.
Add sifted ingredients to first mixture.
Blend thoroughly.
Pour into greased 3 x 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: quick apple crisp
directions: Spread apples for pies in square cake pan.
Sprinkle on top the cake mix.
Melt oleo or butter.
Pour evenly over dry cake mix.
Bake at 350° to 375° until crispy.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Saute onion, celery and pepper.
Add ground beef and cook until it loses the pink color.
Add remaining ingredients and cook, covered, over medium heat 30 to 45 minutes.
Stir often.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Toss lightly the chopped vegetables with chopped seafood and mushrooms.
Mix mayonnaise with seasoning and 1 cup stuffing mix.

title: baked squash
directions: Cook squash and onion in small amount of water until tender. Drain if necessary.
Mash squash.
Add other ingredients.
Put in greased baking dish.
Cover with grated cheese and bread crumbs if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until light brown.

title: snack goodies
directions: Put in pans in slow oven (200°) for 1 hour.
Pour out onto paper towels or brown paper sacks.
Soak off excess oil.
Yield: A whole bunch.

title: cucumbers and onions
directions: In a bowl, combine mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar and salt. Add cucumbers and onions. Stir to coat. Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours. Serves 6.

title: meat pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix meat, onion, salt, pepper and water; cook in saucepan for 45 minutes. Add seasoning and potatoes. Put ingredients into 2 pie crusts. Bake small pies for 30 minutes; large pies for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: french silk frosting
directions: In small mixer bowl, blend sugar, butter, chocolate and vanilla
on
low speed.
Gradually add milk; beat until smooth and fluffy.
Makes enough for 2 (9-inch) layers or 3 (8-inch) layer cakes.

title: easy layer dessert
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans well.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes until browned; cool.
Beat cream cheese with powdered sugar.
Fold in 2 cups Cool Whip. Spread over cooled crust.
Beat pudding with 3 cups cold milk (mixture will be very thick).
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Cover.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: healthy fruit muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large bowl and wet ingredients in smaller bowl.
Add the mashed bananas to wet mixture.
Add raisins, blueberries and cranberries to the dry mix and stir thoroughly.
Add chopped apples to dry mixture.
After both bowls are well mixed, pour the milk mixture into the dry mix, barely incorporating the wet and dry mixes.
Spoon into 24 muffin tins. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream sugar, oil and shortening.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Add flour mixture and apples alternately to sugar mixture.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: snowballs
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix Bisquick, butter, nuts and flavoring. Add water and stir together.
Shape into balls (about 24).
Bake 10 minutes.
While still warm, roll each ball in confectioners sugar.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: pepper jelly
directions: I didn't have potatoes

title: sweet baked yams
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in buttered brownie pan.

title: baked corn
directions: Blend sugar, salt and flour.
Add 2 beaten eggs, milk and corn. Pour into buttered casserole.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: peanut butter vegetable soup(a colorful vegetable soup)
directions: In large saucepan heat oil.
Add celery, carrots, onion and red pepper; saute until tender.
Stir in flour.
Gradually add chicken
broth,
stirring
until smooth.
Bring to a boil. Stir in peanut butter until smooth;
simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes,
milk,
sherry
and
lemon juice.
Heat through. Season with salt and pepper.
Garnish with chopped peanuts, as desired. Yields 7 servings.

title: hamburger barbecue
directions: Fry beef; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer and serve on hamburger buns.

title: moby dick's crab cakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients in small bowl.
Mix wet ingredients in separate bowl.
Mix wet and dry ingredients together.
Let mixture set until it turns to jello thickness.
Mix crab meat in carefully; do not break up crab lumps.
Place piles of crab mixture onto greased baking pan.
Broil until golden.

title: kings ranch chicken
directions: Pour mixture over chicken, cheese and tortilla and bake.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: rouladen
directions: Salt and pepper steak.
Cover steak with bacon slices and chopped onion.
Roll like jellyroll and tie securely with string. Dredge in flour.
Brown in roasting pan.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add water as necessary.
Makes delicious gravy.

title: cheesy bacon chicken
directions: Pour in casserole dish the chicken broth.
On broth, place the chicken with bacon (1 strip) wrapped around pieces (2 pieces per person).
Place a slice of Swiss cheese and a dollop of sour cream on each bacon wrapped piece.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Delicious.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix together orange juice, water and sugar.
Add pineapple and bananas.
Let freeze until solid.
To serve, thaw until slushy.

title: barbecued pork sandwiches
directions: In a Dutch oven, combine meat, onions, chili powder, salt, water, ketchup and vinegar. Cover and simmer for 4 hours or until the meat falls apart easily. Skim off the excess fat.
With a slotted spoon, remove meat, reserving cooking liquid. Shred the meat with two forks.
Return to the cooking liquid and heat through. Serve on rolls.
Yields 16 servings.
Freeze in serving size portions for a quick and easy meal.

title: macaroni sauce
directions: Cut up about 4 to 5 pieces of garlic.
Brown in pan; add 1/2 onion.
Brown as well.
Add in tomato puree and remaining ingredients.
Let simmer for 1 to 2 hours.

title: no fail meringue
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar, water and salt.
Cook until thick.
Set aside to cool.
Beat egg whites until fluffy.
Continue beating while pouring in the cooked mixture and beat for five minutes. Pour on top of pie and bake for 5 to 7 minutes, until slightly browned.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: Combine pineapple juice, orange juice, cranberry juice, water, lemon juice and sugar to taste.
Mix well; heat.
Yield:
20 servings.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Combine corn flakes and melted butter.
Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake in a 350° preheated oven for 1 hour.
This can be frozen before it is baked.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables until tender.
Drain.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Mix together mayo, cheese and onion.
Spread over vegetables.
Mix crushed cracker crumbs with margarine and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tomato paste or sauce
directions: Wash
and cook tomatoes, onions, celery, parsley flakes and red pepper; run through strainer.
Add sugar, cornstarch, salt and butter.
Put in kettle and bring to a boil.
Boil for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours; stir often.
Put into clean sterilized jars.

title: pumpkin cake pudding
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in pumpkin and molasses.
Sift together flour, salt, soda, baking powder and spices.
Blend into pumpkin mixture alternately with orange juice.
Stir in nuts and orange rind. Turn into a greased and waxed paper lined 9-inch square pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
May be served with whipped cream or topping.
This is great with cream cheese icing.

title: double chocolate chewies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch x 13-inch pan.
Combine cake mix, eggs, and melted butter in large bowl.
Stir until thoroughly blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Press evenly into pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool completely.
Cut into bars.

title: rhubarb cherry jam
directions: Combine rhubarb and sugar.
Let stand overnight.
The next day, cook rhubarb mixture until rhubarb is tender, about 30 minutes. Stir in cherry pie filling and cherry gelatin.
Bring to a boil. Cool. Put in containers and refrigerate or freeze until ready to be served.

title: jello fluff
directions: Whip all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight.

title: kling's kielbasa
directions: Crock-pot is ideal for this recipe.
